title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef with celery.
Add onion.
Mix other ingredients well.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Brown.
Combine the remaining ingredients.
Pour over meatballs.
Keep warm in crock-pot.

title: white sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven at 375 degrees.
Mix all by hand until crumbly mixture, don't over mix.
Pat down dough onto floured pan roll flat 1/8 inch thick or 1/4 inch thick.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: low-fat sausage casserole
directions: Spray saute pan with low-fat cooking spray and saute turkey, onion, celery and green pepper.
When done, drain.
In a two-quart casserole dish, put chicken broth, uncooked rice and sausage mix. Top with undiluted soup; cover and bake for one hour at 325°.

title: crab muffins
directions: In a large saut pan, melt butter and add garlic powder, mayonnaise, Old English cheese, Tony Chachere seasoning, cayenne pepper and spring onions.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Add crabmeat and heat thoroughly.
Spread generously on English muffin halves.
Place on a cookie sheet and place in freezer until firm. Stir in Ziploc storage bags.

title: pasta with spinach alfredo sauce
directions: In small saucepan, place butter and cream to boil. Simmer 1 minute and reduce to low to thicken slightly. In separate pan, bring water to a boil and follow pasta package instructions. Drain when finished. In another saucepan, boil small amount of water; boil spinach a few minutes and drain very well, squeezing out excess water. In same pan, rinse and dry, then add olive oil and chopped garlic. Saute briefly, then add drained spinach and mix well.

title: fluffy pancakes
directions: Separate 3 eggs; beat yolks in large mixing bowl, using mixer. When thick and fluffy, beat in buttermilk and soda.
Sift together and beat in flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Beat in butter or oil.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake on preheated grids until bubbly.
Makes about 15 pancakes.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs together.
Add sugar and melted butter.
Add extract and other ingredients.
Bake in 2 unbaked 8-inch pie crusts until light brown.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 unbaked shells. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: mediterranean artichoke-chicken-rice salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve over lettuce.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Cook potatoes until tender enough to mash.
Mix other ingredients with potatoes; put in dish and bake until thick. Cover with marshmallows and brown.

title: piquant sauce for meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread on top of meatloaf and bake.

title: angel food strawberries
directions: Beat Dream Whip stiff and fold in remaining ingredients.
Tear up angel food cake into bite size and pour mixture over and serve.

title: cream cheese and chives chicken breast
directions: Pound chicken breasts, not too thin.
Place margarine and generous portion of cream cheese and chives.
Roll chicken breasts.
Wrap with 1 slice bacon.
Cook at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve lime and raspberry jello separately using 1 1/2 cups boiling water for each package.
Pour into separate 8-inch square pans; chill until firm.
Cut into small cubes.
Combine marshmallows, pineapple and jello mixing lightly.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into spring-form pan lined with ladyfingers, split and cut in half.
Chill several hours and serve.
Can be mixed as a salad eliminating ladyfingers.
This salad is pretty for Christmas.

title: banana chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, vanilla and eggs.
Add flour, soda, salt, bananas and chips.
Mix together and drop by spoonfuls on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Cream the oleo. Add brown sugar and white sugar; cream until fluffy.
Add the eggs and beat well.
Mix oats in 1 1/2 cups boiling water and let stand 20 minutes. Add to creamed mixture along with 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Last add the flour and soda. Beat well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: roast pork
directions: Take pork ham and cut off all skin.
Cut holes with a knife deep enough to put index finger in.
Fill each hole with green onions and garlic.
Season with salt and pepper.
Wrap in foil paper.
Bake at 350° for 4 hours.
Slice to serve.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt together peanut butter, chocolate chips and margarine. Pour over cereal and mix together.
Put confectioners sugar in a large bag.
Add cereal mixture and shake.

title: chocolate crisp
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
After all chocolate is melted, take off burner.
Add Rice Krispies, peanuts and pecans. Stir until blended together well.
Spoon out on waxed paper. Leave until dry.

title: chicken parisienne
directions: Mix together last 4 ingredients.
Pour mixed items over chicken breasts.
Sprinkle top generously with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
(Serve with rice and molded fruit salad.)

title: taco meat
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add tomato sauce, 3/4 of taco sauce and other ingredients.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with flour tortillas or taco shells, tomatoes, lettuce and cheese.
Use remaining taco sauce to pour over other ingredients.

title: pineapple chicken lo mein
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/3 cup juice; set pineapple aside.
In a large skillet over medium heat, cook the chicken and ginger in 2 Tbsp. oil for 6 minutes.
Add the pineapple and vegetables.
Cover and cook for 2 to 3 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender and chicken juices run clear.
Stir in spaghetti. In a small bowl, combine the cornstarch, soy sauce, corn syrup, pineapple juice and remaining oil until smooth.
Stir into chicken mixture.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: wacky cake
directions: Combine
flour, sugar, cocoa, soda, salt and vanilla in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Makes 3 holes in mixture.
Put oil in one hole, vinegar
in
one
hole and water in the third hole. Mix with fork; swirl.
Bake
at
for
to 35 minutes. When done, sprinkle powdered sugar over the cake.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Put all ingredients in a mixing bowl and add a pinch of salt. Use seeded raisins.
They make the cookies much better.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil chicken.
Tear into strips or small pieces.
Place chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix sour cream and soup together.
Pour over top of chicken.
Add poppy seed and melted butter to crackers.
Sprinkle cracker mixture on top of chicken mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal scotchies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat butter, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla or orange peel until creamy.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in oats and butterscotch morsels.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Peel eggplants and slice into 1/2-inch slices.
Fry in oil until lightly browned.
Drain on paper towels.
Cover bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch buttered pan with a layer of eggplant slices. Combine tomato paste and water, mixing well.
Pour over eggplants. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, mushrooms and Mozzarella cheese. Repeat layers, ending with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in a 400° oven for 20 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.
Makes 10 servings.

title: cheese grits
directions: Boil grits in water, milk and salt in a heavy pan.
Stir often until stiff.
Stir diced/grated cheese into hot grits.
Add butter.
Cool.
Blend eggs into mixture.
Season to taste with salt, Tabasco, Worcestershire sauce, pepper and paprika.

title: mexi-dip
directions: Mix dairy sour cream, Cheddar cheese and chili powder.
Spread over ground beef mixture when cooled.
Sprinkle with shredded lettuce and grated Cheddar cheese.
Serve with corn chips.
Makes 3 1/2 cups dip.

title: green beans with rosemary
directions: Cook bacon in microwave; add margarine and rosemary; set aside.
Cook beans, potatoes and onion in water, in oven, covered. When cooked to suit taste, pour bacon, margarine and rosemary over beans.

title: whole wheat dinner rolls
directions: Blend hot water, salt, honey and vegetable oil in mixer bowl. Mix in 6 cups whole wheat flour.
Sprinkle yeast over top.
Mix in 5 to 7 cups more whole wheat flour until dough cleans side of bowl.
Knead on slow speed for 10 minutes.

title: joseph's favorite waffles
directions: Separate eggs.
Set egg whites aside.
Combine all dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl (including sugar).
Combine in 2-cup measuring cup the egg yolks, oil and milk.
Stir with fork (including honey if used).
Beat egg whites until fluffy and stiff; set aside.
Add wet ingredients to flour mix and fold together.
(Do not beat.)
Add whipped egg whites and continue to fold until all ingredients are lightly mixed.
Pour in 1 cup scoops onto waffle iron.
Cook lightly.
Serve with favorite topping.

title: baked eggs in spinach nests
directions: Saute onion in butter in a heavy saucepan until tender.
Stir in flour and bouillon granules; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and bubbly.
Stir in nutmeg and spinach.
Spoon equal portions of creamed spinach into 4 greased 6 ounce custard cups or ramekins, spreading sides slightly higher than center.
Break an egg into each cup.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until eggs are set.
Sprinkle with Cheddar and Parmesan cheese; bake an additional 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch pan (long), mix uncooked rice and all 3 cans of soup together.
Wash chicken, lay on top of mixture.
Slice onion in rings and lay on top of chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not remove foil for 30 minutes (hot). Will need to cool for a while.

title: stuffed fish
directions: Cook celery in 1 cup of water for 15 minutes.
Drain; reserve liquid.
Cook onion slowly in butter until transparent.
Mix bread cubes and spices.
Add celery, 1/4 cup celery liquid, onion and butter.
Mix thoroughly with fork; cover and let stand 10 minutes.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Bake covered 15 minutes in a 425° oven; drain.
Combine tomatoes, cornstarch, basil and hot sauce.
Cook, stirring until thick.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes uncovered.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot drink
directions: Into a saucepan, pour a mixture of 1/2 apple juice and 1/2 white grape juice; add cinnamon and red hots.
Bring mixture to a boil and serve.

title: potato bread
directions: Scald milk, add potatoes and salt.
Blend in oil.
In cup, combine yeast and water.
In another bowl, combine eggs and sugar. Add to potato mixture.
Blend in yeast mixture.
Add flour gradually to make a soft dough.
Knead.
Place in bowl, covered. Let stand 1 hour.
Should double in size.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine cream cheese, juice and rind, mixing until well blended.
Beat whipping cream until soft peaks form gradually. Add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold into cream cheese mixture.
Chill.
Layer fruit in 2 1/2 quart bowl.
Spoon cream cheese mixture over fruit; sprinkle with nuts.
Chill.

title: cream squares
directions: Simmer raisins and water until tender and set aside to cool. Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, liquid from raisins, soda, vanilla, salt and cinnamon.
Add and mix well the raisins. Bake on greased 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet with 3/4-inch rim for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat the eggs. Add sugar, salt and corn syrup together.
Melt butter; add to mixture.
Put the pecan halves with mixture.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cranberry dessert
directions: Blend all together and freeze.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 X 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Note:
Start in cold oven.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: dessert cake
directions: Mix cake mix, water, applesauce and egg whites in large bowl. Beat on low until moist; beat on high 2 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 round 9-inch pans sprayed with Pam.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix the sugar, oil and eggs; mix well.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Bake in 2 greased and floured bread pans or 3 greased and floured 1-pound coffee cans at 350° for 75 minutes or until done.

title: foolproof fudge
directions: In heavy saucepan, melt chips. Add Eagle Brand milk.
Cook over low heat until melted. Add nuts. Spread into an 8 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cool and refrigerate.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken.
Let cool and save broth. Cut chicken in small pieces and put in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Drain vegetables and pour over chicken.
Mix the soups with 1/2 can chicken broth.
Pour mixture over chicken and vegetables.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Tear lettuce into small pieces; place in 9 x 12-inch dish or bowl.
Layer the next 6 ingredients in the order given.
Add sugar to mayonnaise; spread over the top of the salad as you would frosting a cake.
Top with cheese and cover.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Add more bacon bits on top.
Toss when ready to use.
This salad will hold for a quite a while.
Leftover salad can be kept in refrigerator for later use.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Mix with mayonnaise.
Cook and eat.

title: individual fruit cake
directions: Cut cherries and pineapple into small pieces with scissors. Mix ingredients as listed.
Use miniature paper baking cup, 1/2 tablespoon per cup.
Bake 15 minutes in a 300° oven.

title: fruited chicken breasts
directions: Combine oil, lemon juice and orange juice in large bowl.
Stir well.
Place chicken breast in mixture; turn to coat.
Marinate at least 20 minutes.
Turn occasionally.

title: grandma's gingerbread
directions: Cream brown sugar and butter.
Add eggs and blend well.
Stir in molasses.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with sour milk.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until tested done.

title: ham roll-up
directions: Preheat oven to 400° (or as described on package).
Spread out refrigerator biscuits into triangle shape.
Spread with mustard. Lay ham on biscuit.
Lay cheese on ham.
Starting on wide side of triangle, roll biscuit, ham and cheese together.
Shape into crescent.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stem portion of mushroom; reserve crowns for stuffing. Chop stems and add to sausage about a minute and a half before it is finished.
Add crushed garlic at the same time.
Drain any excess fat off.
Mix with just enough cream cheese so it binds (will not need all the cream cheese probably).
Stuff mushroom caps and put under broiler for 5 to 8 minutes.
Good hot or cold.

title: cajun deep fried turkey
directions: Saute first 7 ingredients until salt and pepper are dissolved. Fill the injector and inject turkey at breast, wings, drumsticks, thighs and back.
Allow to marinate 24 hours in refrigerator or ice chest.
Use a 10 gallon pot for frying.
Bring peanut oil to 350° temperature and fry turkey for 38 to 42 minutes.
Turkey should float to surface after 35 minutes and you should cook an additional 5 to 7 minutes.
You may want to tie turkey legs with 1/2-inch cotton ropes to be able to remove from frying pot when done.

title: nonna bronx's lasagne
directions: Heat olive oil and garlic in a pan. Puree cans of tomatoes in a blender. While garlic is browning, pour tomato mixture into pan. Add basil, salt and pepper to taste. In a separate pan, brown chop meat. Sprinkle with garlic powder, salt and pepper to taste. Drain chop meat and add to sauce. Let cook 2 hours. (This can be done in advance.)

title: apple dumplings
directions: Separate rolls into 16 triangles. Place one apple wedge in center of each triangle. Roll from large end to small. Place in 13 x 9-inch pan. Mix sugar and cinnamon. Melt butter and add to sugar and cinnamon mixture. Pour over dumplings. Pour Mountain Dew over dumplings. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water according to package directions.
Drain macaroni and pour into greased 2 qt. baking dish.
Stir in sour cream, milk and cheese packet.
Top with shredded cheddar and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Quarter biscuits and roll into balls.
Roll balls in 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon mixture.
Place 1/2 rolled balls into a Bundt pan.
On stove, boil butter, 1/2 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Stir until bubbly.
Take 1/3 and pour over the balls in pan.
Add second half of balls.
Pour rest of mixture over balls.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Eat with fingers.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Chill pineapple; remove slices from can and place in container.
Mix flour in shaker with some of the juice.
Put sugar, juice, egg and flour mixture in saucepan.
Stir and bring to a boil.
Cool.
Serve over pineapple slice on lettuce with cherry in center.

title: pumpkin-pecan biscuits
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cut butter into flour mixture until it resembles small peas.
Stir in pecans.
In a glass measuring cup, combine pumpkin and half and half.
Stir into flour mixture.
Dough should be stiff.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Knead several times.
If dough is too wet to handle, add more flour.
Pat dough out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut out with 2-inch cutter.
Place biscuits on cookie sheet and bake.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Put 1/2 can soup in casserole.
Add 1/2 can tuna and 2 tablespoons water.
Add chopped onion, bell pepper and celery and black pepper.
Add half can of soup and tuna plus 2 tablespoons water.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Add biscuits.
Return to oven and bake until biscuits are brown at 425°.

title: mom rickett's sugar cookies
directions: Mix together and chill dough.
Roll out dough and cut with favorite cookie cutters.
Decorate.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown meat.
Drain off excess fat.
Add cheese until melted. Add beans and chiles (peppers).
On medium heat, stir well until all ingredients are well mixed.
Put into serving bowl.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: creamy caramel icing
directions: Melt sugar in heavy saucepan until medium brown.
Stir.
Scald milk with butter and blend with sugar.
Cook until smooth, remove from fire.
Add sugar and beat until all is used.
Add vanilla and sprinkle with nuts, if desired.

title: caramel apple cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Reserve 3/4 cup apple filling and spoon remaining filling into crust.
Beat together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Add eggs and beat well.
Pour over apple filling.
Bake 35 minutes or until center is set. Cool.
Mix reserved apple filling and caramel topping in a small saucepan.
Heat about 1 minute.
Arrange apple slices around edge of cheesecake.
Spoon caramel sauce onto the cheesecake and spread evenly.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: shakedown cake
directions: Mix and put in a pie tin.
Scatter almonds on top of batter. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Take the cake out of the oven, drop on the counter and put back in the oven for 10 minutes.
Cool and eat.

title: martha campbell's valentine candy
directions: Mix together the cereal, peanuts and pretzels.
Melt chocolate.
Pour over cereal, peanuts and pretzels.
Spread on wax paper.
Break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Cut a tunnel approximately 2-inches wide and about half the depth of the cake, leaving the edges (inside and out) intact.

title: harvest bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil, then add pumpkin.
Add seasonings to flour.
Alternate adding water and flour to rest of mixture. Grease and flour 4 coffee cans and fill 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: banana whip
directions: Cut up bananas and blend until smooth.
Whip the cream until stiff, gradually adding sugar and lemon juice.
Fold in bananas. Pour into sherbet dishes and refrigerate 2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine the soup, chilies and seasonings.
Set aside.
Line a casserole dish with tortillas that have been moistened in the chicken broth.
Bake sure the tortillas are high enough on the sides to extend over the sides (you're going to wrap them over the top of the casserole).
Spread half of the shredded chicken over the tortillas and top with 1/2 of the soup mixture.

title: cheese 'n' broccoli puff
directions: Cook broccoli according to package omitting salt; drain. Combine soup and cheese; stir in milk and mayonnaise.
Blend in egg.
Grease bottom of 2-quart casserole dish with 1 tablespoon of margarine.
Place drained broccoli in dish.
Pour soup mixture over broccoli; top with bread crumbs and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach squares
directions: Cook spinach as directed on package, drain well.
Beat eggs and add to spinach.
Blend in other ingredients.
Place in greased 9-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix together.
Store in large dry container.
Use 1/3 cup per 1 cup hot water.

title: easy pie
directions: Melt 1/2 cup margarine in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients in order given and pour into margarine.
Add any type canned fruit on top of batter.
Bake at 350° until batter covers fruit and forms crust.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown beef with onions. Add flour, pork and beans, tomatoes, mustard and molasses. Stir and pour in 9 x 13 baking pan. Place 4 or 5 strips bacon on top. Cook 1 hour at 375°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Spray dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch) with olive oil spray.
Sprinkle with minced garlic.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl; place half in baking dish, top with half of onion rings.
Add balance of mixture, topping with balance of onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Add grated cheese as soon as removed from oven. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: tuna casserole(quickie)
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with buttered corn flakes or cracker crumbs.
Bake until top is brown at 450°.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 1/2-quart dish.
Mix flour, sugar and milk in a mixing bowl.
Pour into melted butter.
Do not stir.
Add fruit.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: nut goody bars
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch chips in top of double boiler or in saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Cool slightly.
Blend in marshmallows and nuts.
Place in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and refrigerate.

title: crunchy chicken casserole
directions: Cook a 4 to 5 lb. chicken; remove bones.
Cut into small pieces.

title: dressing for spinach salad
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Shake and toss.
Add bacon and egg.
Makes 1 pound.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: Mix together cream cheese, egg yolk, sugar and vanilla.
Roll bread until flat.
Spread mixture on each slice (small amount). Roll like a jelly roll; dip into melted butter.

title: vegetable stew
directions: Cook cabbage and potatoes until nearly done. Add canned vegetables and salt and pepper to taste.

title: shoestring salad
directions: Just before serving add 1 can shoestring potatoes and 1 can tuna.

title: crunchy butterscotch squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 8-inch square pan. Evenly layer cornflake crumbs, then coconut, butterscotch chips and nuts.
Evenly pour condensed milk over nuts.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, until golden brown on top.
Cool on wire rack; cut into squares.
Cover and store in cool place.
Makes 16 (2-inch) squares.

title: lo-cal vegetable soup
directions: Slice carrots and celery together. Then slice onion and cabbage. Place in a 3-quart saucepan.

title: champagne breakfast
directions: Layer half of the first 3 ingredients in a 3-quart baking dish; repeat.
Combine mushrooms, soup and 1/4 cup of milk; pour over mixture.
Also, blend together the eggs, 2 1/4 cups milk and mustard and pour on top of all.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight.
Bake at 300°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: high altitude adjusted chocolate brownies
directions: Heat oven to about 360 (this is not a typo).
For not so thick brownies, grease 13 x 19 x 2 - inch foil lined baking pan.
For thick chewy brownies, grease 8 x 8 or 9 x 9 - inch foil lined baking pan.
Melt chocolate and butter together in a microwave-safe bowl in the microwave oven for 1 minute.
Stir with a wooden or plastic spoon until all chocolate is melted.
May put in microwave for 30 more seconds if chocolate is taking more than 5 minutes to melt by stirring.
Add sugar and stir until well blended.
Add eggs and vanilla (and raspberry flavor if you want to); mix well.
Add flour and water; mix well.
(Add nuts and or chocolate chips and mix well.)
Spread into prepared pan.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Insert toothpick or cake tester in center of brownies.
If it comes out with wet crumbs, bake for another 5 minutes and check again.
The top of the brownie should look `dry' when finished baking.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Peel foil from brownie and cut into serving pieces.

title: fresh apple pound cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt into a platter or waxed paper.
In a large bowl, beat oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat on medium speed in electric mixer for 3 to 4 minutes, until well blended. Gradually add flour mixture; beat until smooth.
Fold in pecans and apples.
Pour in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar and salt.
Bring to a rolling boil; cool. Slice onions and cucumbers.
Pack in jars and pour solution over this.
Seal and put in deep freezer.
Use a good supply of onion in this.

title: oatmeal scotchies pan cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small bowl, combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; set aside.
In large bowl, combine butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla; beat until light and fluffy.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in oats and butterscotch.
Spread into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool.
Yields 35 two-inch squares.

title: fruit cake balls
directions: In a large bowl, combine pecans, cracker crumbs, raisins, cherries and pineapple.
In large saucepan, combine marshmallows, milk and butter.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until melted.

title: macaroni-cheese puff
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling, salted water until tender.
Drain. In saucepan, combine milk, cheese and salt.
Stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Stir about 1 cup of the hot mixture into egg yolks.
Return to hot mixture in saucepan.
Blend well. Stir in macaroni, bread crumbs, pimento and onion.

title: sourdough cinnamon rolls
directions: Triple the roll recipe and add 3 packages of yeast.
Should make 4 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: hash brown bake
directions: Mix hash browns, sour cream and potato soup together in a large mixing bowl.
Add 3/4 of the cheese and mix well.
The last few minutes of baking, place the remaining cheese on top.
Put ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Great for in a hurry and extra guests.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all together.
Toss with Thousand Island dressing.
Save a few chips to decorate edges.

title: mama's cream pie recipe
directions: Pour milk in saucepan.
Add butter and bring to
a boil.
Add sugar, cornstarch, flour, anywhere from 1 to 3 eggs and vanilla. Cook until mixture starts to thicken.
To this you may add coconut, pineapple or bananas.
For chocolate pie, add 2 tablespoons of cocoa to dry ingredients.
Makes 1 pie.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil the chicken and save the broth.
Let chicken cool.
In a buttered casserole dish, add chicken soup.
Stir in milk and mixture is smooth.
Take chicken off bones and lay on top of soup. Prepare stuffing as directed but use broth instead of water. Place stuffing on top of chicken.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes or until soup begins to bubble up over stuffing.

title: one bowl chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda and salt into a bowl; stir in sugar, then add oil, milk, eggs and coffee.
Mix on low speed until combined (1 minute).
Mix 2 minutes more on medium speed.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lace cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop very small amount of dough (1/4 teaspoon, as it spreads thin) on greased and floured wax paper-lined cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 5 minutes until slightly brown at edges.
If underdone, will not come off paper. Allow cookies to cool on paper before removing.
Makes 80 to 100 cookies.
Cookies look like beige bits of lace.

title: american chop suey
directions: Brown hamburger; add rest of ingredients.
Bring mixture to a boil and simmer for 1 hour.

title: best ever chocolate cake
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add soda and water; mix together.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 300° for 90 minutes.
Test for doneness.
Cool and ice with your favorite icing.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: In large bowl, beat together the sugar, oil, pumpkin and eggs. In medium bowl, stir together white and whole wheat flours, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Fold this into pumpkin mixture, stirring for 2 minutes just to moisten the dry ingredients.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan (or 2 mini loaf pans).
Bake the bread in a preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour, or until a pick inserted in center of bread comes out clean.
(Check after 50 minutes if using mini loaf pans.)
Set the pan on a rack for 10 minutes, then turn out loaf to cool completely.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Mix flour and salt. Roll ribs in flour mixture.
Preheat electric frypan with salad oil to 260°.
Add 1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce.
Add ribs and fry until golden brown. Remove ribs and set aside.

title: cherry cheese  pie
directions: Bake pie crust if needed and cool.
Beat cream cheese with sugar, fold in cool whip.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with pie filling and chill.

title: piccalilli
directions: Grind and measure vegetables; mix in a large bowl.
Add salt. Let stand overnight.
Drain.
Put spices in cheesecloth.
Tie firmly.
Cook 1/2 hour.
Seal in sterile jars.

title: yummy stuffed pasta shells
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Cook pasta.
Rinse with cold water and set aside.	Combine onion, oil and spinach and heat 3 minutes. Puree cottage cheese in food chopper or blender.
Combine cottage cheese, bread crumbs, nutmeg and 1/2 cup of Parmesan cheese.
Mix all then fold in spinach mixture and stir in egg white.
Spread 1 cup of marinara sauce in 9 x 13 dish.
Stuff pasta shells with mixture (approximately 2 tablespoons per shell).
Place stuffed shells on top of marinara sauce.
Cover shells with remaining marinara sauce (2 cups) and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.	Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
May cover if needed.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Pour oil in pot and heat on medium heat. Add onion, celery, jalapenos and chicken; stir. Add warm chicken broth and bring to a boil. Add remaining ingredients and reduce heat; simmer for 30 minutes. Meanwhile, cut tortillas in 1/2-inch strips and fry in oil until crisp. Serve soup with tortilla strips and grated Monterey Jack cheese.

title: spicy shrimp
directions: Combine lime juice, garlic and shrimp in large bowl. Refrigerate, covered, for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add onion, oregano, thyme and bay leaf; saute until onion is softened.
Add tomatoes and jalapeno pepper and salt.
Simmer until thickened, about 20 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Cook, covered, about 5 minutes, until shrimp are pink and curled.
Stir in parsley.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken picadillo pie
directions: *Prepare these the night before.

title: microwave salmon steaks
directions: You will need 1 Reynolds oven bag, regular size.

title: tab chicken
directions: Remove skins from thighs.
Place in an electric frypan (250°). Season with salt and pepper.
Heavily sprinkle with garlic powder.
Coat with ketchup.
Turn pieces over.
Repeat salt and pepper, garlic powder and ketchup.
Pour in enough Tab to bring fluid level even with top of chicken pieces.
Cover.
Cook approximately 45 minutes, turning pieces frequently with spatula. Fluid will thicken when done and coat pieces.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: Beat together egg yolks, lemon juice, lemon rind and butter with rotary beater until thick and lemon-colored.
Combine sugar and flour.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Blend into yolk mixture on low speed of electric mixer.

title: meat loaf maison
directions: For even finer texture, add 1/2 pound chicken livers (pureed), but this is optional.

title: cracker jack cookies
directions: Cream sugar, oleo, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, soda, salt and cream of tartar.
Add oatmeal and Rice Krispies.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly and add pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices, mix well.
Add melted butter and milk stirring thoroughly.
Pour into uncooked pastry shells.
Bake in hot oven (400° to 425°) for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to moderate oven (350°) and continue to bake for 35 minutes or until the filling is "set" and crust is nicely browned.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot oil.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix together ground beef, egg, milk and rice.
Sprinkle with seasonings and mix.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar and shortening.
Add 1 egg and vanilla; stir, then add cold water and stir.
Add salt, baking powder, baking soda and flour; stir well, then drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: orange-oatmeal cake
directions: Heat orange juice to boiling.
Pour over oatmeal.
Set aside. Cream the shortening and both sugars.
Add egg; mix well.
Add dry ingredients and oatmeal mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in large baking pan for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.
May add 2 teaspoons of mix to hot cup of water.
Delicious.

title: cranberry orange relish
directions: Peel orange; reserve fruit for other use.
Cut up peel into 1-inch pieces.
In food processor bowl, finely grind orange peel (about 15 seconds).
Add half of cranberries; process until coarsely chopped.
Place in large bowl; stir in pecans and ginger. Cover; refrigerate until flavors are blended (at least 2 hours). Makes 24 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and cauliflower as directed on package. Drain and put in baking dish. Cover with slices of American cheese. Add layer of cracker crumbs. Slice butter into small pats and cover cracker layer. Cook in microwave for 5 minutes on High.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together sugar, Crisco oil and eggs.
Add to this liquid flour and cinnamon. Add carrots. Also add chopped nuts.
Beat well and bake at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan for about 50 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: barbecued turkey breast
directions: Toss in 1 Tbsp. flour and shake to coat bag.
Place turkey breast in bag and pierce bag with fork.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over turkey.
Seal bag.
Bake 4 to 5 hours at 300°. Remove bones from turkey.
Shred meat and add to juice remaining in bag.
Good served on buns.

title: chafing dish crabmeat spread
directions: Melt butter and cheese.
Toss in crabmeat and seasonings. Transfer to chafing dish.
Serve with melba toast rounds or Ritz crackers.

title: shrimp in butter sauce
directions: Melt oleo and
add
dressing,
pepper
and lemon juice. Add shrimp and cook at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes, depending on size of shrimp. Do not overcook!

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Eat and enjoy.

title: chili pasta
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Put on bottom of casserole.
Top with last 3 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pork roast with fennel and sage
directions: Have butcher cut roast almost through bone to form individual chops.
Trim off fat.
If necessary, tie roast to hold it together.
Sprinkle top and sides with salt, pepper and sage.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Make pudding by package directions with 3 cups of the milk. Add whipped topping and fruit; mix.
Pour into 4-quart ice cream freezer.
Add remainder of milk and stir.
Process by ice cream freezer directions.
Serves 12.
I made strawberry and it made 13 cups when frozen.

title: mexican mess
directions: Brown meat and add seasonings to taste. Add chiles, tomatoes and pinto beans. Turn heat to low and let mixture simmer for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve over tortilla chips and top with cheese.

title: shortcut frozen salad
directions: Prepare pudding mix according to package directions.
Blend in topping, mayo and lemon juice.
Fold in remaining ingredients and turn into 9 x 5 x 3-inch pan.
Freeze until firm.
You could also use papers in 12 muffin tins.

title: tomato sauce for pasta
directions: Saute garlic and then onion.
Add tomatoes.
Add water and spices.
Bring to boil and reduce heat.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: cheese soup
directions: Put 2 quarts water in a large saucepan.
Add potatoes, onion, salt and pepper.
Boil until the potatoes are almost done. Add the whole bag of Winterblend and continue boiling until soft.
Add ham and peas.
Take off heat immediately.
Add milk to color, then spoon in the Cheez Whiz and stir.
Serve. Serves 4.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Stir flour into melted butter to form paste; gradually stir in milk and cook until thickened.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring and cooking until smooth.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, lemonade and condensed milk together until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in baked crust or graham cracker crust.
Chill.
Very good.

title: rice krispie cookie
directions: Boil sugar and Karo until buttery.
Add the peanut butter and Rice Krispies cereal.
Heat to melt in double boiler the 2 kinds of chips.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Ice with melted chips.

title: meat sauce
directions: In a large cooking pot, saute onion in oil. Combine next 5 ingredients. Cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours, stirring often.
Cook meat until done and light brown. Drain and add meat, spatine and a little oregano to sauce.
Cook about 20 minutes longer.
Use with spaghetti, lasagna, etc.

title: stuffed patties
directions: Saute onion and garlic in butter until golden brown.
Add pepper.
Cut cooked shrimp into 1/2-inch pieces and add to onion mixture.
Mix well and cool.

title: sour cream banana bars
directions: Mix sugar, sour cream, butter and eggs. Beat on low speed for 1 minute. Add bananas and vanilla on low for 30 seconds. Beat in flour and baking soda on medium for 1 minute. Stir in nuts. Bake in greased and floured 15 x 10 x 1 pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool.

title: hoagie sandwiches
directions: Mix hot roll mix as directed.
Let rise 1 hour.
Punch down; roll out until it is about size of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place on large pan sprayed with Pam.
Place margarine all over top of dough. Sprinkle dressing on top of margarine.
Layer thin sliced meats on top of dressing.
Layer cheese.
Meat and cheese may be any variety or you can also mix them.
Fold over 1/3 of side, then fold the other 1/3 of side on top of it.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well with a spoon. Put into a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, 55 to 60 minutes.

title: mel plymale's toffee brittle
directions: Line cookie sheet with crackers.
Boil sugar and butter for 3 minutes and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Melt chocolate chips and spread over baked crackers; sprinkle with nuts.
Let cool, then break apart.

title: cheesy potato lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Divide noodles into 3 portions.
Layer a 13 x 9-inch pan with a third of the noodles.
Spread 1 cup of potatoes over noodles.
Dot with 1 third of butter.
Sprinkle with one kind of cheese.
Layer another third of noodles.
Spread on remaining potatoes and dot with butter.
Sprinkle with second kind of cheese.
Layer top with noodles.
Melt remaining butter in saucepan.
Pour over noodles and sprinkle with parsley.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Put sugar and lemon juice on peaches.
Let set for 1 hour. Drain, saving juice to make 1 cup (add a little water if necessary).
Add cornstarch and cook until thick.
Add butter and salt; cool.
Mix in peaches.
Put in baked pie shell and chill.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Melt the cranberry sauce in a heavy saucepan over very low heat and add the jello until dissolved.
Add pineapple, nuts and celery.
Pour into mold; chill and serve.
Great with fried chicken.

title: tuna cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put into refrigerator until firm. Serve with crackers or chips.

title: healthy pancakes
directions: Process oats in blender or processor to make flour.
Mix flour, salt, baking powder, eggs and sugar.
Add milk in amount to reach desired consistency.
Makes great pancakes or waffles.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
You can make and add ice cubes made of orange juice with fruit frozen in them.

title: orange cottage cheese salad
directions: Sprinkle Jell-O over cottage cheese and let set for 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and let set in refrigerator for several hours before serving.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together thoroughly.
Sift flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt together and stir in.
Chill dough; roll in size of walnuts.
Roll in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet, 15 balls per sheet.
Bake until light brown, but still soft at 400° for 7 minutes.
Makes approximately 9 dozen.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican cinnamon tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease a cookie sheet.
Combine butter and sugar in large mixing bowl and cream.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add.
Shape dough into small balls, using about 1 teaspoon dough for each cookie.
Roll balls in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Place on cookie sheet and flatten slightly.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen cookies.

title: best-ever brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in small saucepan over low heat. Beat eggs with mixer.
Gradually beat in sugar until mixture is fluffy and thick.
Stir in chocolate mixture and vanilla.
Fold in flour and salt until well blended.
Stir in walnuts.
Bake evenly in 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased baking pan in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Cool.

title: chicken and mushrooms
directions: In large skillet over medium-high heat, in 6 tablespoons butter, brown chicken on both sides; place on warm platter and set aside.
Add 2 tablespoons butter and cook mushrooms over medium heat.
Remove to platter.
Into drippings, stir salt and flour until blended.
Stir in chicken broth and cream, cook, stirring over medium heat until thickened and smooth.
Add another chicken broth, flour and cream recipe.
Add mushrooms and chicken, simmer, covered for 20 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: rotini antipasto salad(makes 10 to 12 servings)
directions: Cook pasta.
In large bowl, combine pasta and next 7 ingredients.
In small bowl, whisk together next 5 ingredients. Pour dressing over pasta mixture; toss to coat.
Cover and chill. Just before serving, add olives and toss gently.

title: divinity
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and water until it spins a thread.
Pour half in egg whites and beat.
Put back on fire and cook until it cracks (in cup of cold water).
Then add to the egg whites and continue beating until it peaks on the beaters.
Drop by spoon on waxed paper.

title: country style chicken kiev
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan, basil, oregano, garlic salt and salt.

Dip chicken breasts in melted butter, then coat with crumb mixture; reserve remaining butter. Place chicken skin side up in ungreased 9-inch square baking dish. Bake for 50-60 mins. or until chicken is fork tender.
Meanwhile, add wine, green onion and parsley to reserved butter (about 1/2 c).
When chicken is golden brown, pour butter sauce over chicken. Continue baking for 30-40 minutes or until sauce is heated through.
Serve with sauce spooned over.
Makes 4 servings.

title: seafood lasagne(worth all the effort)
directions: Melt butter in skillet and add shallots.
Cook about 1/2 minute, add shrimp and scallops.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. When shrimp start to turn pink, add wine.
Cook just until the wine comes to a boil.
The moment the wine boils, turn off heat. Using a slotted spoon transfer the seafood to a bowl.
Bring the cooking liquid to a boil and add the mushrooms.
Cook about 5 minutes and add to the Bechamel sauce.

title: pretzels
directions: Mix yeast into warm water. Add flour, sugar and salt.
Knead mixture.
Divide into 16 to 18 parts.
Paint with a mixture of an egg beaten with 1 tablespoon of water after rolling into desired shape.
Sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake at 425° until golden. (Pretzel recipe used for class at C.N.S. in J. Lee's class.)

title: cocoa short dough
directions: Place sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla in mixing bowl.
Mix on low speed using the dough hook, just until the ingredients are combined.
Sift flour with cocoa.
Add to the dough and mix only until smooth.
Place dough on a paper lined sheet pan; press the dough as flat as possible.
Cover and refrigerate.
Use to make cookies, shells for tarts, etc.

title: black pepper cookies
directions: Beat egg whites and yolks separately, then beat together.
Add brown sugar and beat.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Add additional flour, if needed.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Makes 5 to 7 dozen.

title: hush puppies
directions: Use food processor or chop very, very fine celery, green peppers and large onions.
Add cornmeal, flour, salt, sugar and egg (blended well).
Just before frying, add baking powder.

title: lemon crackle cake
directions: Crush crackers in bowl.
Add sugar, flour and soda.
Work in butter well.
Add coconut.
Spread 3/4 of mixture into greased and floured 9-inch baking pan.
Carefully spread lemon filling on top. Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Spread cream cheese onto the sliced ham.
Cut pickles in 1/4-inch length and place on top of cream cheese.
Roll ham around pickle and cut in bite-size pieces.
Insert with colored toothpicks.

title: glazed carrots
directions: In a dry sauteuse, add the cardamom, then the coriander and toast. Heat fat in a medium sautoir. Add carrots, sugar or syrup, turmeric, toasted cardamom, toasted coriander, orange or apple juice, water and salt. Bring to a boil; cover and simmer until fork-tender. Quickly evaporate the liquid. Add the remaining ingredients and saut coat the carrots.

title: mexican seasoned potatoes
directions: Cut each potato lengthwise into 4 equal wedges.
Set aside. Place butter in 10-inch square casserole.
Microwave on High for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until butter melts.
Add potatoes, turning to coat with butter.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients. Sprinkle over potatoes.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 14 to 18 minutes or until potatoes are tender, rearranging potatoes twice. Let stand covered for 5 minutes.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Grease and flour a loaf pan.
Sift flour, salt and soda together twice.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs. 1 egg at a time beating thoroughly with bananas.
Pour batter in pan and bake 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: "creamsicle" dip
directions: Blend Marshmallow Creme and cream cheese until smooth.
Thin with a few tablespoons of orange juice.
Add orange rind to taste.

title: 3 tier chocolate buttermilk cake
directions: Cream butter, add sugar gradually and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, then vanilla.

Sift dry ingredients together, add to creamed mixture, alternately with buttermilk. Pour batter into three 9-inch pans, which have been greased and lightly floured, or lined with wax paper and buttered.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cool on racks.
Frost with butter icing.

title: grandma taylor's crust
directions: Melt margarine; stir all together and pat into pie tin.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.
Use for 1 crust pies.
Great with fresh fruit pies.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Grease and flour two 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Combine all dry ingredients
and
mix well.
Make a well in the center of mixture and
pour
all
liquids
into it.
Mix by hand.
Pour mixture into pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tester inserted
in center
comes
out clean.
Can be frozen.
Slice thinly before completely thawed.
Can spread with cream cheese spread. Refrigerate until served.

title: skillet pork chops
directions: Trim excess fat from pork chops.
Heat fat in skillet until you have about 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Remove trimmings. Coat chops with flour and brown slowly on both sides in hot fat. Combine cheese, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of the mixture over the meat.
Cover with potato slices.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of cheese mixture.
Add onion slices.

title: date pudding
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and add dates and nuts.
Pour in buttered pan and mix brown sugar, boiling water and butter and pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks. Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt thoroughly. Gradually add to egg yolks. Add milk; mix well. Cook in a double boiler until thickened. Cool and add vanilla. Stir. Pour into a baked pie shell and top with meringue using the 2 egg whites and 6 teaspoons sugar. Brown meringue in oven. Cool before serving.

title: p'nut butter and oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk and margarine in saucepan; bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Let cool.

title: quick cupcake-cones
directions: Cut bottoms off egg carton.
Insert cones in holes so egg carton holds them upright.
Mix cake mix as directed.
Fill cones 2/3 with batter.
Bake in microwave 30 to 40 seconds on full power for 1 cone, 15 seconds longer for 2 cones.
Let cones stand in oven for 2 minutes after cooking is completed.
Makes 12 to 18 cones.

title: fish chowder
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven, saute onion and green pepper in butter.
Add potatoes and simmer 4 to 6 minutes. Add fish stock and fish. Simmer 10 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and simmer just until done.
Season to taste.

title: red rice
directions: Take meat, peppers, onion and celery and cook them on stove until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and bake for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place seasoned chops in bottom of large baking or casserole dish.
Layer potatoes and onions alternating on top.
Spread mushroom soup over all.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: spicy chicken
directions: Cook chicken in large skillet.
Cut into small pieces and drain.
Add salsa to chicken and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes. Layer a casserole dish with the tortilla chips.
Cover the bottom. Put the chicken over the chips and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is completely melted.
Serve topped with sour cream.

title: bean dumplings
directions: Put enough milk to leave thick enough to roll out as biscuit dough (3/4 cup).
Roll to thickness of pie crust.
Cut into 1/2-inch wide strips.
Drop in pan of 1 cup brown beans, cook and simmer for 20 minutes or until done.

title: witch's brew
directions: Place apple juice in saucepan.
Tie cloves and cinnamon in cloth bag and add to juice.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove spices.
Add remaining ingredients; heat to boiling again.
Serve hot.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry with paper towels.
Combine and mix buttermilk, bouillon and oregano.
Let stand 10 minutes; stir. Place chicken in a large bowl; pour bouillon mixture over it; toss to coat.
In plastic bag, mix flour and paprika.
Add a few pieces of chicken at a time and shake to coat.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake uncovered 1 hour or until golden brown at 350°.

title: cherry-pineapple dessert
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: pear crisp
directions: Place pears in bottom of Pyrex (8-inch) round dish.
Combine brown sugar, flour, oats and cinnamon in a separate bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle mixture over fruit. Microwave on High for 10 minutes or until topping is bubbly.

title: bombay chicken salad
directions: Combine and chill.
Add and mix lightly:

title: bubbles
directions: Combine, shake and let settle 4 hours.
Store, covered, in refrigerator to extend suds shelf life.
Allow to warm before using.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Dip a teaspoon in hot water and cut portions (size as desired); drop in a pot of boiling water, cover tightly and cook for 10 minutes.

title: red punch
directions: Add tropical punch to pineapple juice.
Add enough Sprite or ginger ale to taste.
Chill before serving.

title: christmas morning pancakes
directions: Preheat griddle to 400 degrees.
Spray with pam.
Mix all three ingredients until smooth.
Pour batter on griddle and flip when pancake starts to look dry on top.
Top each one with a pat of butter.
Serve with syrup or honey.
Can top with powdered sugar.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add marshmallows and dissolve. Add cream cheese and pineapple.
Stir until cool and fold in whipped Milnot.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Chill until set.

title: bacon olive dip
directions: Stir soup mix, bacon, bacon drippings and chopped olives into sour cream.
Serve with potato chips or your favorite crackers.

title: low-fat banana bread
directions: Mix applesauce, honey, egg substitute, banana chunks, water and vanilla in food processor or with mixer.
Mix in dry ingredients, using as few strokes as possible.
(Optional:
Stir in 1 cup walnuts and/or 1 cup raisins.) Pour batter into loaf pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: tomato beef stew
directions: Dust meat with flour.
Brown in oil in Dutch oven.
Add soup and water.
Cover and simmer 1 to 2 hours.
Add vegetables and seasonings.
Cook 1 hour, until tender.

title: wintery day bean soup
directions: *Use at least 7 varieties of beans (Great Northern, navy, black, garbanzo, green split peas, pinto and red beans).

title: cheese rarebit
directions: Melt margarine and stir in flour.
Slowly add milk until thickens.
Reduce heat and stir in cheese and Worcestershire sauce and simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve over toast points.
Top with paprika.

title: cream of potato soup(especially irresistible on a cold day.)
directions: Cut potatoes in halves.
Cook with onion in 2 cups boiling water until tender.
Do not drain.
Mash potatoes.
Add sausage, thyme, marjoram, salt, pepper, butter, sharp cheese and remaining boiling water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add grated cheese just before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: creamy cheese frosting
directions: Let cream cheese sit on counter to soften.
Mash together with powdered sugar in a small bowl with a fork
. Add vanilla a little at a time.
Mix very evenly.

title: rhubarb bar
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients, then set aside to cool.
Combine next 5 and stir cornstarch with water and add to oat mixture. Pour 3/4 of this mixture into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour rhubarb on top, then put last 1/4 on top of rhubarb. Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.
Good plain, or with ice cream or whipping cream, hot or cold.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix well.
Can be served with Ranch dressing.

title: cheezy potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes into greased Pyrex dish. Layer onion on top. Combine last 4 ingredients and pour over potatoes and onions. Cook 15 minutes at 500° and 45 minutes at 350°. Uncover and cook 15 more minutes at 350°.

title: chile rellenos casserole
directions: Drain chiles and place in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Grate all cheese over chiles.
In blender, beat eggs, flour, salt and milk.
Pour over cheese and chiles.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Pour on tomatoes and chiles; bake 5 more minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat together potatoes with sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and 1/4 cup butter.
Put into buttered casserole dish.
Mix brown sugar, flour, 1/3 cup butter and nuts.
Crumble on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: nacho dip
directions: Fry sausage in pan.
Crumble up very fine and drain thoroughly.
Melt cubed Velveeta and add salsa.
Add sausage.
Mix well.
Serve hot with nacho chips or a hot dog topper.

title: slim dip
directions: Puree in blender.
Chill before serving.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: pecan roll
directions: Mix ingredients and cook to a soft ball.
Then beat until candy will stand in peaks.
Knead in 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Roll in long roll in chopped pecans.
Cool and slice.

title: shoo-fly pie
directions: In a bowl, mix molasses, egg, soda and water.
In a second bowl, combine flour, brown sugar and spices.
Work with your fingers until even crumbs form.
Sprinkle 1/3 of the flour mixture into the pie crust.
Pour on 1/2 of the molasses mixture.
Repeat with 1/3 of flour mixture and remaining molasses mixture.
Top with remaining flour mixture.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 20 minutes more or until filling is firm when shaken.
Cool.

title: chocolate chip meringue drops (or almond meringue drops)
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Line two baking sheets with baking parchment (or aluminum foil).
In the large bowl of an electric mixer, beat the egg whites at high speed until they hold stiff peaks.
Beat in the sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, then beat in the vanilla extract.
Reduce mixer speed to low and beat in cocoa powder.
Fold in chocolate chips with spatula.
Drop by rounded teaspoon (1 inch apart) onto the baking sheets.
Bake for 1 hour. Turn off the oven and dry the cookies in the oven for 2 hours longer.
Store covered.
Makes about 40 cookies.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix applesauce and baking soda together.
Let stand.
Sift flour and spices.
Add
sugar and shortening to flour mixture. Mix well.
Add fruit to mixture.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour or more.

title: brownies for sweet tooth
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and margarine together; cream.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and nuts.
Bake in a large pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: plain cake
directions: Mix ingredients as usual for sheet cake.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Bring 1 cup water, sugar, cornstarch and food coloring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Mix together gelatin, lemon juice and 1 tablespoon water.
Add to cooled mixture.
Pour over strawberries arranged in a baked pie crust.
Cool until set about 2 hours.

title: milk tart
directions: Blend egg yolks, butter and sugar.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mix to egg mixture and add a little of the milk to mix.
Add rest of the milk and vanilla and blend until smooth.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in 3 tablespoons of margarine.
Add broccoli and rice, then add soup and milk.
Add 6 ounces Cheez Whiz; mix well. Top with remaining Cheez Whiz.
Bake in greased casserole dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: butter tea cookies
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Gradually add flour.
Roll 1 teaspoon in hand long and narrow.
Bake approximately 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool dough in refrigerator before baking.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Let sauce stand until it softens; drain.
Add cranberry juice to hot water; dissolve Jell-O in this.
Cool.
Beat until stiff; add sour cream and berries and fold in.
Put in mold. Refrigerate.
Can double for a large mold.
Delicious with holiday meals.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake as directed. Pour kahlua over cake and let sit for a few minutes.

title: quick-easy lunch
directions: Prepare rice as directions on box state.
Heat soup.
Spoon out rice.
Add soup generously over the top.
Little mess and takes 5 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, pat your hamburger in dish. Sprinkle salt, pepper and onion over meat.
Spread cream of chicken soup over that.
Cover soup with cheese slices.
Place Tater Tots over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: barbecue
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Trim all visible fat from roast. Place in	roaster
or Dutch oven (do not brown).	Mix together all other ingredients
and
pour
over
meat.
Cover and bake until well done.
Remove
meat
to
platter
and
remove
any remaining fat and bone.
Shred until fine.
Put meat back into sauce in roaster and stir to mix.

title: good venison hamburger soup
directions: Cook all ingredients for 1 hour.
Then add rice, green beans, carrots and parsley.
(If you have Watkins soup flavoring, add a few sprinkles.)

title: hanky pankies
directions: Brown meats and drain well.
Add diced cheese and remaining ingredients.
Spread on party rye bread and freeze until firm. Put in plastic bags and keep in freezer.
When needed, broil until bubbly or bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: polenta and italian sausage
directions: Spread peppers and mushrooms in an even layer in a shallow 9 x 13-inch oval or rectangular baking dish.
Lay sausages on vegetables.
Put into a 350° oven.
After 10 to 15 minutes, stir the vegetables to moisten with the pan drippings. Continue to bake until sausages are lightly browned and no longer pink in the center (50 to 60 minutes).

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, vinegar and water.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add beets.
Stir well.
Can add 1 tablespoons butter.
Serve warm or cold.

title: beef tenderloin
directions: Combine last seven ingredients in a quart-size fruit jar. Marinate tenderloin for 12 hours, turning several times.
Take tenderloin out of refrigerator until it returns to room temperature.
Bake at 450° for 22 minutes for rare meat.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix butter and cream cheese until smooth and creamy, about 3 minutes.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Mix in vanilla.
Add flour and salt and mix until flour is well incorporated.
Spoon into greased and floured bundt pan.
Place in cold oven and bake at 275 for 1 hour and 55 minutes.

title: kelly's pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Season chops on both sides with salt and pepper.
Arrange in baking dish.
Cut onion and lemon into 6 slices.
On each chop, place in order:
1 onion slice, 1 lemon slice, 1 tablespoon brown sugar and 1 tablespoon chili sauce. Cover dish with aluminum foil.
Bake 35 minutes, remove foil and bake another 35 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar and syrup in 2-quart measuring cup.
Cook 4 minutes on High.
Add vanilla and butter.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in soda.
Pour on a buttered cookie sheet.
Spread thin or leave fairly thick if you like it foamy.
Work fast as it sets up in a hurry.

title: amaretto egg nog muffins
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, salt, baking powder, nutmeg and raisins and set aside.

title: toasted seeds
directions: Separate the fiber from melon, pumpkin, squash, sunflower or watermelon seeds.
Cover with salted water.
Simmer 2 hours. Drain and dry on brown paper bag.
Cook the nuts in oil (allow 1/2 cup vegetable oil for every cup of nuts) heated to 365°, 1 to 2 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Spread the seeds in a shallow pan, leaving a small amount of oil on seeds.
Sprinkle with salt. Bake in 250° oven until golden, stirring from time to time.

title: spinach cups
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease 20 mini muffin cups.
In large skillet saute onion and garlic in olive oil until tender. Add spinach, mushrooms, bread crumbs, cheese, yogurt, salt and pepper.
Blend well.
Set aside.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits, separate each into 2 layers.
Place each layer in a muffin cup; firmly press in bottom and up sides.
Spoon generous tablespoon spinach mix into each cup.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Let set a few minutes.
Remove to serving plate.
Can garnish with dollop of sour cream.
Serve warm.

title: aunt carrie's lemon bars
directions: Boil slowly 50 to 10 minutes.
Use as jelly.
(Keep out of cold places.)

title: pizza dough
directions: Sprinkle yeast in lukewarm water; let stand 5 minutes.
Pour boiling water over shortening, salt and sugar in a large bowl. Cool to lukewarm (important); stir yeast, then add to shortening, salt and sugar mixture.
Add one half of the flour.
Beat until smooth with spoon.
Add remaining flour and knead until smooth. Put in greased bowl.
Cover with towel.
Let rise in warm place. Keep free from drafts until double bulk.
Punch dough down, then roll out as for pizza.
Add sauce and toppings.
Bake in 450° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until it comes off bone.
Save broth.
Cut in small pieces.
Cook rice by recipe on box, except use chicken broth for the liquid.
Mix chicken, rice, soups and sour cream and pour in baking dish.
Put stuffing mix over the top of this.
Pour any broth left over dressing mix.
Makes one large casserole or two small.
Freezes well.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: bill belew's chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and Karo.
Cook until a soft ball will form.
Remove from heat.
Place pan in cold water. (I put a little water in the sink not high enough to spill into pan.)
Add peanut butter, butter, vanilla and nuts to fudge and beat till thick.
Pour into buttered platter and wait till it is firm.
If you can't wait, lick the pan.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: white texas sheet cake
directions: In a large saucepan, bring 1 cup butter and water to a boil; remove from heat and stir in dry ingredients and eggs. Pour into greased 13 x 9 baking dish and bake at 375° for 20 to 22 minutes.

title: orange-pineapple pie
directions: In saucepan, heat pineapple with juice to boiling.
Take off heat.
Add dry jello, stirring to dissolve well.
Fold in 1 pint (2 cups) vanilla ice cream.
Pour into baked shell or graham shell.
Chill well before serving.
Top with whipped cream.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Dice onions.
Saute in butter.
Add to make syrup:
2 cups brown sugar, 1/4 cup prepared mustard, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Stir frequently and simmer 2 hours.
Can make 1/2 batch.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix avocados with mayo, lemon juice and salt and pepper to taste.
(Add more mayo if dry.)
Add taco seasoning to sour cream. In a pie or quiche plate, layer refried beans, avocado mix and sour cream.
Top with chopped tomatoes, cheese and olives.

title: cookie coffee cake
directions: In a small bowl, dissolve yeast in water. In a large bowl combine flour, salt, orange rind, and 1/4 cup sugar. Cut in butter with fork. Combine eggs, milk, dissolved yeast and add to flour mixture. Combine lightly, cover tightly. Refrigerate overnight. Divide dough in half on a floured surface. Roll each piece into an 18 x 12 rectangle. Sprinkle with remaining sugar mixed with cinnamon. Roll up tightly beginning at the wide end. Cut each roll into 1 inch slices. Place cut side up on a greased baking sheet. Flatten with palm of hand. Bake at 400° about 12 minutes. Glaze-orange juice and powdered sugar. Pour over warm rolls.

title: pineapple pie
directions: In saucepan, cook pineapple, cornstarch and 1/2 cup sugar until thick; cool.
Roll pie crust.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 tablespoon flour on bottom crust.
Pour pineapple mixture into crust.
Put butter on top.
Cover with top crust; slit for steam.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: salad dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients, except oil, in blender.
Then add oil and blend again.
Shake before using.

title: soft chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, cocoa, soda, salt and sugar.
Beat water and Miracle Whip together for 2 minutes.
Add vanilla; mix with dry ingredients.
Put in 2 greased 8-inch pans or 1 greased 9 x 13 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger meat, stir in onion and cook for about 3 minutes.
Add beans and soup.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Stir chili powder, flour and water together to make paste.
Add to the recipe.
Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed until well blended. Add oats, flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed until well blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts and drop by rounded spoonfuls 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, until lightly brown.

title: carol's chicken surprise
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package directions and spread on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Arrange chicken over stuffing.
Combine soups and sour cream in a bowl.
Spread soup mixture on top of chicken layer.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted and bubbles.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt Crisco in saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add sugar, molasses and eggs.
Beat well.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Chill.
Form 1-inch balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Combine egg, onion, soup and 1/2 grated cheese.
Pour over drained and squeezed spinach and mix.
Mix melted margarine and stuffing mix together and pour over spinach mixture. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cauliflower supreme
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook cauliflower, celery, onion and red or green pepper, covered, in a small amount of lightly salted water 5 to 7 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain.

title: wonderful stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut peppers lengthwise in half; clean and parboil in salted water for 10 minutes.
Drain peppers and set aside to cool.

title: pizza
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of pizza pan.
Next layer Pizza Quick, then shredded cheeses and last olives and mushrooms.
Serve taco chips to dip pizza onto plates.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: Measure dry ingredients and sift together.
Dice bananas and add to dry ingredients.
Add oil, vanilla, eggs and pineapple with it's juice.
The mixture is stirred to blend, but do not beat. Pour into a greased 9 inch tube pan.

title: goober haystacks
directions: Melt butterscotch coating;
add peanut butter and melt. Mix in
noodles
and
peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into wax paper and allow to harden.

title: cucumber lime pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers crosswise.
Mix pickling lime and water, add cucumbers and soak 24 hours in crockery or enamel ware (do not use aluminum ware).
Stir occasionally in lime water.
Remove from lime water and rinse in 3 cool waters.
Soak 3 additional hours in ice and water.
Remove carefully to drain.
Mix vinegar, salt, sugar and food coloring.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour over cucumbers.
Let sit 5 or 6 hours or overnight.
Add pickling spice to taste (may use whole cloves or allspice).
Boil mixture for 35 minutes.
Fill sterilized jars with cucumber slices and pour syrup over cucumbers leaving 1/8-inch head space, then seal jars.

title: grape and broccoli salad(8 servings)
directions: Combine broccoli, walnuts, grapes, celery and green onions. In a small bowl, mix together sugar and mayonnaise. Slowly stir in vinegar. Toss with salad. Refrigerate.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix ingredients
and form into small balls.
Serve with a pick in each
ball.
Double
recipe number of times it takes for desired number of servings.
Keep refrigerated.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Beat together first 5 ingredients; pour into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Mix brown sugar, flour and nuts with oleo and sprinkle over sweet potatoes.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: tex-mex wontons
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper; drain well.
In mixing bowl, add hamburger mixture, refried beans, cheese and chili powder; mix well.
Put 1/2 teaspoon of mixture in the middle of a wonton wrap; wrap well.
Take filled wraps; cook in a skillet of hot oil for about 1 minute on each side, or until golden brown.
Serve hot.
Dip in taco sauce and sour cream.

title: crazy orange salad
directions: In large bowl, mix together cottage cheese, dry gelatin mix, whipped topping, drained fruit and walnuts.
Chill before serving.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and turn into a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until center tests done.

title: cranberry-orange slush cocktail
directions: Mix all ingredients except the carbonated beverage in a nonmetallic container.
Divide among pint containers.
Cover and freeze at least 8 hours until slushy.
Stir a couple of times during the freezing processes to make serving easier.
To serve, mix equal parts slush and chilled carbonated beverage.
An ounce of cranberry liqueur or vodka can be added to each glass when serving.

title: hamburger corn bread casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, salt and drain.
Do not prepare corn bread according to package instructions.
Instead, combine the dry corn bread ingredients with the can of corn and the egg.
Pour half of this batter into buttered casserole.
Top with ground beef; add onion, chiles and cheese.
Pour remaining batter over meat and vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, until lightly browned on top.
Serves 8.

title: salmon spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into a ball and chill overnight.
Roll in fresh parsley before serving.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: vodka punch
directions: Have everything chilled.
Mix orange juice, lemonade, pineapple juice, vodka and soda together until frozen juice is melted.
Then add strawberries while still frozen.
Stir. Serves 35.

title: oven-fried chicken(serves 4 to 5.)
directions: Place the oil and butter in a shallow cooking pan (jelly roll); put in a preheated 375° oven to melt.
Set aside.
In a large paper sack, combine the flour and seasonings.
Roll the chicken pieces, 3 pieces at a time, in the melted oil-butter mixture, then drop them in the sack and shake to cover.
Place on a dish or wax paper.
Place chicken in the pan, skin side down. Bake for 45 minutes.
With a spatula, turn over and bake 5 to 10 minutes longer or until the top crust begins to bubble.
Serve hot or cold, but the crust texture is better if chicken is not refrigerated before eating.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together croutons, oleo and water. Use 1/2 of mixture to line pan.
Mix chicken, onion, celery, salad dressing and salt.
Mix well and put over croutons. Top with remaining crouton mix.
Beat eggs and milk.
Pour over all.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Put shredded cheese over last 10 minutes of baking.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375° and grease square pan.
Peel apples; cover them and cut into quarters.
Slice and put into square pan. Measure brown sugar, flour, oats, cinnamon and nutmeg in small mixing bowl.
Using pastry blender, cut in margarine until mixture is crumbly.
Do not overmix! Sprinkle over apples.
Bake until apples are tender, about 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: halibut piccata
directions: In a 6 to 8-inch frying pan over medium-high heat, stir garlic in 1/2 tablespoon oil until limp, about 2 minutes.
Add wine, lemon juice and capers.
Boil, uncovered, over high heat until reduced to 1/2 cup, 3 to 4 minutes; keep sauce warm.

title: roast eggplant soup
directions: Using the onions, celery, carrots, peppercorns, mustard seed and bay leaves, boil these off for about 1/2 hour.
Drain, saving the water which is now your stock.
Place the eggplant that have been cut in half on a cookie sheet and lightly sprinkle with salt, pepper and olive oil.
Roast in oven at 375° for 1/2 hour or until golden brown.
Puree the eggplant until no chunks are left.
Chop garlic very fine and saute until brown.
Mix vegetables, stock, garlic and eggplant and enjoy!!

title: sweet potatoes biscuits
directions: Mix flour, sugar and baking powder together and add margarine and mashed potatoes with hand. Make into biscuits and bake.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Chop chicken (can use canned chicken).
Chop
water chestnuts. Cook macaroni and mix all ingredients. Chill.
Can be used as a sandwich filling without macaroni.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, 1 tablespoon lemon rind, butter, lemon juice, milk and egg yolks in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until smooth and thickened, stirring constantly; cover and cool.

title: our favorite oatmeal bread
directions: Combine oats, wheat flour, sugar, salt and margarine in a large bowl.
Pour boiling water over this.
In a separate bowl dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
When batter is cooled to lukewarm, add yeast.
Stir in 5 cups flour and knead 5 to 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, cover and let rise until doubled in size.
Punch down and let rise again.
Shape into 2 loaves and place in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool on a rack, brushing loaves with margarine for a soft crust.

title: fruit cake
directions: Line cake pan with greased paper.
Put all fruits and nuts in a bowl and put all flour on them and mix thoroughly with hands. Do no cut fruit or nuts.
In a separate bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Beat eggs then add to creamed butter and sugar, add flavoring.
Pour this mixture over fruits and nuts.
This is easily done with a spoon but hands may be used.
Bake at 300 degrees for 1 3/4 hours.

title: featherweight pancakes
directions: Mix flour, salt and cheese together.
Beat egg yolks until lemon colored.
Add to flour mixture.
Beat egg whites stiff, but not dry.
Fold in egg whites.
Drop in small spoonfuls on a griddle and brown on both sides.
A lid helps cook these through. Yield: 12 (3-inch) pancakes.

title: vidalia onion pie
