directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix crumbs with melted margarine.
Press into 8-inch pie pan.
Saute thinly sliced onions in 2 tablespoons of margarine until clear, but not brown.
Spoon into crust.

title: spanish noodles
directions: Cook noodles as instructed on package.
Drain.
Saute onion in margarine.
Stir in flour.
Then add tomato juice, mushrooms (in juice), sugar, salt and pepper.
Put noodles into 9 x 13-inch greased pan (or 2-quart casserole).
Add cheese cubes.
Pour tomato juice mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is bubbly and lightly browned.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: *In place of glaze, you can use a large package of strawberry jello and half the amount of water called for on the package.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine peaches, cornstarch and sugar.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.

title: pound cake
directions: Boil sugar and water until rolling.
Add almond flavoring. Have this ready to pour on the top of the cake immediately
after out of the oven.
Cool in pan.

title: whiskey wieners
directions: Mix together last 4 ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Put sausages and hot mixture in crock-pot.
Simmer for 2 to 3 hours.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together 2 cups crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Mix butter and cornflakes and put on top of the potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 12.
This is a perfect party make ahead casserole.

title: steak casserole
directions: Brown cube steak (no flour) in butter (melted) in frypan.
Use pepper (no salt).
Cut in bite size pieces after browning.
Mix soup, water and garlic.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Put steak and liquid in covered casserole dish and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve on cooked noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: velvet mushroom soup
directions: In a large saucepan, over low heat, cook mushrooms, onion and parsley in butter until tender.
Stir in flour and cook 1/2 minute.
Remove from heat and gradually add broth, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in sour cream until blended. Heat through, but "don't boil".

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Combine hamburger meat and onion and fry together until brown. Drain grease off.
Drain green beans.
Spread hamburger meat in long pan, then spread the beans over the hamburger meat.
Cover with cream of mushroom soup, undiluted.
Cover with Tater Tots and bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries; break apart with fork as they melt.
Add pineapple and bananas. Pour 1/2 gelatin into long dish.
Chill until firm.
Spread with sour cream.
Spoon remains of gelatin into dish.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage until tender.
Brown beef and drain.
Drain cabbage well and add ingredients, except bread crumbs.
(Save some cheese to mix with bread crumbs.)
Spray casserole dish with Pam; pour casserole in.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and remaining cheese over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Boil noodles; add margarine.
Combine balance of ingredients and add to noodles.
Pour into well-greased (glass) baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: italian chicken
directions: Soak chicken in beaten eggs for 1 hour.
Gently roll pieces in bread crumbs. Fry in batter until browned.
Put in casserole. Cover with mushrooms and broth. Top with thinly sliced cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 4.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into greased casserole. Bake at 350° until knife comes out clean.

title: peanut butter with a twist
directions: Combine oleo, peanut butter, eggs, sugar, vanilla.
Beat all together.
Sift flour, baking powder, and soda.
Add to mixture. Put 1 table around candy.
Bake at 350° 10 - 12 minutes.

title: sweet and sour ribs
directions: Put ribs in single layer in pan.
Broil on all sides until well browned.
Drain off all grease.

title: prune cake
directions: Pour into greased and floured pan, 12 x 8 x 3-inch.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: banana bread
directions: Put bananas in large mixing bowl.
Add eggs, vanilla and margarine.
Sift together flour, salt, sugar, soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add to banana mixture and mix well.
Stir in raisins and dates.
Pour entire mixture into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch bread pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Mix sugar, brown sugar, shortening and vanilla until smooth; set aside.
Sift flour, soda and salt together; add to sugar mixture.
Stir in oats and pecans.

title: italian stuffed shells
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef, onion and garlic; drain well. Stir in water, tomato paste, bouillon and oregano.
Simmer, uncovered, for about 30 minutes.
In medium bowl, combine cottage cheese, 1 cup Mozzarella, Parmesan cheese and egg; mix well. Stuff shells with cheese mixture.
Arrange in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour meat sauce over shells.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover.
Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella cheese. Bake for 5 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix ingredients in large saucepan and cook until thickened. Add chicken and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: zucchini chocolate cake
directions: Cream oleo, oil and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla and milk.
Beat.

title: wilted lettuce salad
directions: Clean lettuce piece by piece or leaf by leaf and dry.
Cut up in small particles (serving size).
Cut bacon in small pieces and fry until greasy or microwave (heat to desired texture).

title: vinegar pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add 1/4 cup water, vinegar, salt and sugar. Stir into boiling water until thick on moderate heat.
Add lemon extract.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Beat melted butter, chocolate and sugar together.
Add unbeaten eggs; beat well.
Add flour and vanilla.
Fold in nuts. Pour into greased Pyrex pie plate.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 25 minutes.
Serve plain or with vanilla ice cream.

title: roast pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in large roasting pan in 350° oven for 1 hour, turning once, basting with sauce.
Cook onion and garlic in 1/4 cup vegetable oil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour over chops, cooking until tender.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, vanilla, butter and syrup.
Turn into pie shell and sprinkle nuts on top; stir into mixture using a fork. Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and bake 35 minutes longer, or until an inserted knife comes out clean.

title: adam's bachelor special
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to directions on box. Add other ingredients and stir well.
May be baked in 350° oven or eaten as is.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix together rhubarb and sugar and blend well.
Let mixture stand an hour to melt sugar.
Bring slowly to boiling point.
Boil 20 minutes.
Stir in thoroughly 1 package Jell-O.
Skim and put in Mason jars.
Cover with wax.
Makes 4 small jars.

title: cheese and rye
directions: Mix all ingredients and add enough salad dressing to moisten. Spread on party rye.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: broccoli souffle
directions: Saute onion in butter until light beige.
Stir in flour and water.
Let come to a boil.
Remove from stove.
Add eggs, Cheez Whiz
and
drained
broccoli.
Blend well.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart buttered
baking
dish.
Sprinkle
Ritz crackers on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: tuna and noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions until not quite done.
Drain; mix in soup, seasonings and tuna.
Top with crumbs or crumbled potato chips.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly and crumbs lightly browned.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake
cake by directions.
Into punch bowl place 1 layer of cake.
Spread
package
of pudding over cake.
Spread 1/2 pineapple, 1/2
pie
filling, 1/2 pecans, 1/2 Cool Whip and 1/2 coconut.
Repeat all this again.
Chill before serving.
Serves 35 people.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix together and store in a tightly covered container.
Use about 2 tablespoons to a cup of hot water.
Use more or less to taste.

title: rum coconut pound cake
directions: Cream
butter
and
shortening;
gradually
add
3 cups sugar, beating
until
light
and
fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating
after
each
addition.
Combine
flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk. Mix
just until blended.
Stir in rum and coconut flavorings. Pour
batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: sherried beef
directions: Put in a covered baking dish and cook 4 hours at 350°.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: baked beans
directions: Pour beans into large pot on stove.
Grate in onion and heat to boiling, adding all other ingredients.
Once combined and hot, bake in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Coat chicken with flour, salt and pepper.
Brown in oil on all sides.
In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, juice, vinegar, soy sauce, ginger and bouillon.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Pour over chicken.
Add pineapple and other vegetables.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 to 25 minutes until tender.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies (reserve 1/4 cup).
Mix with margarine.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar; mix well.
Fold in 1/2 of Cool Whip and spread over crumbs.
Prepare pudding with milk and spread over cream cheese.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with reserved cookie crumbs.

title: confetti muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Crush cereal and set aside, reserving one tablespoon.
Put baking mix into a bowl.
Add egg, water, oil and sugar.
Mix just enough to moisten.
Fold in crushed cereal. Fill greased and lined muffin cups 2/3 full.
Sprinkle tops with reserved crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes.
Makes 9 muffins.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix all together and serve with sliced apples.

title: vanilla wafer pie
directions: Mix the wafers and oleo together and press into pie plate. Cream together the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread over crumbs. Top with your favorite pie filling. Spread Cool Whip over all. Chill.

title: coconut black walnut cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately. Add rest of ingredients and beat well.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes. Pour hot Coconut Syrup over hot cake in pan.
Allow cake to remain in pan 4 hours to absorb syrup.

title: ham sauce
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients
about 1/2 hour, then thicken a little with a smooth cornstarch and water mixture.
Simmer until ready to serve.

title: no bake peanut butter bars
directions: Soften butter.
Add peanut butter and cream well.
Add sugar and graham cracker crumbs.
Mix well.
Spread on greased cookie sheet; pat down with hands.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over top.
Cut when set (about 30 minutes).
Don't wait too long to cut.
Easy and really good!

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients, except preserves and barbecue sauce. Form into small balls.
Place on broiler pan and bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: m.j.'s applesauce bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together in large bowl.
Beat eggs and applesauce into mixture.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice and oats in medium bowl.
Stir dry ingredients into applesauce mixture and add walnuts, raisins, dates and fruit.
Bake in 3 small or 2 large greased loaf pans at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce(fat-free)
directions: Mix ingredients and simmer for about 45 minutes.
Very good over pasta.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
Break cake into pieces about golf ball size.
Cover bottom of punch bowl with cake.
Top with layers of fruit, pudding and Cool Whip.
Repeat.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts.
Garnish with cherries.

title: rice salad
directions: Put all ingredients into bowl and mix well.
Cover and chill. May serve on lettuce leaves.
Garnish with tomato wedges.

title: nutty apricot cake
directions: Prepare the cake mix as per the directions on box. Omit the water. Substitute the apricots (chopped) and their syrup for the water. Mix per box directions. Stir in walnuts and cinnamon. Grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt pan. Sprinkle the pecans on the bottom of pan. Pour the batter and bake per box directions. No topping is necessary; just remove from pan, slice and serve.

title: chicken gumbo soup
directions: Cut meat into small pieces.
Add vegetables and bay leaves to broth and cook until vegetables are almost done.
Add meats and okra and simmer 15 minutes.

title: goody bars
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and margarine together and press in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla, 2 eggs and powdered sugar together.
Stir in chocolate chips and spread this mixture on top of mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° until you can stick a toothpick in center and it comes out nearly clean.
Do not overbake.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk in heavy saucepan.
Stir frequently to avoid scorching.

Mixture will boil; allow to boil about 5 minutes until it reaches 234° on candy thermometer or "soft ball stage. When mixture reaches desired temperature, remove from range top and stir in peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Stir quickly until smooth.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch or jelly roll style pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Allow to cool and cut into squares.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate.

title: swiss cream steak
directions: Melt 4 tablespoons butter in large skillet.
Saute onions, remove from skillet.
Pound steak strips and dredge in flour seasoned with salt, pepper and paprika.
Melt remaining butter in skillet, brown meat well on both sides.
Mix in prepared onions, water and sour cream until well blended.
Cover, cook over medium heat until meat is tender (35 to 45 minutes).
Uncover and cook until sauce thickens, about 10 minutes.
Serve over hot, cooked noodles.

title: chili and tamale casserole
directions: Spread chili in 11 X 7 inch or larger baking dish.
Remove paper from tamales, place tamales on chili.
Sprinkle with onion and cheese.
Bake in 350 degree oven
25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked vegetable medley
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in 7 x 10-inch low glass pan.
Cover and bake 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: jalapeno potatoes
directions: Cool, peel and slice potatoes.
Layer in baking dish.
Layer sliced onion and thin slices of bell pepper.
Add salt and pepper. Melt and blend flour and butter.
Cook until bubbling.
Add milk. Cook until thick.
Add garlic and jalapeno cheese.
Pour over layers forming a top layer.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: teriyaki turkey wings
directions: Place wings in a single layer in a shallow pan.
Roast, uncovered, in 375° oven 45 minutes until skin is crisp.
Drain.

title: yellow coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions.
Cook approximately 45 minutes or until done.
Then take out of oven and punch several holes.
Pour crushed pineapple with syrup all over the cake.
Let cool.

title: six 3's ice cream
directions: Blend bananas with milk and sugar.
Dump all ingredients into ice cream freezer; add milk to fill line.

title: hamburger bean pot soup
directions: Heat water and beans to boiling and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand 1 hour.
Reheat and cook for 20 minutes. Then add all other ingredients, except hamburger.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour meatballs with rice
directions: Mix ground beef, bread crumbs, onions, egg and garlic.
Make meatballs and brown.
Pour off fat.
Add rest of ingredients, except rice, and cook 20 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all the ingredients in casserole dish (greased) and bake at 350° for 25-30 minutes.
Add 1 cup cheese on top and bake for 10 more minutes.

title: crispy eggplant
directions: In small bowl, stir together first 3 ingredients.
Combine bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Brush both sides of eggplant with mayonnaise mixture.
Coat with crumbs.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in a 350° oven until golden brown.

title: baked bananas(malaysia)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream the butter and the sugar together.
Beat in the cloves, orange, lemon juice and ginger. Lay the bananas on a well-greased medium baking dish and spread the butter mixture over them.
Put the dish into the oven and bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until the top is bubbling and the bananas are cooked through and tender.
Remove from the oven and serve at once.
Serves 6.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt. Cut in shortening.
Combine remaining ingredients and stir into shortening mix.
Let stand a few minutes.
Roll dough to desired thickness.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need a bowl, a spoon and a flower.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar together until light.
Add oil a little at a time, beating continuously.
Add eggs, one at a time as you continue beating.
Mix salt and flour together, then add alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla last.
Bake in greased tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or 1 hour for 2 loaf pans.
Cool on rack before turning out of pan.

title: cranberry orange gelatin mold
directions: Add boiling water to gelatin, salt and spices in bowl; stir until dissolved.
Add cranberry sauce and orange rind.
Chill until thickened.
Fold in apples and oranges.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours or overnight.
Makes 9 servings.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
In shallow dish, combine bread crumbs and salad dressing mix.
Dip chicken in melted butter, then in bread crumb mixture to coat. Place in greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender and juices run clear, turning once during baking.

title: caramel corn
directions: Place popcorn in cake pan.
Boil all ingredients for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add soda.
Keep stirring.
Pour over popcorn.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: shrimp curry
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Melt butter in a large skillet and add shrimp.
Saute over low heat for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add the soups and stir until blended.
Stir in curry powder, parsley flakes and sour cream.
Heat thoroughly.
Do not boil.
Serve on hot, fluffy rice.

title: turkey or chicken divan(great for leftover turkey.)
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Stir together yogurt, soup (don't add water) and curry powder.
Place broccoli in prepared pan.
Top with turkey.
Pour yogurt mixture over turkey. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Top with cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: moussaka with eggplant
directions: Brown hamburg in oil.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Brown eggplants in oleo after peeling, slicing and salting (let set about 5 minutes).
Cover bottom of roasting pan with tomato sauce and a layer of eggplant, followed by hamburg, then crumbled cheese.
Cover with tomato sauce.
Repeat until all ingredients are used, ending with tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti amore
directions: Brown meat with onion, celery and green pepper.
Drain excess grease.
Add garlic, soups and water; stir.
Add 1/2 of the cheese (cut up).
Mix well, then pour in casserole and top with rest of the shredded cheese.
Use 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 2 casseroles; eat one and freeze the other.

title: seasoned baked potato wedges
directions: Wash the potatoes well.
Cut the potatoes in half, then in half again.
In a paper bag, mix the Parmesan cheese and flour.
Place the potatoes in the bag of flour mixture and shake until well coated.
Place the potatoes on a baking dish and pour the melted butter or margarine over the potatoes.
Bake in a 350° oven until golden brown and tender when pierced with a fork.
It may be necessary to rotate or turn the potatoes once while they are cooking to ensure even cooking.
Serves 4 healthy eaters.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Put into bread pan.
Bake at 350° or 375°.

title: christmas hard candy
directions: In a large heavy saucepan, combine sugar, corn syrup and water.
Cook on medium-high heat until candy thermometer reads 300° (hard crack stage), stirring occasionally.
Remove from the heat; stir in oil and food coloring, keeping face away from mixture as odor is very strong.
Immediately pour onto an oiled cookie sheet.
Cool; break into pieces.
Store in airtight containers.
Yields about 2 pounds.

title: pink salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except jello.
Mix well.
Sprinkle dry jello on top of mixture; stir until mixture is completely pink. Refrigerate overnight in covered bowl.

title: pinto bean fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk; boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Add ingredients and stir until marshmallows are dissolved. Pour in buttered pan; cool and cut into squares.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix together and serve with vegetable spears.

title: italian soup
directions: In a stockpot; put all of the ingredients carefully into the pot.
Let simmer for 1 hour.
Serve hot with a nice Italian bread.

title: german hot potato salad
directions: Cook bacon in skillet until crisp; drain, reserving 4 tablespoons drippings.
Blend reserved bacon drippings, sugar, flour, vinegar and 2 cups water in skillet.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour over hot potatoes in serving bowl.
Add onion, crumbled bacon, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Garnish with sliced, hard-boiled eggs, paprika and parsley.

title: chicken cheese bake
directions: Cut chicken into 1-inch wide strips and place in ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan (glass).
Lay cheese over the chicken to cover. Spread undiluted mushroom soup evenly on top of cheese slices. Sprinkle stuffing mix over soup to cover evenly.
Melt margarine and drizzle over stuffing mix.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: coconut-butterscotch fudge
directions: Stir together Parkay, milk and sugar in a heavy 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly. Boil 5 minutes over medium heat.
Stir to prevent scorching. Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallow cream, then butterscotch chips until melted. Add coconut and extract.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: corned beef salad
directions: Mix jello in 1 1/2 c. boiling water to dissolve. Cool.
Add all other ingredients.
Refrigerate until set.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix flour, cheese, oleo, pepper and salt. Roll out and cut with small biscuit cutter. Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: cheezie potato
directions: Scrub and bake potato until tender.
Remove from oven.
Split top.
Spoon out potato and save skin.
In small bowl, mash potato with fork.
Sliver cheese into potato, add onion and salt, if desired.
Mix well.
Spoon back into potato skin.
Return to oven for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sausage and rice bake
directions: Fry out and drain sausage.
Mix all ingredients together, saving 1/2 cup cheese
for	topping.
Top
with
reserved cheese. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.
Serve with Ritz crackers, carrot sticks and celery.

title: creamy pasta primavera
directions: Cook pasta per instructions.
Add broccoli, carrot, green onion and red pepper the last 5 minutes of cooking time.
Drain.
In same saucepan, combine soup, water and cheese.
Heat to boil.
Stir occasionally.

title: a pound cake(by missouri oneal-gates, a cousin)
directions: Cream butter, all sugar and cream well.
Add 1 cup flour and 1 or 2 eggs at a time until all used.
Mix well.
Put cake in cold oven.
Set at 300° and cook for 2 hours.

title: tasty oyster crackers
directions: In a large bowl, mix crackers and Ranch dressing.
Add the popcorn butter and stir, stir, stir.
Let the bowl stand out for approximately 30 minutes, stirring the mixture often.
Be sure to get the crackers on the bottom to the top for drying.

title: red cabbage(rodkaal)
directions: Melt shortening in heavy skillet.
Add cabbage and remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Delicious with pork roast.
Serves 6.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Preheat oven at 325 degrees.
Blend oil, sugar, brown sugar together.
Add eggs 1 at a time into sugar mixture.
Add vanilla. Fold in apples and nuts.
Cook 50 minutes to 1 hour.
Cool 20 minutes.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Dissolve jello	in
water.
Add sugar, lemons and salt. Chill, and when
begins
to
jell, whip.
Whip milk and add to jello mixture.
Crush and line large Pyrex dish (10 x 14-inches) with wafers;
pour
in
jello
mixture.	Top
with
wafer crumbs.
Cut in squares.
May be topped with whipped cream and a cherry.

title: chocolate peanut butter pan cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt. Bring to a boil the margarine, water, shortening and cocoa.
Pour over flour, sugar and salt. Mix by hand.
In another bowl, mix eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add to the other bowl and stir well.
Pour in a 13 x 9-inch well-greased pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Make icing the last 5 minutes of cake baking.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Combine prepared whole strawberries and sugar in alternate layers and let stand for 8 to 10 hours or overnight.
Heat the fruit mixture to boiling, stirring gently.
Boil rapidly, stirring to prevent sticking.
Cook until syrup is somewhat thick, 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and skim.
Ladle into hot jars and seal.

title: sue moore's lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Add other ingredients except cheese and noodles.
Let simmer about 1 hour.
Cook noodles according to directions.
Layer noodles, sauce and cheeses. Repeat.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator dinner rolls
directions: Scald together milk, Crisco and sugar.
Cool to room temperature.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add to milk mixture.
Stir in 6 to 8 cups flour; enough to make batter consistency.
Let rise to double in bulk.
Stir into raised batter salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Make a well with remaining flour in a large pan or bowl.
Pour batter into the flour well. Mix in enough flour to make a soft dough (not sticky but don't put too much flour).
Makes about 6 dozen rolls.

title: chicken with mushrooms
directions: Heat butter in a large, covered skillet.
Add garlic and 4 tablespoons of olive oil.
Brown chicken on both sides for about 10 minutes.
Lower flame, cover and continue cooking about 25 minutes. Saute sliced onion in 2 tablespoons olive oil in separate saucepan for 5 minutes.
Add sliced mushrooms.
Simmer 15 minutes, then add to chicken.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes longer.
Pour in sherry; boil up quickly for 1 minute.
Serves 4.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and milk.
Add remaining ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Old Bay. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with crackers or bread. (Recommend doubling this recipe since crabmeat is sold in 1 pound containers and because it is so good!)

title: yummy meatballs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; roll into 1 to 1 1/2-inch meatballs. Fry until cooked through.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Stew enough yellow squash to make 2 cups (16 ounces) with 1 onion, chopped and drained. Mix together pimiento, chicken soup, sour cream, salt and pepper. Melt 1 stick oleo and mix with the herb stuffing. Add 1/3 to squash mixture. Pour into greased casserole. Add remaining stuffing. Bake at 300° to 350° for 30 minutes. This freezes well. Thaw before baking.

title: vegie pizza
directions: Separate rolls and press on cookie sheet.
Beat egg and spread over rolls.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix the remaining ingredients, except vegetables and spread over crust. Chop vegetables of your choice and top mixture.

title: mr. goodbar
directions: Line cookie sheet with wax paper.

title: blondies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat together butter and sugar in a large bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, until well blended.
Mix in vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture until well blended.
Fold in nuts and coconut.

title: mexican dip
directions: Blend together refried beans and 1/2 jar of taco sauce. Spread on cookie sheet.
Mix the remainder of taco sauce with sour cream.
Spread on top of refried beans.
Sprinkle cheese, tomatoes and olives on top of sour cream.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: sweet fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Blend until smooth.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with assorted fruits.
Yields 4 cups.

title: coleslaw with tomatoes
directions: Cut cabbage or shred with a sharp paring knife.
Mix or toss lightly in large bowl.

title: pecan and post toasties ring mold
directions: Cook and watch carefully sugar and butter for 3 minutes.
Pour hot syrup over nuts and Post Toasties and place in an ice cold ring mold.
Pack down somewhat in mold.
(For best results, place ring mold in freezer hours before using.
Grease mold with margarine.) Cool in refrigerator.
Release mold onto serving plate and serve with mounds of vanilla ice cream in center.

title: light pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add skim milk and oil; mix well.
Beat 2 egg whites until peaks form.
Fold into batter mix.
Spray griddle with Pam or other nonstick cooking spray.
Heat.
Cook pancakes as usual.
Use lite margarine and syrup or better yet, apple butter or applesauce.
These are great!
You don't miss the extra calories.
Even my picky eater son loves them and requests them for Sunday breakfast every week.

title: peach pie
directions: Can make strawberry pie the same, only use strawberry jello.

title: baked crab spread(appetizer)
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spoon into 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: chess cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and press into 13 x 9-inch pan, forming slight ridge at side.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 350. Microwave chocolate and margarine in microwaveable bowl on high for 1-2 minutes or until margarine is melted, stirring halfway through melting time. Stir until chocolate is completely melted. Stir in sugar, corn syrup, eggs and vanilla until well blended. Stir in pecan halves. Pour into unbaked pastry shell. Bake for 50 minutes, or until filling is firm 2 inches from edge. Cool on wire rack. Serve with whipped topping. Makes 8 servings.

title: slush
directions: Boil water and sugar.
Put tea bags in for 5 minutes.
Add orange juice and lemonade.
Put in ice cream pail and freeze. Stir every few hours.
To serve, put a scoop of slush in glass. Add 7-Up to fill glass.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs with an electric mixer.
Continue beating and add oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in zucchini, walnuts, coconut and raisins.
Pour into greased pans (will make 2 loaf pans, 1 Bundt pan or 1 tube pan).
Bake for approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: breakfast bake
directions: Grease or spray a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish. Crack in the eggs.
Do not beat!
Stir a little, breaking yolks.
Sprinkle on half the cheese.
Drizzle on the cream.
Sprinkle on mushrooms. Sprinkle on onion and green pepper.
Salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle on sausage.
Sprinkle on remaining cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. Test with knife for doneness. Let set 5 minutes. Cut and serve with toast and juice.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add egg yolks.
Mix graham cracker crumbs with baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with milk. Fold in egg whites, stiffly beaten, last.

title: beef sukiyaki stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet or wok; add beef and cook, stirring constantly, until meat turns gray.
Remove meat and set aside.
In same pan, add water with bouillon in it, then add green pepper, onion and celery; cook about 12 minutes.
Add soy sauce, sugar, Chinese vegetables and mushrooms, stirring to mix thoroughly.
Add steak and cook about 5 minutes until heated thoroughly.
Serve immediately over cooked rice.
The vegetables should be a little crisp.

title: jelly roll
directions: Mix and bake in greased pan.
When done, roll up with a towel. When cool, unroll and put in bananas, jam, and/or sugar mixed with cream and vanilla.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix in order, drop with ice cream scoop onto a lightly greased cookie sheet, flatten before baking.
Only 4 to 6 cookies per sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
This recipe can be divided into halves, thirds or quarters.
Whole recipe makes approximately 95 cookies.

title: healthy crab dip
directions: Combine sour cream, mayonnaise, cream cheese and seasonings. Mix well.
Then stir in Cheddar cheese and crab.
Cover.
Chill 2 hours.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with crackers, bread sticks or vegetables.
Makes approximately 20 servings.

title: hearty ham casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to
package
directions, drain. Place in 2 quart buttered casserole,
mixing well with remaining ingredients.
Top with potato chip
crumbs.
Bake
at 350° for 40 minutes or until hot through.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in homemade ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Measure and then crush Post Toasties.
Measure out 2 cups flour.
Cream butter well. Add sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in the flour, baking powder and baking soda and blend well.
Add cereals and nuts and mix well.
Makes very stiff batter.
Drop from spoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour and chill in baked pie shell.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant in two.
Scrape out inside and put in saucepan with minced ham.
Cover with water; boil until soft.
Drain and add crumbs, butter, onion, salt and pepper to taste.
Fill each half of hull with mixture.
Add small lump of butter.
Bake for 15 minutes or, if preferred, omit ham, using more bread crumbs and mixing with beaten yolks of 2 eggs.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Blend in egg, peanut butter, vanilla, dry ingredients, oats and chocolate chips.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until light brown.
Do not overbake.
Spread with icing while hot.

title: german-style slaw
directions: Place the cabbage, onion and green pepper in a large nonmetalic bowl.

title: marinated shrimp
directions: Shrimp can be deep fried, peeled or unpeeled.

If it is peeled the tail is often left on to act as a handle when it's eaten. Large shrimp are often butterflied or split down the back, filled with a stuffing, coated with a breading or batter and then deep fried.
Use any drench or dredge you like.
Fry in oil at 365° until they float and turn golden brown, about 2 minutes, depending on the size of the shrimp.

title: grandmother's mandel brot
directions: Beat sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla with mixer.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and nuts.
Add to wet mixture.
Store in refrigerator 4 hours or overnight until firm.
Knead by hand, using a bit of flour.
Make 4 strips by dividing dough into 4 parts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or longer until golden.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Crush strawberries in saucepan.
Stir in lemon juice, powdered pectin and sweetener.
Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and continue stirring for 2 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars half pint size, to within 1/4-inch of top.
Put on cap and screw tight.
When cool, store in refrigerator.
Yield:
2 1/2 pints.

title: souffle salads
directions: Add boiling water to gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Chill until the mixture begins to set, then fold in the mayonnaise and any additions you may wish to make.

title: fried bows
directions: Beat the eggs.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Make a ring of flour.
Add ingredients and knead until smooth. Add more or less flour.
Roll dough a small amount at a time about 3-inches wide, very thin.
Cut into 3-inch rectangles.
Cut a slit in center. Pull one end through slit. Deep fry until a light tan. Remove to paper towel.
These can be made a few days before needed. Will keep for a few weeks. Sprinkle powdered sugar when ready to serve.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw and cook the broccoli.
Drain.
Cook the rice as directed.
Combine the drained broccoli and rice. Mix in the soup. Add the margarine and Velveeta.
Put all of the mixture in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Great to go with chicken dishes!

title: carrot bread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Makes 1 large loaf or 2 small loaves.

title: mom's light rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Add all-purpose flour until thickens and doughy.
Pull back sides and grease bowl with shortening.
Let rise in bowl until doubles in size.
Dip fingers in cooking oil and make rolls.
Let rise again in pan.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: joy's maryland crab dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, mayonnaise, onion and garlic salt in a bowl; mix well.
Spread in shallow serving dish.
Pour chili sauce over top.
Sprinkle crab meat over chili sauce.
Garnish with chopped parsley.

title: lemon dessert salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Add 2 cups cold water.
Let cool.
Add all but one cup pie filling and pineapple. Pour in 9 x 13-inch dish and let set.
Mix reserved pie filling and Cool Whip.
Spread on top of set Jell-O.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Add one can to start of water.
Add water when needed.
Keep covered.
Cook at 325° for 3 1/2 hours.
Twenty minutes before serving, add 1 pound mushrooms, fresh.

title: moist turkey dressing
directions: Cook the chicken, celery and onions together.
While this is cooking, mix the Stove Top, cornbread stuffing mix, eggs, sausage and sage seasoning (to your taste) together.
When chicken is done, remove it from the bone and tear it into tiny pieces.
Add to the broth, pour the broth, onions, celery and chicken into the bread mixture.
Mix well.
If the dressing is not moist enough, use the drippings from the turkey.
Bake in 325° oven until lightly browned and done.

title: vegetable and meat casserole
directions: Place meat of choice in bottom of baking dish.
Add potatoes, beans and carrots.
Cover with soup.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: Heat a small amount of oil in a large skillet; fry chicken until browned.
Drain;
place chicken in a 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish.
In a saucepan, saut onion in butter until tender, stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered for 15 minutes. Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350 about 1 hour or until chicken is done, baking occasionally.
Yield:
6-8 servings.

title: old fashion pot pie
directions: Put all in the bowl; add cold water a little at a time.
Stir until you have a soft dough, like pie dough.
Roll out thin.
Cut in strips.

title: orange julius
directions: In blender, mix together 3 cups orange juice and rest of ingredients.
Blend, gradually adding the remaining 3 cups juice. Refrigerate.

title: exploding dessert
directions: Melt butter; mix with other ingredients, except ice cream. Put half of mixture on bottom of a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with 1/2 gallon softened ice cream.
Smooth with a spoon; cover with remaining mixture.
Cover with foil and freeze.

title: grape nuts bread
directions: Soak Grape-Nuts an hour in the cup of buttermilk.
Then add egg and sugar.
Combine flour, baking powder, soda and salt; stir into mixture along with the teaspoon of melted butter. Mix well. Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake in 350° oven 45 to 50 minutes.

title: orange freeze
directions: Empty orange concentrate into blender container.
Fill can with milk and pour into container.
Blend together with ice cubes. Pour into 4 (6 ounce) glasses.
Mixture is thick enough to eat with a spoon.

title: raspberry pretzel jello salad
directions: Mix pretzels and margarine and bake for 10 minutes at 375° in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking pan.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar together and spread over crumbs.
Cover all crumbs.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over cream cheese mixture.
Set in fridge and let thicken until well set.

title: mckinley pie
directions: Place fruit in cake dish.
Sweeten fruit with sugar as desired.
Add some water to fruit, then take a box of cake mix and spread over contents.
Take quarter sticks of pure butter and slice, about 1/8-inch thick.
Cover entire dish solid and bake at 450° for 45 to 60 minutes or until brown.

title: great meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Turn
into loaf pan; top with small amount of sauce, if desired.	Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: Melt butter in heavy fry pan or Dutch oven.
Saute onion and garlic 5 minutes; add mushrooms and meat, browning lightly.
Add celery, stock, wine, tomato paste, tomato, salt, pepper, parsley and flour.
Mix thoroughly.

title: congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water.
Add cottage cheese.
Stir until all is dissolved.
Cut grapes in half and add.
Add crushed pineapple and pecans.
Pour in mold and let set overnight.
I have some children that do not eat pecans, so I leave them out.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: In saucepan on low heat, melt butter with sugar, vanilla, salt, cocoa and milk; bring to boil.
Remove from heat.
Blend in 1/2 cup peanut butter if wanted.
Mix well.
Add oats; mix again. Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
Cool.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: spoon bread
directions: Bring milk to boil.
Stir in cornmeal and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool until batter is stiff.
Add eggs, baking powder, salt and butter; beat with electric beater 5 minutes.
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Measure rice, salt and water into saucepan, bring to a boil. Cook until rice is tender about 40 minutes.
Place rice on top of double boiler, stir in sweetened condensed milk and butter.
Cook, stirring frequently over until slightly thickened, about 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla.
To make parfaits, spoon alternating layers of creamy rice pudding with canned pie filling, any flavor.
Top with whipped cream.
Wala!!
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potatoes, butter, eggs, milk, sugar, salt, spices and flavorings in mixer bowl; beat well.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 425° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until set.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: smoked oyster dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer until smooth.
Best if made one day in advance.
Serve with corn chips or potato chips.

title: apple butter
directions: Mix applesauce and sugar; bring to a boil. Cook 10 minutes and add pineapple. Cook 10 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Working quickly, mix well and can.
Seal.
Use a heavy pan and watch closely to keep from scorching.

title: asparagus vinaigrette
directions: Blanch cook fresh asparagus until crisp-tender and rinse under cold water.
If using frozen spears, thaw and drain well.

title: bean and corn salad
directions: Mix and drain beans, peas and corn.
Mix together all ingredients and chill overnight.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Boil margarine, sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and butter flavoring gently for 5 minutes.
Add baking soda.
Mix with popped corn and stir.
Place in 2 large, buttered cake pans and bake at 200° for 1 hour.
Stir 2 to 3 times during and after baking.

title: farm style potato frittata(brunch, lunch or supper)
directions: This recipe is for 4 servings.
For 2 servings, half the ingredients and for 8 servings, double the ingredients.

title: chewy bars
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm, then add brown sugar.

Stir in dry ingredients, then vanilla and eggs. Fold in marshmallows and chocolate chips until just combined. Bake in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Don't overbake; it firms up as it cools.
Cut into bars.

title: hash
directions: Brown meat and onions in fat.
Stir in rice, water, bouillon cube and tomato paste.
Add seasoning.
Heat to boiling; stir well.
Cover and simmer for 25 minutes.
Add cheese and toss lightly.

title: "seven day" slaw
directions: Slice cabbage and onions or shred them.
Toss with 1/3 cup of sugar.
Mix remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour boiling mixture over cabbage, let set and in five minutes, mix. Chill in refrigerator.
Serves 4.

title: turkey curry salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine mayonnaise and sour cream or yogurt; stir in curry powder,
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: scrambled eggs(makes 6 servings)
directions: In an 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking dish, crumble meat. Microwave, uncovered, on 100% power (High) for 3 to 5 minutes or until meat loses its pink color, stirring once during cooking. Drain off fat, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings in the baking dish.
Place meat on paper toweling.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in a 2-quart baking dish.
Mix together the milk, baking powder, flour, sugar and salt.
Pour batter over margarine, don't stir.
Bake at 400° until done.
Fruit will be on bottom and dough on top.

title: florentine casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender; put in baking dish.
Melt 1/2 stick margarine and Velveeta cheese.
Pour over vegetables.
Melt remaining 1/2 stick margarine and mix with cracker crumbs.
Top vegetables with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until brown.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichokes, then chop them into small pieces.
Combine with all other ingredients, except parsley.
Mix well.
Pour into small baking dish.
Sprinkle parsley on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, until bubbly.
Serve with crackers.

title: margarete's surprise dessert
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Add pudding and pie filling after cool.
Top with Cool Whip, nuts and coconut.

title: chopped chicken livers
directions: Boil livers about 15 to 20 minutes.
Boil eggs until hard-boiled.
Saute onion (sliced) until golden brown.
Skim fat and other residue from livers and rinse in hot water.
Peel and slice eggs.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup
and water in 4-quart saucepan. Bring to a boil on medium heat.
Boil for 5 minutes. Add butter, peanuts and salt.
Boil until thick, stirring constantly.
Drop a little bit in cup of cold water.
If candy cracks, it is done.
Turn off stove. Add vanilla and baking soda.
Stir. (Be careful, mixture will bubble up and pop a little.)
Pour into 2 buttered 9 x 2 x 13-inch pans.
Let cool.
Break into pieces.

title: banana muffins
directions: Mash bananas. Add egg and beat.
Stir in shortening and sugar. Mix
well.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour in muffin tins. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yield:
1 dozen muffins.

title: czech family sauerkraut
directions: Turn undrained kraut into large enough saucepan and cover with water, then sprinkle with caraway seed and the brown sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Fry bacon pieces in skillet until half done; get rid of drippings.
Add the garlic and onion to bacon and cook 3 to 4 more minutes.
Now sprinkle the flour over the bacon and onion mixture and stir in the flour until thoroughly incorporated with the bacon mixture.
Now pour the water from the simmered kraut into the bacon-onion mixture, stirring and cook 4 or 5 minutes or until mixture is thickened.
Now pour the thickened mixture over the cooked kraut and stir to mix thoroughly. This makes 5 to 6 servings.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: grandma's berry shortcake
directions: Sift flour once; measure.
Add baking powder, salt and sugar; sift into a bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture looks like coarse meal.
Add milk, mixing until a soft dough is formed. Knead dough on lightly floured board half a minute.
Divide and pat 1/2-inch thick in two greased 9-inch layer pans. Bake in hot oven, 450°, for 20 minutes, or until done.

title: frying pan cookies
directions: Put sugar, dates and eggs in lightly buttered skillet (deep iron frying pan is great).
Simmer at low heat for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add nuts, salt and Rice Krispies.
Stir. Remove from heat and cool slightly.
With buttered fingers, form in 1-inch balls and roll in coconut, nuts, powdered sugar, etc.

title: peanut butter rolls
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, vanilla and just enough milk to moisten. (You may want to use your hands.)
Roll out in confectioners sugar about the size of a pin and then spread with peanut butter. Roll up as a jelly roll.
Slice.

title: ground beef stroganoff
directions: Brown onion
with ground beef in skillet.
Add consomme and tomato
paste to crock-pot with ground beef mixture.
Cook on low 6 to 8 hours.

title: sparkling strawberry punch
directions: About 10 minutes before serving, blend strawberries and undiluted lemonade concentrate in covered blender on high speed. Pour mixture in chilled punch bowl and add remaining ingredients. Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Put in 3 trays of ice.
Garnish with orange slices.

title: pasta salad
directions: Soak sun-dried tomatoes in hot water for 30 minutes; drain and set aside.
Cook pasta according to directions on package.
Run under cold water and drain well.
While pasta is cooking, prepare dressing.

title: virginia ham biscuits(yorktown cookbook)
directions: Sift flour and baking powder and mix with salt and ham.
Cut in shortening with knife until all is consistency of meal.
Add milk.
Handle as little as possible.
Pat with hands or roll on floured board.
Bake in hot oven until brown.

title: applesauce squares or diamonds
directions: Mix in order given and bake in a large cookie sheet type pan at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Ice with a maple flavored icing or serve plain.

title: curried salad dressing
directions: Mix everything together, except the milk. If too thick, add enough milk to reach pouring consistency. Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours to allow the flavors to develop.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix together 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs thoroughly.
Blend flour, tartar, baking soda and salt and stir.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons of sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased baking pan. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
The cookies puff and then flatten.

title: taco soup
directions: *If you don't like kidney beans, mix pinto and navy beans.

title: chicken continental
directions: Roll chicken pieces in flour. Brown in butter in skillet. Remove chicken to ovenproof dish and cover. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Remove cover and bake 30 minutes more.
Combine all other ingredients except rice in skillet with chicken drippings.
Bring to a
boil. Add rice in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Bake rice at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: sauerkraut soup
directions: Chop the sausage coarsely by hand or in a food processor. Transfer the chopped sausage and onion to a deep pan; saute over medium heat until the sausage is lightly browned, about 8 minutes. On a small plate or on wax paper, combine the flour, thyme and pepper.
Add to the sausage and brown all together until the mixture bubbles up, about 5 minutes.
Add the milk and half and half all at once; cook, stirring, until the mixture again bubbles up, about 5 minutes.
Add the sauerkraut and its juice; bring to a boil.
The mixture will continue to thicken.
Taste for tartness; add lemon juice, if desired.

title: italian casserole
directions: Saute onions and green peppers in butter.
Brown ground beef and pour off grease.
Add garlic salt, onions and peppers.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce and water.
Cook until boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes.
Pour half of the beef mixture into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Top with noodles.
Add the remaining beef mixture and top with cheese, making sure all noodles are covered.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Melt butter in large skillet; add shrimp and garlic.
Saute, stirring constantly, for about 3 to 5 minutes or until shrimp turns pink.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook, stirring gently, for about 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: scones with berries
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper. Keep berries frozen until time to use. In a large bowl, whisk together unsifted flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Mix in butter until mixture is size of fine crumbs. Stir in buttermilk and then stir in berries. Be careful to use the fruit and not the liquid. Shape dough into two 7-inch circles on prepared baking sheet. Cut each circle into 6 wedges and coat with cooking spray. Bake until cooked through and golden, about 20 minutes. Yields 1 wedge per serving.

title: chili relleno bake
directions: Brown hamburg and onion.
Drain off fat and season.
Lay chillies in bottom of a 9x13 pan,
cover with hamburg, then sprinkle with cheese.
Mix flour, eggs and milk and pour over top. Bake at 350 degrees for 45-50 minutes.

title: oatmeal raisin bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients with boiling water; cool to 105° to 115°.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water and add to oats mixture.
Gradually stir in enough flour to make soft dough.
Turn out and knead until smooth.
Put in a greased bowl, cover and let rise until double.
Punch down and turn out on floured board. Knead 2 minutes.
Divide in half and let rest for 10 minutes.

title: gravy baked pork chops
directions: Sprinkle the pork chops with salt and pepper.
Brown chops on both sides in skillet on medium heat in shortening.
Drain grease. Mix soup, half and half and water together.
Pour over chops in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Stir gravy well before serving.

title: pork and cabbage
directions: Brown ground pork and onion in skillet, stirring frequently. Add salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat for 5 to 10 minutes. Separate cabbage into leaves.
Add to pork mixture with 1 cup water.
Steam, covered, for 5 minutes or until cabbage is tender-crisp.
Stir in noodles.
Simmer, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes or until heated through.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: simple shrimp curry
directions: Saute shrimp in butter for 3 to 5 minutes over low heat.
Stir and turn.
Add soups and blend well.
Stir in sour cream and curry powder.
Continue stirring until very hot.
Serve over rice or spoon into hot patty shells.

title: vegetable grinder
directions: Prepare vegetables; season to taste.
Saute until just cooked. Serve in hard rolls.
Makes 4 sandwiches.
May be topped with grated cheese.

title: icebox cookies(from the files of viola clark williams)
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Have baking sheets ready; do not grease.
Start oven 10 minutes before baking; set to 400°.
Sift flour, measure; resift 3 times with salt and soda. Cream butter until smooth; add sugars gradually, creaming thoroughly.
Stir in vanilla, then eggs one at a time, and beat until well blended.
Add flour in 3 portions, mixing well after each.
Stir in nuts.
Chill dough until stiff, then divide in half and place on 2 sheets of waxed paper.
Quickly shape into 2 uniform rolls about 2 inches in diameter, then roll up in the paper.
Store in refrigerator until very firm, from 4 to 6 hours. When firm, slice with a sharp knife into 1/4-inch thick cookies. Bake 8 to 10 minutes to a pale golden color.
Dough will keep in refrigerator 3 to 5 days.
Makes 40 cookies.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together; put into a greased large casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, or longer if you prefer it drier.

title: recipe for a happy home
directions: Mix thoroughly in a good-natured pan.
Then sprinkle with a little sympathy over the top.
Bake at an even temperature for as long as you live.
Remember to serve large helpings and serve often.
This can be prepared so easily.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine flour, corn meal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, egg and melted margarine.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in 8-inch square pan for 20 to 25 minutes in 425° oven.

title: vogelpahl ice cream recipe
directions: Mix egg yolks, sugar and 1 quart of milk together in a large bowl.
Add vanilla, can of milk and salt.
In another bowl, whip egg whites until foamy.
Add egg whites to egg yolk mixture.
Pour into freezer can and add more milk until it reaches the fill line mark on can.
Now you are ready!
Makes 1 gallon.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Bring 1 3/4 cups of water to rolling boil.
Add salt.
Stir in dry rice; cover and cook.
Brown the sausage.
Add to cooked rice. Add oil, cheese and milk to make soupy mixture.
Add sausage, bell pepper, onion, parsley, salt and pepper.
Place in 3-quart casserole.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 300°.
Serves 8.

title: prune cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and Wesson oil.
Add flour and spices; add buttermilk, nuts and prunes.
Last mix well.
Cook in stem pan 60 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake for 30 minutes at 450°.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 9-inch square baking pan.
Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat. Stir in remaining ingredients (sugars, eggs, peanut butter, flour, vanilla and chocolate chips); mix well.
Spread in prepared pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Cut into 16 squares.

title: tostado casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add salt, pepper, garlic, chili powder and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: make sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in an electric blender.
Process until smooth.
Store in refrigerator.
Use as you would regular condensed milk.
Yields about 1 1/4 cups.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Bake cake to box directions.
Pack light brown sugar in bottom of cake pan.
Place pineapple over brown sugar, 7 or 8 slices, depending on cake size.
In middle of pineapple hole, put a whole cherry.
Cover with cake batter and bake at 350°, until a toothpick is clean.
When cake is nearly cool, turn upside-down in cake dish.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook in the pan where the streak-o-lean was fried.
Cook for approximately 15 minutes (with just enough water to cover) on low to medium heat.

title: apple pie in a bag
directions: Toss apples, 1/2 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons flour and spices. Fill pie shell.
Sprinkle lemon juice over this.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar, flour and butter into soft paste.
Spread over apples. Place in large brown grocery bag.
Fold top sharply 3 times.
Bake for 1 hour.
Let cool 15 to 20 minutes before opening bag to avoid burns.
Ignore burning smell while cooking.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Grease a large cookie sheet with butter.
Cook sugar, syrup and water until a soft ball forms (236°).
Add peanuts and cook until amber colored (294°).
Remove from stove and add vanilla and soda.
Stir for 30 to 45 seconds, briskly.
Pour onto cookie sheet and spread out quickly to about 1 peanut thickness.
Once cooled, run a flat knife under it to loosen and turn onto a brown paper bag.
Wipe excess grease from surface.
When completely cooled, break into pieces.

title: egg noodles
directions: With a fork, beat eggs, salt and water until blended. Add sifted flour and mix, may take more flour. Dough should be stiff. For ease in rolling, divide the dough in half. Roll out as thin as you can. Allow to "rest" for about 30 minutes. Cut in long strips, then stack the strips and then cut them as narrow or as wide as you prefer. Add them to boiling chicken or beef stock. They freeze well, uncooked.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add seasonings; drain.
Mix in soup.
Put in baking dish.
Layer Tater Tots.
Layer cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: orange-cauliflower salad
directions: Toss oranges, cauliflower, green pepper, spinach and dressing.
Serve in lettuce cups.
6 servings
120 calories per serving

title: stewed tomatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaves.
Spoon hot mixture into hot sterilized jars, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Cover at once with metal lids and screw bands tight.
Process in pressure canner at 10 pounds pressure (240) 15 minutes.
Yield: 7 pints.
About 41 calories and 14 milligrams sodium per 1/2 cup serving.

title: mexican salad
directions: Prepare lettuce as for a tossed salad.
Drain and wash chilled beans.
Add to lettuce.
Add diced tomatoes, onion, grated cheese and dressing.
Chill 30 minutes before serving.
Add chips just before serving and mix well.
Yields 12 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: carrot delight
directions: Drain pineapple and mandarins.
Add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid, heat.
Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup hot fruit water.
Add sherbet and the remaining water, mix.
Add softened cream cheese, carrots and pineapple.
Pour into a mold, top with mandarins, freeze.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: low calorie cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over milk in top of double boiler. Beat in egg yolks. Cook and stir until gelatin dissolves and mixture thickens slightly (about 5 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar, lime juice, vanilla, almond and salt. Set aside.

title: crock-pot hot mulled cider
directions: Combine cider and brown sugar in crock-pot.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Tie allspice, cloves and cinnamon in cheesecloth. Add to cider mixture.
Add orange slices.
Heat, covered, on low for 30 minutes.
Keep warm on low for 1 1/2 to 7 1/2 hours. Yields 8 servings.

title: cherry torte
directions: Mix melted butter, flour and nuts.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese and powdered sugar, then add the Cool Whip.
Mix and pour over crust.
Pour pie filling over mixture.
Keep refrigerated.

title: fruity cranberry punch
directions: Mix all together.
Add ice, then ginger ale last, when ready to serve.

title: mrs. texas casserole
directions: Brown meat and drain off fat.
Add salt, sugar, tomatoes, tomato sauce, garlic powder and pepper.
Combine cooked noodles, cream cheese, sour cream and green onions.
Add this to meat mixture.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart casserole; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: Chop chocolate; melt with butter; add cream. Gradually stir in sugar until lump-free. Cover and refrigerate 12 to 24 hours. Make individual balls by rolling between palms of bands. Roll balls in any of the nuts or cocoa. Refrigerate until 2 hours before serving.

title: cottage cheese and cool whip salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
You can also use orange Jell-O and mandarin oranges with the pineapple.

title: microwave tortellini casserole
directions: Remove sausage from casing.
In 2 1/2-quart casserole, cook sausage, onion and garlic, covered, on High, 2 to 4 minutes, until done.
Drain.
Set aside.
Coarsely chop 2 tomatoes, tortellini, bouillon and 1/4 cup water.
Cook, covered, on High, 10 to 14 minutes until tortellini are almost tender.
Stir occasionally. Cut zucchini into 1/2-inch pieces.
Add to casserole.
Cook 5 minutes.
Cut up remaining tomato.
Stir in tomato and basil. Cover and let stand 2 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Mix sugar and flour.
Put
peaches in melted margarine and add milk.
Pour flour and sugar over the top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet; add diced onion.
Drain off fat. Add soups and 1 soup can of water.
Mix well.
Cook this mixture until hot, over low heat.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place cooked spaghetti in oblong baking dish.
Pour soup and hamburger mixture over spaghetti.
Spread evenly.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake 1 hour at 350° or until brown.

title: butter cookies
directions: Allow butter to soften.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs; beat.
Mix well.
Add vanilla and lemon juice or almond extract; mix well.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Divide into portions. Roll and cut as desired.
Bake at 475° for 3 minutes.
Cool and decorate, if desired.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Brown sausage with vegetables.
Drain and add sausage. Return to frying pan and add cheese cubes.
Let melt while stirring often.
Once they have melted, add eggs and move around with spatula,
like scrambling eggs, until they are set.
Turn off heat.
Cut english muffins in half and top with mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes until bottoms of muffins are crispy. You can also freeze these and just
pop in
the oven whenever you like.

title: stew beef
directions: Mix everything but sour cream together. Cook in crock-pot all day on low. Mix in sour cream to taste before serving.

title: lebkuchen (german pastry)
directions: Mix honey and molasses.
Boil and stir in sugar, egg, lemon juice and rind.
Add flour.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Mix in citron and nuts.
Chill overnight.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll small amount at a time, keeping rest chilled.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into oblong pieces.
Place 1-inch apart on a greased baking sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Immediately remove from pan.
Cool; store to mellow.

title: sausage cake
directions: Mix the sausage and brown sugar. Add nuts, raisins and flour. Mix the baking soda and coffee and add to mixture. Add other ingredients and bake at 350° for 2 hours in 10-inch Bundt pan.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa.
Add egg yolks, Pet milk, vanilla and butter.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Spread meringue on top.
Bake at 250° until golden brown.

title: peanut butter fudge bars
directions: Mix together the yellow cake mix, peanut butter, melted 1/2 cup margarine and eggs.
Press 2/3 of dough into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch cookie sheet.

title: hidden valley cheese balls
directions: Mix together; form a ball (optional).
Serve with crackers. Yields 1 cheese ball.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake mix in 9 x 13-inch according to package directions.

title: creamy chicken bake
directions: Boil chicken; remove bones.
Place chicken in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Cover chicken with partially cooked broccoli.
Melt butter and pour over broccoli.
Mix cheese and soup and spoon over broccoli.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350°.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound flour and seasonings into steak with steak hammer (or edge of plate).
Melt fat in skillet.
Brown meat on both sides over medium heat.
Place in casserole.
Add water or juice (juice preferred) and onion.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: roast
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover tightly.
Cook on high in crock-pot for 4 to 6 hours, depending on the size of the roast.

title: cherry dream squares(microwave)
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine cake mix, 6 tablespoons oleo and 1 cup oats.
Mix until crumbly.
Reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping. To remaining crumbs, add 1 egg and mix until well blended.
Press into a 9
x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Pour cherry pie filling over crust and spread to cover.
To reserved crumbs, add remaining 1/4 cup rolled oats, 2 tablespoons oleo, nuts and brown sugar. Beat until thoroughly mixed.
Spread over cherries.
Microwave at 70% power for 12 to 14 minutes, giving dish a 1/4 turn twice during cooking.
Cool and serve with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: double peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients; beat in eggs and vanilla. Stir together flour, soda and 1/4 teaspoon salt; blend into batter. Stir in nuts. Form into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten slightly with fingers. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes 6 dozen.

title: ginger fruit salad
directions: Prepare all fruit by washing, peeling, removing pits and slicing into bite-size pieces.
Melons may be scooped out with a melon baller, if desired.
Combine all fruit in a large ceramic bowl.
Mix lime juice, rind, honey and ginger together.
Pour over fruit, toss and marinate at least six hours.
Serve chilled or at room temperature.
Yield:
8 servings.
Carbohydrate 24 g, protein 1 g, fat .4 g, calories 128.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Store in airtight container.
Add 2 or 3 heaping teaspoonfuls per cup of hot water.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine salad dressing and seasonings.
Mix with other ingredients.

title: ding dong cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions; cool. Mix sugar, cream cheese and cool whip. Split cake into layers. Spread sugar mixture on bottom and replace top. Microwave frosting about 20 seconds and pour over cake.

title: puppy chow
directions: In saucepan, combine peanut butter, oleo and chocolate morsels.
Melt until smooth.
In large bowl, mix Rice Chex and melted chocolate until well coated.
Put 10x sugar in large food storage bag and add chocolate coated Rice Chex.
Seal bag and shake until Rice Chex is well coated.

title: reba's gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, egg and molasses.
Add dry ingredients.
Add hot water; beat until smooth.
Bake in 7 x 11-inch pan for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: split pea soup
directions: Simmer in crock-pot for 5 to 8 hours, or boil gently 2 to 3 hours in a large kettle.
Take meat off bone; return to soup.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Can puree with hand held blender, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onions together.
Drain.
Add red dark kidney beans, chili beans, chili seasoning, cut up tomatoes and cooked macaroni.
Let simmer for about an hour.
Instead of macaroni, you could pour your chili over cooked white rice.

title: chocolate-oatmeal cake
directions: In large bowl cream together first 4 ingredients.
Sift together the next 3 ingredients and add to those in the bowl. Combine 1/2 cup chocolate chips, water and oatmeal; let stand for 10 minutes.
Add this to the bowl and pour into a cake pan and top with the last 2 ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes and serve with whip cream.

title: brotherhood cookies
directions: Take 1 large field, half a dozen children, 2 or 3 small dogs, a pinch of brook and some pebbles.
Mix the children and dogs well together; put them on the field, stirring constantly.
Pour the brook over the pebbles; sprinkle the field with flowers; spread over all a deep blue sky and bake in the sun.
When brown, set away to cool in the bathtub.

title: lemon crush
directions: Mix flour, margarine and sugar together and press in jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: kathleen's cranberry tea
directions: Place cloves and cinnamon stick in a tea ball.
Stir all ingredients together; add tea ball and simmer for 10 minutes. Serve hot or cold.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Put can of tomatoes in a large skillet.
Mix all together the other ingredients in a large bowl.
Shape into golf ball size meatballs and place in tomatoes in skillet.
Heat to boiling, then cover and simmer about 15 to 20 minutes, turning meatballs over once during cooking.
Serve with rice.

title: easy cheese sauce
directions: Mix cornstarch and milk until smooth.
Add margarine, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Boil 1 minute.
Add cheese to sauce.
Stir until cheese is melted.

title: peanut butter chompers
directions: Add peanut butter to warm honey and mix well.
Stir in dry milk and form into small balls.

title: tropical fruit salsa
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees. Halve onion, brush cut sides with olive oil. Cook cut side down in a roasting pan until caramelized. 1 hour 20 minutes. Turn onions over let cool. Peel onions and cut into 1/4 inch dice. Combine onions with the remaining ingredients toss well.

title: eggdrop soup
directions: Slowly mix the cornstarch into the chicken broth and bring to a boil (no lumps).
When thick, whisk in beaten egg with fork. Pour into individual bowls and garnish with onion.

title: three layer water cake
directions: Mix all together; bake at 350° in round pans.

title: hearty stew
directions: Trim fat from steak.
Spray Dutch oven with cooking spray. Brown on all sides.
Remove and place on paper towel to drain. Wipe grease from oven.
Re-coat with spray.
Add carrots and onion. Saute until slightly brown.
Return steak to pan.
Add all other ingredients.
Stir and simmer on low for 1 1/2 hours.
Add beans and simmer 30 minutes.
Yield:
2 1/2 quarts.
Serving size:
1 cup.

title: cream of abalone soup
directions: Boil potatoes in clam juice.
Saute onions and celery in butter until golden brown.

Add abalone and continue to cook. Gradually add flour, stirring constantly, until smooth, then add 1 plus quart milk slowly and continue to stir until well blended. Season to taste with m.s.g., salt, pepper, Worcestershire, Tabasco and clam juice.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Beat eggs, add buttermilk and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Combine flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Mix and add to buttermilk mixture. Cook on preheated griddle.
Serve with butter and maple syrup.

title: sweet potato-pineapple casserole
directions: Mix everything together.
Place in large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat until well mixed (about 5 minutes on low-medium).
Pour into large oblong cake pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes (at least).
I bake longer.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Soak gelatine in water.
Heat soup (right from can) to boiling and add cream cheese.
With fork, beat until cream cheese is thoroughly blended and smooth.
Add gelatine and mix well.
Cool. Add mayonnaise, celery, onion and shrimp.
Pour into 4 cup mold and refrigerate until firm.
Unmold on serving platter and garnish as desired.
Serve with bread or crackers.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: chicken rice-a-roni casserole
directions: Boil chicken; separate from bones into bite size pieces. Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix in sour cream and soup. Prepare Rice-A-Roni as directed on box.
Mix Rice-A-Roni in with chicken and soup.
Grate cheese and cover top.
Place in oven at 350° until cheese melts and casserole is bubbling.

title: lemon-poppy seed bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Combine milk and 3 tablespoons of lemon juice; set aside. Beat eggs and granulated sugar with spoon in a large mixing bowl. Stir in mayonnaise.
Add flour and milk mixture alternately to mayonnaise mixture, beginning and ending with flour.
Stir well after each addition.
Stir in 2 teaspoons lemon rind and poppy seed.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 50 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Combine remaining lemon juice, remaining lemon rind and powdered sugar.
Pour over bread in pan.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove to wire rack and cool completely.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In a baking dish, combine soup, milk and seasonings. Add meat and drained vegetables. Bake at 400° until mixture begins to bubble (approximately 15 to 20 minutes). Cut biscuits into fourths while this bakes. Remove dish from oven and stir. Arrange biscuits on top and bake until biscuits are golden brown.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream oil and sugar; add eggs and blend in molasses.
Dissolve soda in hot water; add to mixture.
Sift flour, salt and spices; add to creamed mixture.
Add boiling water.
Bake in greased 13 x 9 1/2-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: homemade dressing
directions: Pour hot water over bread.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Add chicken broth.
Mix well.
If too dry, add more broth or water.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes one large or two small pans.

title: pickled rosebuds
directions: Place washed buds in the jar.
Dissolve the sugar in the vinegar over heat and fill the jar to the top.
Seal and store in the cupboard for about two weeks before using.
Serve with crab, lobster or chicken salad sandwiches.
Makes 1 pint.

title: banana pancakes
directions: Beat egg with sugar.
Add flour, baking powder and bananas. Mix together with a fork.
Drop a tablespoonful at a time into a hot buttered frying pan.
Turn when bubbles appear.
They cook quickly; watch for burning and add more butter as needed.

title: apple butter
directions: Peel apples and slice into pan (I use Dutch oven).
Cover with 2 cups sugar.
Repeat until you have used 6 1/2 cups of sugar. Cover with foil; let set overnight.

title: quick casserole
directions: Combine all but cheese, pour in casserole.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: 7 in 1 dinner
directions: Mix tomato soup with juice from drained peas.
Pour over casserole and bake approximately 45 minutes at 375°.

title: mac and stuff
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner as directed on package. Meanwhile, bring water, peas or corn, hot dogs and margarine to boil in large saucepan.
Stir in stuffing mix; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir stuffing mixture into macaroni and cheese dinner.
Serve immediately.
tags: Stove Top chicken flavor stuffing mix

title: banana pops
directions: You will need 6 short, thick straws.

title: tofu
directions: Soak the soy beans for 10 hours.
Rinse and drain.
Heat 7 1/2 cups water on stove.
While the water is heating, take about 1/2 the soy beans, put them in a blender with about 2 cups water. Blend 2 to 3 minutes until ground very fine.
Add to the heating water.
Do the same with the other portion of soy beans.
Continue heating pot on high, stirring frequently.
You are watching for a sudden rise in the mixture level.
When this happens, immediately remove from heat.
Pour into a colander that has been lined with a cheesecloth.
The colander should be over a bowl to catch the liquid.
Rinse out the pot and put it back on the stove.
Twist the ends of the cheesecloth closed.
With a glass jar or potato masher, press against the mass to force out the liquid.
When this is done, open the cheesecloth.
Add about a cup of cold water to the soy bean puree; mash again.
Discard.
Keep the juice; pour it back into the pot.
Bring to a boil.
Add a cup of water to solidifier. Stir the soy milk vigorously 5 to 6 times and pour 1/3 of the solidifier in while stirring.
Take spoon out of mix; wait until there is no turbulence.
Sprinkle another 1/3 on surface.
Cover pot; wait 3 minutes and sprinkle rest on top.
Very slowly stir upper 1/2 inch layer until you see definite "curds and whey".
With a soup ladle, gently press into mix; allow whey to seep in and dispose of as much as you can get to.

title: baked bacon-grits and eggs
directions: Heat oven to
