Prepare grits according to package directions.
Stir in 2 tablespoons butter and the bacon.
Pour grits
mixture into ungreased 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Make 6 depressions
with
back of spoon about 2 inches apart in grits mixture.
Carefully
break one egg into each depression.
Melt remaining
butter;	pour
over eggs.
Sprinkle with pepper, if desired.
Bake,
uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes or until eggs are desired
doneness.	Garnish
with parsley.	Serve hot.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: 1000 island dressing for a crowd
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, pickle relish and catsup together. Mix water, lemon juice and spices in a small container.
Add to main batch.
Mix well.
Keep under refrigeration.

title: whole wheat yogurt muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and oats. Make a well in the center. Combine egg, oil, vanilla, milk and yogurt; add all at once to flour mixture. Stir just until moistened.
Lightly grease muffin pan; do not use paper cups. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden. Makes 8 to 10 muffins.

title: oreo cookie freeze
directions: Mix crushed Oreos and 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and place in freezer.
Spread softened ice cream over Oreo crust.
Place back in freezer.
Melt chocolate, 6 tablespoons margarine, sugar, milk and vanilla over low heat. Cool chocolate mixture.
Spread chocolate mixture over ice cream. Top with Cool Whip and pecans.
Place
in freezer.

title: new orleans spaghetti
directions: Brown first 6 ingredients in 1 tablespoon shortening.
Add soups and cook 15 minutes.
Add Velveeta and cook 15 minutes, stir frequently.
Add mushroom pieces.
Pour this sauce over spaghetti which has been cooked according to directions on package and well drained.
Mix sauce well with spaghetti.
Serves 10 to 12; takes 45 minutes to prepare.

title: curry-shrimp creole
directions: Saute onions, green pepper, celery and garlic in oil until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, parsley, catsup, lemon juice, salt, hot sauce, curry powder and thyme.
Bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes, or until shrimp turn pink.
Serve over hot cooked rice. Serves 4.

title: onion casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread into 2 layers the thinly sliced onions in rings. Sprinkle on Cheddar cheese and half the bag of potato chips.

title: homemade mints
directions: Knead the cream cheese, flavoring and sugar together.
Add coloring if desired (if you add coloring, you may need a little more 10x sugar).
Roll into balls and roll in granulated sugar. Press into molds.

title: apple cake #2
directions: In a large bowl, combine dry ingredients, apples and nuts. Add vanilla, eggs and oil.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased, floured tube pan at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: chocolate-peanut butter no-bake cookies
directions: Put sugar, cocoa and milk in large saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes.
Take off heat and add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Will be set when cool.

title: broccoli slaw
directions: * Use as much as you like.

title: **cookie theadora
directions: Cream shortening, add sugar gradually.
Add well beaten egg. Add flour, salt and baking powder which has been sifted together alternately with milk and vanilla.
Roll thin, cut and bake in moderate oven.

title: cucumber slaw
directions: Pare cucumbers and slice into a bowl.
Put in salt.
Set aside for 5 minutes.
Pour off the liquid.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar, sliced onions, 2 tablespoons vinegar and serve.
Mayonnaise may be added if you prefer it so.

title: easy pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat margarine in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan in oven until melted.
Sprinkle brown sugar over margarine.
Arrange pineapple on top.
Decorate with walnut halves and cherries. Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour batter into pan. Bake until cake springs back when touched lightly in center 45 to 55 minutes.
Immediately invert pan on heat proof serving plate.

title: joyce's maids of honor
directions: Roll out the pastry thinly and cut in rounds.
Line 16 to 18 patty tins.
Place a little jam in each.
Cream margarine and sugar; fold in beaten egg and flour.
Place small spoonfuls in each pastry case.
Bake in oven at 200°C or 400°F for about 15 minutes.

title: mid-eastern lentil soup
directions: Saute onion, celery and garlic in oil 2 to 3 minutes over medium heat.
Rinse lentils and add to pan along with chicken stock. Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Add carrot, apple, cumin and coriander.
Simmer until tender.
Add parsley and salt to taste. Garnish with croutons.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cut ham into pieces.
Chop green onions up (stems and all). Mix cream cheese, ham and onions, then form into round ball.
Take rest of ham and stick on side of ball.

title: double-strawberry cheesecake
directions: Reserve 1 cup dry cake mix.
In large mixing bowl, combine remaining cake mix, 1 egg and oil.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Press mix evenly on bottom and up 3/4 of the side of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In same bowl, blend the cream cheese and sugar.
Add 3 eggs and reserved cake mix.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
At low speed, add milk, lemon juice and food color.
Mix until smooth. Pour into crust and bake at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes, until center is firm.
Chill.
Spread topping before serving.

title: foolproof fudge
directions: Melt chocolate and milk in microwave until chocolate is just melted.
Stir in remaining ingredients and pour into a wax paper lined 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.

title: double chocolate cheesecake
directions: For crust, stir together crushed wafers and butter.
Press mix evenly over the bottom and 1 3/4 inches up sides of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Place the pan in a shallow baking pan.

title: breakfast souffle with sausage
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and salt; mix well.
Stir in bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Refrigerate overnight, covered.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10.
Great for a brunch or Christmas morning.

title: marinated steaks
directions: Combine all ingredients in Ziploc bag.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Barbecue, panfry or broil, using marinade as a baste.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash and soak beans overnight.
Boil meat with vegetables in the water until very tender; remove.
Add beans and cook until all to pieces.
Put through a strainer to remove skins.
Cut meat into tiny pieces.
Add to bean pulp.
Put in hot milk and seasoning. Serve piping hot.
Vegetables are used for seasoning.
Any dry beans or peas may be used.
One can of tomatoes may also be used.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Mix vinegar, red food coloring and cocoa.
Pour into mixture.
Blend.
Alternate flour and buttermilk when adding to mixture.
Add soda, salt and vanilla.
Bake in three 8-inch well-greased pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with icing.

title: frozen daiquiri
directions: Mix and freeze approximately 5 hours.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cut up chicken and wash.
Place in large kettle with cut up onion, celery and seasonings.
Cover with water and cook on medium heat until tender, about 1 hour.
Cool chicken.
Broth can be used for soup.
Cut up chicken, celery, eggs and relish.
Mix and add mayonnaise.
Will not need more seasoning, unless desired.

title: chili dip
directions: Add all ingredients to crock-pot and heat.
Serve with corn chips.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Roll beef into 1 to 2-inch balls. Bake at 350° until brown, about 20 to 30 minutes. You can fry them, but it takes longer. Add jelly and chili sauce to crock-pot or large pan. Add meatballs and allow to get hot. Be careful because the meatballs will get hard. Reduce heat and simmer.

title: golden biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour. Stir in milk. Mix and round dough on floured board. Knead.
Roll dough 1/2 to 1/4-inches thick. Cut for biscuits. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put onion soup in buttered pan, rice on top, 1 can cream of chicken soup, 1 can broth and drained peas.
Lay chicken on top. Put remainder of cans on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana pudding
directions: In medium saucepan, mix sugar and flour; beat in eggs and milk.
Cook until thick on medium heat.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Put layer of cookies in 2-quart dish, cut bananas on cookies, then layer of pudding. Continue alternating layers until all is used.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Put cake mix, oil, eggs and oranges in large bowl and beat for 3 minutes. Pour in 3 greased and floured 8 inch round cake pans. Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30
minutes. Let Cool.

title: christmas drop cookies
directions: Combine dates, nuts and cherries; mix in sugar and vanilla. Add egg whites to fruit mixture alternately with flour.
(If mixture is dry, add a little cherry juice.) Drop on cookie sheet; top with cherries and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cover potatoes with water; cook 30 minutes, until tender.
In a large bowl with 1 tablespoon butter mash potatoes.
Add 2/3 cup brown sugar and next 8 ingredients.
Pour into a greased 2-quart dish.
In separate bowl mix flour, 3 tablespoons brown sugar, 3 tablespoons butter and chopped pecans.
Spread on top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 10 people.

title: easy cocoa fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and butter in microwave-safe bowl and microwave on High until butter is melted, about 2 to 3 minutes. Stir until smooth.
Blend in vanilla and nuts.
Spread into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Serve.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Different flavors of Kool-Aid may be used to compliment color scheme.
Yields 50 servings.

title: butter pecan bread
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix, eggs and oil together thoroughly. Add hot water and poppy seed.
Blend well.
Bake in 3 small greased loaf pans at 350° until tests done.
Serve with cream cheese.

title: joyce's apple bread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour in greased loaf pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Blend apples and cranberries together.
Dissolve jello and sugar in hot water.
Add to mixture and chill.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Shake the chicken in a mixture of the flour, paprika, salt and pepper.
Melt the oleo in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Assemble chicken, skin side down.
Bake for 45 minutes. Turn; bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: stew-da-loo
directions: Wine may be eliminated; increase water to 4 cups.

title: knox blocks(finger jello)
directions: Mix Jell-O together.
Add water and bring to a boil.
Add Knox gelatine.
Stir until dissolved.
Add whipping cream.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Cut into squares.
Eat with fingers.

title: mushroom cress salad
directions: In salad bowl, mix well the oil, vinegar, salt and pepper. Add watercress and mushrooms.
Toss lightly to coat.
If desired, stand some mushroom slices on end around rim of bowl to create scalloped garnish.
Serve at once.

title: apple dumplin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cut apple in 8 slices. Put in cool water. Open crescent rolls, break apart and on wax paper roll apple. Seal. Put in baking dish. Boil sugar, water and butter. Pour over dumpling; sprinkle cinnamon. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: baked sausage and peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Oil roasting pan, to just cover bottom. Brown sausage in oven.
Wash and slice into wedges, onions, peppers and potatoes.
When sausage is brown, add these.
Cook for about 1 hour or until peppers, onions and potatoes are tender and golden brown.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: sweet and sour ribs
directions: Place ribs in baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°. Combine sugar and cornstarch in saucepan; stir in ketchup, water and vinegar.
Bring to a boil; cook until thick and clear.
Remove ribs from pan; discard fat.
Place ribs back into pan.
Pour 1 1/2 cups of sauce over ribs.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Turn oven off. Pour rest of sauce over ribs.
Let ribs stand 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from oven and serve.

title: tom's herb-baked fish (or chicken) and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In an 8 x 12 dish, combine bouillon, rice and seasonings.
Bake, covered, for 10 minutes.
Top with broccoli, 1/2 can onions and Parmesan cheese.
Place fillets in dish; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, covered, for 20 to 25 minutes. If using chicken, bake for about 40 to 45 minutes.
Stir rice. Top with Cheddar cheese and rest of onion.
Bake, uncovered, 3 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: busy day beef pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and potatoes.
Line the bottom and sides of 9-inch pie dish with mixture.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and lay slices of cheese over meat.
Pile mashed potatoes on top and place remaining cheese slices over potatoes.
Bake 5 minutes or until cheese melts. Yields 6 servings.

title: pretzel pandemonium
directions: Combine pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; cool.
Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and egg.
Mix well.
Fold in whipped cream. Spread in crust and chill.
Dissolve strawberry gelatin in boiling water; add strawberries.
Chill until partially set.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill until firm.

title: pork tenderloin with rosemary
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Rub tenderloins with salt and pepper and place in baking dish. Sprinkle with garlic and arrange onions around pork.
Melt 1 tablespoon margarine and combine with rosemary. Boil. Drizzle over pork and onions.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes until tender and cooked through (170°). Remove pork and onions from pan. Add water to pan and deglaze.
Stir in wine. Blend together flour and remaining margarine. Add to sauce and heat to simmer, stirring until sauce thickens.
Season to taste. Slice and serve with onions and sauce. Serves 8.

title: caramel flan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In heavy skillet over medium heat, cook sugar, stirring constantly until melted and caramel-colored.
Pour into ungreased 9-inch round or square baking pan, tilting to coat bottom completely.
In medium bowl, beat eggs.
Stir in water, sweetened condensed milk, vanilla and salt.
Pour over caramelized sugar; set pan in a larger pan (a broiler pan).
Fill larger pan with 1 inch of hot water.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool.
Chill.
Loosen side of flan with knife; invert onto serving plate with rim.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: lemon supreme cake with glaze
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, water and Jell-O for 2 minutes. Add oil and mix until well blended.

Pour into a 13 x 9 pan, sprayed with Pam or greased with Crisco and flour. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. While cake bakes, make glaze with powdered sugar and lemon juice. When cake is done, use a fork to punch holes in top of cake. Pour glaze over cake while warm or even straight from the oven. Spread glaze close to edges.

title: ham and cheese biscuits
directions: Partially freeze rolls, then cut them in half.
Melt margarine. Add rest of ingredients.
Saute on low heat for 5 minutes.
Spread on both sides of rolls.
Place slices of ham and cheese on rolls. Wrap in foil and heat for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: bernice's chicken supreme
directions: Cook chicken in salted water.
Cool, debone and cut in bite size pieces.
Mix chicken, noodles, pimento, water chestnuts, celery and onions.
Place in baking dish.
Pour broth on top. Place chips and almonds on top of this and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: nellie's strawberry pie
directions: Combine Water, Sugar and Cornstarch into a saucepan.
Cook until thick and clear.
Remove from heat then add Strawberry Gelatin to saucepan.

title: sweet and sour salad dressing
directions: Mix in a shaker jar and shake well before using.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well; press into crock-pot. Top with extra ketchup. Cover and cook on low 8 to 10 hours or high 4 to 6 hours or cook in oven at 350° for 1 hour or until brown on top.

title: "really good" candied baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight per package directions.
In same water, bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, 1 hour.
Drain and transfer to baking dish.
Saute bacon (I chop mine into bite-size pieces before cooking).
Remove with slotted spoon.
Add to beans. Saute onion in bacon drippings until tender.
Drain and add to beans.
Add remaining ingredients and stir gently.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
This is perfect for a buffet, as it retains its good flavor when cooled.
This can be made a day or two in advance and refrigerated.
Allow an extra 15 minutes cooking time.

title: italian tortellini salad
directions: Cook tortellini according to package directions.
Drain in a colander.
Chill by either refrigerating or placing the colander in a large bowl of ice water for 5 minutes.
Drain well.

title: french apple bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add Eagle Brand milk, apples, water, margarine, cinnamon and vanilla.
Stir in bread and raisins, completely moistening the bread.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Prepare cake as package directs. Stir in 1/2 package of coconut. Pour into 9 x 13 greased pan. Bake as package directs. When done, prick holes in cake with a fork over entire cake to bottom while hot. Stir cream of coconut and pour over entire cake. When cool, spread with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with rest of coconut. Store in refrigerator.

title: sweet surprise chocolate sack
directions: Thaw pastry 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 425°.
On a floured board, roll pastry sheet to a 14-inch square.
In center of square, place chocolate, walnuts and butter.
Pull pastry edges together; twist and turn.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake 20 minutes.
Let stand at least 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: amaretto cookies
directions: Cut each slice of cookie mix in 4 pieces.
Place in small cupcake tin.
Make thumbprint.
Bake until done.
Mix pudding with milk and Amaretto.
Fill cookie cups.
Let cool.
Top with whipped cream.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix jello with water until dissolved, then add all other ingredients.
Let gel in 15 x 9-inch container.
Serves 15.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook fryer with celery and onion. Pull chicken from bone, cut in large pieces and place in a baking dish. Pour soup and chicken broth over the chicken. Mix together, flour, buttermilk, and margarine. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk pancake mix
directions: Sift 4 or 5 times.

title: black bottom cake
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients; add chocolate chips. Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Mix in wet ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Then drop tablespoonfuls of cream cheese mixture around over top of cake.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: biscuit fantans
directions: *May substitute 1 package dry onion soup mix for the sugar and cinnamon.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Place potatoes and onion in layers in bottom of greased baking dish.
Add meat, salt and pepper.
Pour soup over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: easy rhubarb jam
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar; let stand about 6 hours or overnight. In the morning, cook for 15 minutes (looks like sauce).
Add the packages of jello; mix well.
Pour into hot jars (sterilized) and seal with paraffin or lids.
May also freeze.

title: fresh garden vegetables
directions: In a large skillet, melt butter and lightly brown uncooked noodles, stirring frequently.
Add broth, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; add vegetables.
Cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until vegetables and noodles are tender.
Pour into serving bowl.
Sprinkle individual servings with Mozzarella cheese.

title: turtles(candy)
directions: Melt caramels in milk in double boiler.
Add pecans; mix well. Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet; cool.
Mix Hershey bar and paraffin in saucepan until melted.
Shape caramel into balls and dip into chocolate, then place on waxed paper to harden.

title: low-sugar peach cobbler
directions: Bring peaches, water and nutmeg to boil.
Pour 1/3 into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine baking mix, sugar and milk; stir to form a dough.
Turn out onto floured surface, roll out 1/8-inch thick and cut in 6 strips.
Place 3 strips evenly over peaches. Add remaining peaches, cover with 3 strips of dough.
Pour juice over dough and dot with margarine.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes, until brown and bubbly.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with packets of sugar substitute.

title: fig preserves
directions: First wash figs, discarding broken ones.
In a large pot, place equal weights of figs and sugar; add a little water. Simmer, lightly covered, until figs are opaque.
Turn off heat, add 1 sliced lemon and let sit in pot for about 4 hours to make figs plump.
Reheat and pour into sterilized jars.
Cool on rack. Jar tops will make popping sound as they seal.

title: chicken wings
directions: Cut chicken wings at joints, discarding tips.
Mix all other ingredients in bottom of roaster pan.
(Do not cut up garlic.) Add prepared wings and baste.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, basting at least twice.
Great finger food or serve with rice and vegetables for main meal.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, mace, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt in a bowl.
Add milk and whip in beaten eggs.
Put in unbaked pie crust and bake for one hour at 350°.

title: john's portuguese bean soup
directions: In a 5-quart pan, put ham hocks or bones.
Cover with water. Boil with garlic, onion, cilantro and tomatoes.
Simmer until meat comes off the bones.
Remove bones.
Cut up meat and return to pan.
Add sausage, potatoes and carrots.
Simmer until potatoes and carrots are starting to soften.
Add macaroni and cabbage. Cook until tender.
Add salt to taste.

title: texas ranger cookies
directions: Cream together oleo, sugars, eggs, milk and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Mix together oats, coconut and corn flakes.
Add to creamed mixture.
Form into balls.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until set.

title: ground beef and stuffing casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef with onion in medium skillet; drain fat.
Prepare stuffing according to directions on box.
In large bowl, mix the cans of corn, sugar and nutmeg.
Add ground beef and onion mixture and the stuffing to the corn mixture; mix well.
Pour mixture into a 2-quart glass baking dish; cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, or until heated.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix well; top with bacon strips.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage fine.
Chop onion and green pepper.
Mix with salt in a deep bowl.
Pour boiling water over this.
Cover and let stand for 1 hour.

title: rice milk
directions: Put all ingredients into blender.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into container and add enough water to make a total of 6 cups. Stir well when using as it will settle.

title: summer lasagna
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan, drain fat; reserve 2 tablespoons. Saute onions and zucchini in bacon fat.
Add water; cover skillet and simmer 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Crumble bacon; add to lasagna mixture.
Serves six.

title: merry christmas cake
directions: Before you start, sample the sherry to check for quality. Select a large mixing bowl, measuring cup, etc.
Check the sherry again, as it must be right.
Pour 1 level cup into glass and drink fast as you can.
Repeat.
With an electric mixer, beat 1 cup butter in large fluffy bowl.
Add 1 teaspoon thugar and meat again.

title: colorado green chili(chile verde con puerco)
directions: Cut meat into bite sized pieces.
Brown meat with a little flour in small amount of corn oil.
When brown, add the remainder of the flour and oil and stir until flour and oil are completely mixed.
Chop chilies into small pieces.
Put pork, chilies, garlic, tomatoes and some water into a large pot or pressure cooker.
Add water stirring until consistency of gravy is reached.
Add salt and cumin.
Simmer until tender and flavors blend, about 1 hour.
Stir when finished.
Add more water if needed, or simmer with cover off if too thin, until proper consistency is reached.
Pour over burritos or use as enchilada sauce.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening to dry ingredients until crumbly.
Add buttermilk, one cup at a time; mix well.
Place dough on floured board and knead dough until it is workable.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick and cut biscuits.
Bake on greased cookie sheets at 450° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: 7 layer mexican dip
directions: In 8 x 13-inch glass pan, spread bean dip on bottom.
Next, mix taco seasoning, sour cream and mayo; spread over bean dip. Next, spoon guacamole over sour cream layer.
Next, layer onion, tomato and cheese.
Place olives on top of cheese.
Last, pour salsa over top.

title: "variety" cookies
directions: This is a large batch which can be cut in half.

title: burger bundles
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package directions.
Mix beef with evaporated milk.
Divide meat into 5 patties.
On wax paper, flatten patties to form 6-inch circles.
Spoon 1/4 cup stuffing in center of each patty.
Draw edges over stuffing and seal.
Place in 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Combine mushroom soup, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce and heat until bubbly.
Pour over meat. Bake, uncovered, in a medium oven at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Makes 5 servings.
May garnish with parsley.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Drain clams and reserve liquid and set aside.
Cook onion and bacon in a Dutch oven until bacon is browned.
Stir in clam liquid, potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup milk and add to potato mixture.
Add butter, clams and remaining 3 3/4 cups milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened. Do not boil.
Yields about 8 cups.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Boil noodles. Cut cucumber and tomato into small pieces. Mix with noodles. Add Italian dressing, then Catalina. Mix together well and refrigerate.

title: school days johnnycake
directions: Mix eggs with
buttermilk
and molasses in mixing bowl. Add all other
ingredients;
mix well.	Pour into 11 x 15-inch baking pan.
Bake at
for 20 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cut into large squares.
Yields 24 squares.

title: polynesian salad
directions: Mix together and store covered in refrigerator.
Keeps several days.

title: mountain dew cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, oil and Mountain Dew beverage for 2 minutes with mixer.
Pour into 2 prepared pans.

title: best chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan or 2 round pans or a 12-cup Bundt cake pan.
Beat all ingredients in large bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 30 seconds.
Beat on high speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 3 minutes.
Pour into pan(s).
Bake rectangle 40 to 45 minutes, rounds 30 to 35 minutes and Bundt cake 50 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool Bundt cake and layers 10 minutes.
Cool rectangle on wire rack.
Invert onto wire rack and cool completely.
Frost with caramel frosting. Makes 16 servings.

title: cheese filled jumbo shells
directions: Cook jumbo shells according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water.
Combine cheeses, eggs, broccoli, parsley, oregano, salt and pepper.
Fill each shell with about 2 tablespoons cheese mixture. Spread a thin layer of sauce on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Place shells, open side down, in single layer in pan.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese if desired.
Cover with foil; bake at 350° about 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Fills about 36 shells.
Yields ten to twelve servings.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Grind cukes and onions in meat grinder, then sprinkle with the salt.
Let stand 2 hours, then drain.
Heat 1 quart vinegar.
Mix the flour, sugar, turmeric, celery seed and mustard seed with 1/2 cup vinegar, then add to hot vinegar.
Cook slowly until thick, then add ground mixture.
Cook 10 minutes.
Makes about 8 pints.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Can top with crumbs.

title: butter dips
directions: Heat oven to 450° and melt butter in a 13 x 9 1/2-inch pan. Sift together dry ingredients.
Add milk and stir with fork until it clings; knead 10 times.
Roll out on floured surface until 1/2-inch thick in a rectangle.
Cut 16 strips approximately 4-inches long and 3/4-inch wide.
Roll in melted butter and arrange in pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Great with stews.

title: jean's death by chocolate
directions: *Or use 1/4 to 1/2 cup Kahlua or coffee liqueur.

title: danish cucumbers
directions: Cut cucumbers into paper thin slices.
In bowl, mix slices with 2 teaspoons salt.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour. Drain liquid from cucumbers.
Stir in vinegar, sugar, dill and pepper.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving. Serves 8.

title: asparagus with parmesan cheese
directions: In a tall, narrow saucepan, bring enough salted water to boil to reach just below the asparagus tips.
Clean the asparagus and tie it in bundles.
Add to the saucepan and cook just until crisp-tender.
Drain and transfer to a serving dish.

title: barbecue franks
directions: Cut wieners in 1-inch pieces.
Mix all remaining ingredients and pour over wieners.
Marinate overnight.
Cook over medium heat for 30 minutes or until wieners expand.
Serve hot.

title: never tell pie crust
directions: Mix together and roll out.

title: sticks and stones
directions: Pour over other ingredients.
Stir and bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: ajiaco de pollo bogotano(soup)
directions: Heat the butter in a heavy casserole and saute the chicken pieces with the onion until the chicken is golden.
Add the thinly sliced potatoes and the stock.
Cover and cook on a low heat for about 25 minutes.
Add the new potatoes and cook for about 20 minutes more or until chicken and new potatoes are tender.
Remove the chicken pieces and new potatoes and work the stock through a sieve.
Return stock to casserole.
Season to taste.
Add the chicken and potatoes, corn and capers.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add cream and cook just long enough to heat through.
Serve in deep soup plates with avocado sauce on the side.

title: nutty monkey bread
directions: Melt butter and 1 cup sugar; set aside.
Mix 1 cup sugar and cinnamon in large bowl.
Open 2 cans biscuits; cut each biscuit into quarters.
Toss cut biscuits into sugar and cinnamon mixture; coat well.
Toss sugar coated biscuits into well-greased tube pan. Pour 1/2 butter sugar mixture over biscuits; add chopped nuts. Cut remaining 2 cans of biscuits into quarters and repeat directions.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
After removing from oven, invert onto large plate.

title: grandma rose's hungarian lecho
directions: Finely chop pepper and onion and set aside.
Peel and chop potatoes into small cubes. Place butter in a large stew pot and lightly saute potatoes.
Add seasoning to taste, usually lightly covering potatoes will do.

Stir constantly. Add pepper and onion and continue to saute with potatoes. Stir. Slice sausage into thin slices and add to sauteed mixture. Stir. Add full jar of spaghetti sauce and completely blend mixture. Add water and mix until it is consistency of thick stew.
More seasoning may be added, if desired.
Let simmer on low heat for 15 to 25 minutes or until potatoes are soft. Serves 5 to 6 people.

title: filling for fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until thick.
Add strawberry jello, strawberry flavoring and food coloring.
Let cool.
Put fresh strawberries in cooked pie shell and pour filling over strawberries.
(Can smooth filling, a little, on pie shell before putting strawberries in shell.)

title: slippery dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll out thin between wax paper.

title: taco fried chicken
directions: In large bowl, combine taco mix, flour and salt.
In a small bowl, blend egg and milk.
Dip chicken in egg mixture, then in flour mixture.
Fry in hot shortening until chicken is thoroughly cooked.

title: double chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt and cocoa.
Set aside.
In a large bowl blend sugars.
Add butter and beat well.
Then add eggs and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients and chips and blend at low speed until combined.
Drop dough by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheets, 1/2-inch apart. Bake 21 to 23 minutes at 300°.
Transfer to a cookie rack.

title: chicken fettucini
directions: Cook fettucini noodles according to package directions and drain.
In medium skillet cook and stir chicken, mushrooms, celery and butter until celery is tender.
Add cream and heat; do not boil.
Toss with fettucini and remaining ingredients.
Serve immediately.
Reheat in microwave on Medium power.

title: noodles with chicken livers, sage and bacon
directions: Prepare noodles, according to directions.
In a large pot, bring 5 quarts salted water to a boil.
In frying pan, melt the butter over medium heat.
Add the bacon and sage and fry until they are both crisp, about 5 minutes.
Add the chicken livers and fry, stirring frequently for 3 minutes.
Season to taste.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar; add and mix together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir vigorously for 2 minutes, adding milk as you mix.
Add eggs and mix for one minute.
Add blueberries.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook ingredients until thick; let cool.
Put strawberries in baked pie shell.
Pour thickening over them.
Store in refrigerator.
Put Cool Whip on if you like.

title: ravioli and sauce
directions: Bring to a boil 4 quarts of water in a large pan.
Separate ravioli and slowly put them in boiling water.
Cook for 20 minutes or until tender.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, milk and cocoa; heat over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Add to the sugar mix, oatmeal, coconut, peanut butter, salt, vanilla and marshmallows.
Remove from heat. Stir to mix all thoroughly as marshmallows will melt.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Allow to cool.

title: macaroons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool before removing from cookie sheet. Yields 5 dozen.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients; put in hot greased skillet (cast iron). Bake at 350 degrees until brown or done.

title: easy pancakes
directions: Mix together.
Add milk, a small amount at a time, until the right consistency.
May use regular sweet milk.
Fry on lightly greased griddle.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: betty whetstone's caramel sweet potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and slice lengthwise.
Place in medium casserole. Sprinkle whole box of brown sugar over potatoes.
Then pour carton of whipping cream over sugar and potatoes.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: bubble bread
directions: When loaves are almost thawed, cut into 1/2 inch cubes.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan or Bundt pan.
Let thaw completely.
Mix the other ingredients together and pour over the bread cubes.
Let rise for 30 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fattigman
directions: Beat eggs and sugar well.
Mix all and put in refrigerator for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Dough will be sticky.
Using plenty of flour, so can roll out, cut with crimper, if you have one, and fry in deep fat.

title: spring vegetable soup(swedish cooking)
directions: Rinse the vegetables.
Cut into strips or dice.
Boil the vegetables in slightly salted water until barely tender, about 5 minutes (start with the vegetables which require the longest cooking time).
Mix the flour with 1/2 cup of milk.
Blend this thickening into the soup.
Boil for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add the rest of the milk and bring to a boil.
Beat the egg yolk and cream together and stir into the soup.
The soup must not boil after this.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: *Use 1/2 cup margarine and 1/2 cup vegetable oil for brownies.

title: ham and bean soup or ham and potato soup
directions: In large soup pot, add ham, cubed into 1/4 to 3/8-inch cubes, pepper, broth, celery, carrots, onion and beans (cubed potatoes if you are making potato soup), all cut into soup size chunks. Bring to a boil, then turn down to simmer while you thicken milk.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil the potatoes and carrots.
Bone cooked chicken and return to broth.
Add potatoes and carrots; season with salt and pepper to taste.
Thicken with cornstarch.
Cover top completely with biscuits.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: fruit topping for pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bananas.
Chill.
Add bananas just before serving.
Great over pound cake.

title: soft chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix Crisco, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix flour, salt and baking soda.
Add flour mixture to 1st mixture alternately with milk.
Batter will be real thick.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.

title: brown sauce
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour.
Cook and stir over low heat until browned.
Stir in soup.
Bring to a boil and cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes about 1 1/3 cups.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning together. Spread on flat large serving tray.
Top with lettuce and cheese (optional, diced onions and tomatoes).
Serve with nacho chips.

title: pumpkin butter pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, butter and eggs.
Mix well.
Add milk and then the honey or molasses.
Stir until well combined.
Last add spices and pour into pie shell.
Cook at 350° until the custard sets, about 65 minutes.

title: cinnamon butter
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer.
Store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Use on biscuits, pancakes, waffles, etc.

title: fruit cake
directions: Crush wafers.
Add chopped nuts, fruit and Eagle Brand milk and mix.
Pack lightly.
Wrap in wax paper and place in the vanilla wafer box and place in refrigerator.

title: meat loaf wellington
directions: Combine 1/4 cup gravy with ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion, salt and pepper, mix thoroughly. Shape firmly into loaf. Place in shallow baking dish. Bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes. Separate rolls, place crosswise over top and down sides of meat loaf, overlapping slightly. Bake 15 minutes more. Meanwhile, heat remaining gravy. Serve.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream shortening with sugar.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla. Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to sugar mixture alternating with milk.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: shrimp and rice
directions: In a large skillet, melt 1/4 stick butter, onion and celery. Cook until tender (do not brown). Add shrimp and parsley. Cook for 10 minutes over medium heat. Add rice and boiling water. Cook for 1 hour over low heat until rice is tender. Before serving, add 1/2 stick melted butter on top of rice.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into ball and cover with chopped pecans.
Chill.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine milk, mushroom soup and pepper.
Pour over beans.
Add 1/2 can onions.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Serve 6.

title: breakfast potato pancakes
directions: Pat potatoes dry between
paper
towels.
Put
eggs
in blender and blend for a
few
seconds, then add butter, flour, salt and milk.
Add potatoes
and
puree
smooth.
Pour onto a greased hot skillet or griddle and cook for about 2 minutes on each side.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in 9 x 13-inch dish, chill 12 hours.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs before baking.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 12.

title: pizza butter
directions: Mix together tomato paste, butter, oregano, sugar and garlic. Spread onto English muffin.
Apply Mozzarella cheese to your liking.
Cook in a 375° oven for about 15 minutes or until cheese is all melted.

title: wasp nest cake
directions: Set oven temperature to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan or spray with Baker's Joy.
Mix pudding and milk in saucepan. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and immediately add the dry cake mix.
Mix thoroughly and add nuts.
Spread in cake pan. Sprinkle butterscotch morsels over top and bake for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal chippers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
In large mixer bowl, beat butter, brown sugar, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually beat in flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate morsels, oats and nuts.

title: baked mexican corn
directions: Mix all together and pour into 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: scrumptious double chocolate brownies
directions: In a large bowl, combine cocoa and baking soda.
Blend in 1/3 cup melted butter.
Add boiling water.
Stir until well blended. Stir in sugar, eggs and remaining butter.
Add flour, vanilla and salt.
Stir in nuts and chocolate pieces.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool.
Makes 3 dozen. Can be iced or powdered.

title: one pot stroganoff
directions: Saute beef and onion in Dutch oven until brown.
Pour off excess fat.
Stir in tomato juice, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil.
Add noodles, a few at a time, so mixture continues to boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until noodles are tender.
Stir in sour cream thoroughly, but do not boil.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: beer bread
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Divide dough into 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Bread rises as it bakes.)

title: pepperoni cheese pie
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Cut half of pepperoni slices into fourths.
Toss onion, green pepper, pepperoni and cheese with flour.
Add milk, eggs and seasonings. Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Gently place remaining pepperoni slices around edge of pie.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°, until set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs in large mixer bowl; beat well. Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add to egg mixture; beat well.
Stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Fold in apples.
Pour into greased and waxed paper-lined 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan for several minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Combine confectioners sugar with enough water to make thin glaze.
Stir in remaining 2 teaspoons vanilla.
Drizzle over cooled cake.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: sauerkraut
directions: *This makes 1 quart jar.

title: oyster mosca
directions: Rinse and drain oysters in colander. Spray a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish with Pam.
Sprinkle 1 cup Italian bread crumbs on the bottom of the baking dish.
Evenly place drained oysters on top of the bread crumbs.
Sprinkle pressed garlic on top of the oysters. Layer Parmesan cheese and last cup of Italian bread crumbs evenly on oysters.
Drizzle melted butter evenly over bread crumbs. Sprinkle olive oil with butter.
Sprinkle Tony Chachere seasoning last.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: no bake "special k" cookies
directions: Cook sugar and syrup in a large saucepan and bring to a good boil.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and peanut butter.
Pour over cereal and mix well.
Drop by heaping tablespoon onto waxed paper. Butter hands; you may need to handle cookies to form balls. Quick and easy.
A kid pleaser from 2 to 82.

title: layered casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, cut up fine (not chopped) and salt.
Open and combine peas and corn.

title: roast venison
directions: Place roast in 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Pour over the soup and water.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 2 to 3 hours or until tender.

title: holiday breakfast casserole
directions: Combine eggs and milk in bowl and beat well.
Mix crumbled sausage with eggs and add rest of ingredients, adding bread last. Mix well.
Pour into greased 12 x 9-inch baking pan and cover with aluminum foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes or until set.
If using glass pan, cut down to 325°.

title: peach betty
directions: In a 1-quart casserole, combine fruit, lemon peel, cinnamon and nutmeg.
In a saucepan, melt oleo.
Stir in cracker crumbs. Sprinkle over peaches.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until browned.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crackers and margarine.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch greased baking dish.

title: fruit salad
directions: Whip cream cheese and whipping cream.
Beat it up real good and pour it over the salad.
Stir real good.
Put marshmallows on top.

title: carolina pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and Crisco. Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir baking powder and salt into flour.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk. Add vanilla and lemon flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven. Turn oven to 300° and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop apples, oranges and cranberries in blender or mini chopper. Mix all together and chill.

title: crabby mushrooms
directions: Rinse and drain crabmeat.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Toss crabmeat with lemon juice in medium bowl.
Add rest of ingredients, except cheese and mushrooms, and mix well.
Fill mushroom caps with mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Rinse baking sheet lightly with water; shake off excess.
Arrange mushrooms on sheet.
Cover with foil and bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Remove foil and continue baking until tips are golden, about 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: orange glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water 20 to 25 minutes.
Make sure they are tender.
Let cool to touch.
Peel and quarter.
Arrange in lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer all ingredients.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and dressing together; put on top of salad, seal to edges.
Sprinkle additional cheese on top for garnish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix together before serving.

title: ski trail cheese quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Toss cheese with flour and seasonings. Combine bacon, eggs, tomato sauce, milk and onion, mixing until well blended.
Add cheese mixture; mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: coconut frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan and boil until thickened. Spread on cooled cake.

title: arabian chicken salad(makes large amount - serves 4 to 6)
directions: Cut chicken in small pieces.
Combine with rice and shrimp in a large bowl that has been rubbed with garlic clove.
Add cucumber and onion.
Combine mayonnaise, French dressing and chili sauce. Combine with other ingredients.
Chill in garlic rubbed bowl.
Add lettuce leaves around top and decorate with tomato wedges just before serving.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta; rinse in cold water and drain. Dice and add remaining ingredients. Toss with dressing and chill well.

title: cabbage and pepperoni
directions: Break cabbage down and rinse.
Place in a large pot with about 2 cups water.
Cover and place on very low flame.
Steam about 1 hour.
Drain and add all other ingredients.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: angel kisses
directions: Bring butter, sugar and dates to a boil over medium-low heat. Remove from heat and add coconut and Rice Krispies.
Mix well. Form into balls and roll in powdered sugar.

title: peanut butter snack
directions: Blend cheese with peanut butter and honey.
Form into a log. Cover and refrigerate until stiff, about 1 hour.
Roll in crushed nuts.
Spread on crackers or use in sandwiches.
Makes 1 log.

title: sugar and spice pecans
directions: Beat
egg white (at room temperature) until stiff peaks form; fold
in
butter.
Add
pecans,
tossing gently to coat well. Combine sugar, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and allspice in a small bowl.
Sprinkle
tablespoons
sugar
mixture
on
an ungreased baking sheet.
Dredge pecans, 1/4 cup at a time, in remaining sugar
mixture.
Spread pecans
on baking sheet and sprinkle
with any remaining sugar mixture.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes, stirring after 10 minutes.
Separate pecans with a fork.
Let cool.
Store
in an airtight container.
Yield:
2 cups.

title: cheese and rice omelette(italian style)
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Heat in heavy saute pan and pour in eggs.
Saute as you would an omelet. Mix together the cheese, ham and rice.
When the omelette is set but still moist, spread the rice mixture down the middle.
Fold omelette over with a spatula.
Continue cooking over low heat until omelette and rice are heated through.
Serves 4.

title: orange fluff
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix 1/2 cup juice with jello.
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and oil.
Sift dry ingredients and add a little at a time to sugar mixture, alternating with nuts and apples.
Pour into greased stem or Bundt pan.
Sprinkle the butterscotch chips over the top and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken dijon
directions: Stir together the butter, wine and mustard.
Coat both sides of chicken.
Mix bread crumbs and Parmesan; dredge chicken pieces in it.
Place in baking pan, sprayed with vegetable coating.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 20 minutes until meat tests done and crumb crust is golden brown.

title: chocolate delite
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts and press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 375° until cool.
Blend cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip and spread on crust.
Add chocolate pudding and milk.
Mix and spread over crust, then cover with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Mix other ingredients. Bake in sheet cake pan at 350°
until done.
Test with toothpick.

title: pudding delight(a.k.a. "sex in a pan")
directions: Combine flour, 1 cup pecans, butter and press into 9 x 13 inch greased glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let cool.
Beat cream cheese and sugar in one medium bowl.
Fold in 1/2 of
large carton of Cool Whip.
In another large mixing bowl, beat milk, and both puddings until thick.
Place cream cheese mixture on cool crust, then pudding mixture on top of cream cheese and top with remaining Cool Whip.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: seafood pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Lightly oil a 12-inch pizza pan. Sprinkle with cornmeal.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion and garlic; cook 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes, parsley, red pepper and salt.
Cook 10 minutes.
Press dough in pan.
Cover with sauce.
Top with shrimp and clams; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until crust is golden brown, about 20 minutes.

title: fettuccine primavera with smoked salmon
directions: Heat olive oil; add garlic, snow peas and sweet pepper and cook for 1 minute. Add the cream and bring to a boil. In a separate saucepan, cook the pasta. Add pasta to cream sauce and gently combine with salmon, cheese and parsley. Serve warm.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash beans well, then drain.
In a 6 quart pot, put beans and cover 3 inches with water.
Allow beans to soak for several hours, if possible.
Chop all vegetables to a fine consistency.
After soaking, heat beans on high until boiling.
Take out 1/2 of beans and reserve.
Add onions, bell pepper, celery, garlic and parsley. Stir well.

Bring to a hard boil, reduce heat to maintain boil. Be sure to stir often and add water to maintain level as needed. Add salt, black pepper, chili powder, reserved beans and pickled pork or chunk ham and simmer boil for 2 hours.
Serve over rice. For spicier fare, add Louisiana pepper sauce to taste.

title: carob-banana-peanut butter shake
directions: Blend all ingredients (except ice cubes) in a blender.
With blender running on high, drop 4 ice cubes, one at a time, through the hole in the lid of the blender.
Blend until ice is an integral part of the drink.
Serve immediately.
Makes 1 serving.

title: cherry whip pie
directions: Beat egg whites stiff with sugar.
Add cream of tartar to hold firm.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Add broken soda crackers.
Mix well and bake in 9 x 13-inch pan 30 minutes at 350°.
Set aside to cool at room temperature.
Add Cool Whip on top of crust, then top with cherry pie filling and chill 2 or 3 hours.

title: less sugar-less fat banana bread
directions: Cream oleo and sugar. Add eggs, applesauce and mashed bananas. Beat well. Add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into well-greased pan. Bake, starting in cold oven, at 325° for 1 hour.

title: mayonnaise rolls
directions: Mix
together
and pour into muffin tins.
Bake at 400° until golden
brown.
Makes
muffins or 6 large, using the large, Texas-style muffin pan.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts.
Using electric mixer, beat until smooth and fluffy.
Blend nuts in and spread frosting on cooled cake.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In greased baking dish, put 1 layer of chopped cabbage, 1 layer of uncooked sausage, pinched into small pieces and 1 layer of potatoes.
Continue to layer over again. Bake covered for 50 minutes.
Top with Cheddar cheese and cook 5 minutes longer or until cheese melts.

title: liz's hash browns
directions: Thaw potatoes slightly.
In a large bowl, mix hash browns, Cheddar cheese, cream of celery soup, chopped onion and sour cream.
Spread in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with cornflake crumbs and drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix liquid ingredients.
Set aside.
Mix dry ingredients and add to liquid. Mix well.
Bake 350° for one hour.

title: deep south zucchini
directions: Cook bacon until very crisp; crumble and reserve.
Saute onion in 1 tablespoon bacon grease until golden; then add all the other ingredients except cheese.
Mix and pour mixture into a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle the top with Parmesan cheese and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until hot and cheese is melted.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: bacon-cheese potato slices
directions: Scrub potatoes and trim ends.
Cut into 3/8-inch slices. Evenly arrange on a microwave-safe 12-inch plate, putting small slices in center.
Microwave (High) for 7 to 10 minutes, giving the dish 1/2 turn after four minutes.
Sprinkle potato slices with bacon bits, olives and cheese.
Microwave (Medium) for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes (uncovered) or until cheese just begins to melt.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Combine cheese, crab or shrimp, green pepper, stuffed green olives, tomato soup, Worcestershire sauce, chili sauce and garlic salt.
Butter buns.
Spread mixture inside bun.
Wrap individually in foil and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hamburger patties with mushroom gravy
directions: Form ground beef into patties.
Cook and drain patties.
Heat soup, milk and pepper together.
Place patties back into gravy mixture; cook on low heat.
Turn over patties and heat.
Serve with white rice.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots in water until done.
Place carrots, onion and pepper in a casserole in layers.
Mix and cook the remaining ingredients to a boil, stirring well.
Pour over carrots. Refrigerate.
Keeps up to 4 weeks in refrigerator.

title: holiday chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken breasts in a saucepan. Bring to a boil and cook 5 minuets.
Arrange chicken breasts in a shallow baking pan.
Pour date sauce over chicken.
Bake in a preheated 350°
oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes, basting with sauce occasionally.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pea soup
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook over the stove until done.

title: no cook barbecue sauce
directions: For spicy barbecue sauce, omit Worcestershire, mustard and ginger.
Add:

title: green bean casserole
directions: In medium bowl, combine beans, milk, soup, black pepper and 1/2 can onion rings.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes. Top with remaining onion rings and bake, uncovered, 5 minutes or until onions are brown.

title: amish cookies
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, eggs and milk until well blended.
Stir in flour, baking powder, salt and spices.
Fold in blueberries. Spread batter into a greased 9-inch square pan.

title: dirty rice
directions: Cook first 9 ingredients in cooking oil until brown, then add water and roux. Simmer gently until done (30 minutes). Then add green onion tops and parsley. Cook 3 minutes.

title: hot rolls
directions: Stir first 6 ingredients together.
Add flour; beat well. Spoon into greased muffin pans.
Bake at 350° until browned top and bottom.
If you don't bake all at once, store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Will keep a week.

title: grape salad(heritage)
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add pineapple and pie filling.
I use a 8x11 glass dish to make a thicker salad.
Put in refrigerator and let set till firm.

title: spinach dip
directions: The spinach should have all excess water squeezed out.
Mix all ingredients and chill for 8 hours.
Serve with Wheat Thins or raw vegetables.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix cocoa, milk, butter and sugar in a saucepan and bring to a rolling boil for 1 minute.
Turn off burner.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop out on wax paper and cool, then eat them all up.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Combine lemon and stir into milk; add eggs.
Pour into graham cracker crust and place in refrigerator.

title: turkey dressing pie
directions: In a large bowl, combine dressing, broth, butter and egg; mix well.
Press into the bottom and up the sides of an ungreased 10-inch pie plate.
Set aside.
In a large skillet, saute onion in oil until tender.
Stir in turkey, gravy, peas (if desired), parsley, pimentos, Worcestershire sauce and thyme.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, or until golden.
Yields 6 servings.

title: danish tarts
directions: Mix well.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour.
Roll into small balls.
Punch hole or indention in center of ball.
Fill with any flavor jelly.
Bake at 300° about 15 minutes.
Makes about 35 small cookies.
(I always double the recipe because they go fast.)

title: corn & green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans and corn, put in a greased dish.
Mix soup, cheese, sour cream; pour over bean and corn.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Blend crackers, margarine, almonds; pour over beans and corn.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Suggested Fruit:
Peaches, apples, strawberries, melon and kiwi.

title: marinade for beef
directions: Mix all together and beat with egg beater.
Marinate meat overnight, turning occasionally, in refrigerator.
Especially good for London Broil.

title: freezing fruits
directions: One peck of apples or peaches will make about 2 gallon freezer bags of fruit.

title: fruit freeze
directions: Cream together cheese and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients, blending well.
Place in muffin tins which have been lined with paper or tin; freeze.
Remove from freezer a few minutes before serving.

title: wedding soup
directions: In pot place chicken, water, bouillon cubes, onion and celery. Bring to boil; simmer until chicken is cooked.
Remove chicken, onion and celery.
Beat together eggs and cheese.
Cook spinach as directed on package.
Cook pastina as directed.
Make small meatballs.
Place in oven at 500° for 10 minutes.

title: easy low-fat chili
directions: In large saucepan, cook the onion and green pepper in 1/2 cup water until tender.
Add beans, paste and tomatoes.
Stir in chili powder, salt, pepper and rest of water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serves 7 (1 cup) servings (low-fat).

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix or beat eggs well.
Add sugar; mix well.
Add milk, vanilla and coconut.
Pour in unbaked pie crust and bake on 400° until it shakes like jello in the middle or a knife comes out clean.

title: beef and vegetable stir-fry
directions: Partially freeze steak; slice diagonally across grain into thin strips.
Combine meat, 1 tablespoon soy sauce, 1 tablespoon sherry, garlic powder and 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
Set aside.
Combine water, bouillon cubes and ginger root in a small saucepan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Add hoisin sauce, soy sauce, sherry, cornstarch and red pepper flakes; set aside.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Press rolls into 10-inch ungreased pie pan.
Spread with mustard.
Bake in a 375° oven for 8 minutes.
In a skillet, saute zucchini, onion and mushrooms in margarine.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes until mixture is firm.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 6.

title: spinach balls
directions: Drain spinach well; squeeze to remove excess moisture.
Combine spinach with remaining ingredients.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls; place on lightly greased cookie sheets.
(These can be made ahead and frozen, then baked.)
They taste like sausage.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Alternately add liquids with sifted dry ingredients beginning and ending with flour mixture.

title: black cherry fruit jello
directions: Mix the jello with the boiling water.
Add the milk, fruit cocktail (including juice), pineapple (including juice) and cream cheese (crumbled). Stir. Refrigerate several hours until firm.

title: beef stew
directions: In large stew pan, boil stew meat and garlic together until it starts to become tender. Leaving the broth in the pan; add all the vegetables, tomato sauce and tomato paste. Cover and continue simmering over low heat until meat is tender and vegetables are done. Stir often.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix together.
Add salt, pepper and mayonnaise to taste. Makes a quick dish for salad suppers.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: stickies
directions: Mix flour, Crisco and enough milk to make stiff dough.
Roll dough to 1/8 inch thickness rectangular shape.
Cream together brown sugar and margarine.
Spread on sugar mixture.
Roll beginning with larger side.
Stretch slightly, cut pieces 1/2 inch thick.
Place on heavy cookie sheet that has been Pammed or greased.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: candied carrots
directions: Peel and boil carrots until tender.
Melt margarine in Teflon skillet until hot.
Add carrots, salt and pepper.
Turn heat to medium and cook until lightly browned.
Add sugar and cook about 10 minutes longer, turning occasionally.
Add sprinkled cinnamon, if desired.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Place fresh sliced apples into unbaked pie shell.
Use pastry blender or fork and mix the margarine, sugar, flour and cinnamon. Crumble this over apples.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Pour hot water over sugar and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1/2 c. flour.
Mix thoroughly. Stir in softened yeast, egg, salt and half of remaining flour. Beat thoroughly.
Add enough flour to form a soft dough.
Turn out on lightly flour board.
Let rest 5 to 10 minutes.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in greased bowl, turn to grease top. Cover.
Let rise until doubled.
Punch down.
Cover and refrigerate.
When ready to bake, cut or shape into rolls.
Let rise in ungreased pan until doubled in size.
Bake at 425 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.
Dough may be stored in refrigerator at least 4 days.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: Combine croutons and cheese; put on bottom of a casserole. Mix other ingredients until well blended.
Pour over croutons. Crumble cooked bacon on top.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 325°. Serves 6.

title: chow mein
directions: Brown pork very good and simmer for at least 1 hour, even 2. Add onions, cut up and browned.
Add celery (cut up) and simmer a little longer.
Add bean sprouts, mushrooms, water chestnuts and about 2 tablespoons of brown gravy sauce.
Mix about 4 tablespoons of cornstarch in with water and pour into first ingredients.
Serve over chow mein noodles with rice on the side.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: aunt liz's ginger cookie recipe
directions: Heat butter, Crisco and molasses in a saucepan until all melts.
Pour into a large bowl of remaining ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Divide in 1/4 balls.
Wrap and put in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut round steak into thin strips.
In skillet, cook and stir beef strips until no longer pink.
Add soup and liquid from tomatoes.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Add green pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Cut tomatoes into quarters; add to mixture and simmer 5 minutes.
Add soy sauce and pepper.
In small bowl, combine cornstarch and water.
Stir into meat mixture.
Heat and stir until mixture boils and thickens.
Serve over rice or potatoes.

title: microwave beef stew
directions: In casserole, microwave stew meat with beef broth and water at Low for 60 minutes.
Mix in vegetables and other ingredients and continue cooking for 20 to 30 minutes, stirring gently after 15 minutes, until meat and vegetables are tender.

title: mexican stuffed shells
directions: In a small bowl, combine picante sauce, water and tomato sauce. In a 9 x 13-inch dish, spread 1/2 cup of the combined sauce and swish around to coat the bottom.
Stir 1/2 of the remaining sauce into the meat and add 3/4 cup of cheese and 1/2 can of the French fried onions.
Mix thoroughly.
Stuff the shells with the meat mixture and arrange in the pan.
Top with remaining sauce.
Bake 30 minute at 350° covered.
Top with remaining cheese and onions. Bake uncovered 5 minutes or until onions are golden brown.

title: virginia salad
directions: Layer all ingredients in order given.
Do not mix.
Cover with 1 cup mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese a lot.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Take 3 slices buttered bread, cut 1 package Borden Chateau cheese into 1-inch squares.
Place bread and cheese in layers in casserole.
Beat 2 eggs and add 3 cups milk, salt and paprika. Pour over bread, salt and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ocean somen salad
directions: Boil somen as directed on package.
Mix sugar, oil, salt and vinegar really well.
Mix somen, kamaboko, ocean salad and sauce together.
Chill and serve.

title: oatmeal chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars thoroughly.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Mix flour, soda and salt together and add to creamed mixture; blending well.
Add oats, nuts and chips.
Drop by teaspoon into ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.
(Batter is quite gooey before baking.)

title: hot broccoli dip
directions: Before you add cheese, remove large pieces of broccoli.
Melt oleo.
Add grated onion and broccoli.
Cook slowly until thoroughly cooked.
Add mushroom soup.
Add drained chopped mushrooms.
Cook until mixed.
Add cheese.
Cook over low heat until melted.
Watch closely and stir now and then.
Remove from heat.
Serve with chips.

title: vegetable rice salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Toss to coat well.
Cover and chill.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Combine ground beef and onion.
Cook with a little oil until brown.
Add corned beef, chili powder, Worcestershire sauce, water, ketchup and brown sugar.
Simmer until desired consistency. Good served on hamburger rolls with slaw.

title: creamy nut fruit salad
directions: When a gelatin dessert or salad calls for 2 packages flavored gelatin, use one envelope unflavored gelatin and one envelope flavored gelatin.
Fold in fruits or vegetables as usual.

title: glazed carrot bake
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water until half done.
Drain and put in 1-quart baking dish.
Stir in raisins, butter, honey, lemon juice and ginger.
Bake uncovered in a preheated 375° oven for 35 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Sprinkle with almonds and serve. Makes 4 servings.

title: broccoli noodle pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes in a square pan.

title: pull apart vegetable bread
directions: Quarter biscuits and dip in melted margarine.
Divide bacon, cheese, onion and bell pepper 3 ways.
Layer biscuits, then bacon, cheese, bell pepper and onion.
Repeat.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crab dip
directions: Blend together cream cheese, mayonnaise, dry mustard, dried onion and salt.
Fold in rest of ingredients.
Serve with crackers.

title: diabetic peanut butter balls
directions: Cream peanut butter using 2 Tbsp. of milk from 1 cup. Add raisins, remaining milk, and crushed graham crackers. Roll into one inch balls and drop onto waxed paper. Chill.

title: terrific treats
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows and stir constantly until melted.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies.
Spread in buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: hamburg and potatoes
directions: Simmer hamburg and onions.
Add rest of ingredients.
Slice 1/4 pound of potatoes.
Add to meat mixture and cook slowly until potatoes are done.

title: sausage dip
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Over low heat, combine cream cheese, sausage and chiles and tomatoes until well blended.
Place in small crock-pot and keep on low heat.
Serve with tostados chips as a dip.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Place in uncooked pie shell. Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix all ingredients together. Serve with crackers.

title: snake eyes
directions: Cut a 2-inch circle from the center of both slices of bread. Place the margarine in a 350° frying pan.
When margarine has melted, place the bread in the pan, then put 1 egg in the center of each slice of bread.
When egg is slightly firm and able to be turned, turn the bread and allow to cook for about one more minute or two.
Enjoy!

title: creamy sausage casserole
directions: Fix the Velveeta and shells; stir in chicken soup.
Steam broccoli and stir in sliced sausage and mix together.
Bake at 325° or until good and hot!

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix ingredients well and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: zucchini nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease standard size muffin pans.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Set aside.
Combine sugar and eggs in large bowl of electric mixer and beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Gradually add oil in a slow steady stream, beating constantly for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add zucchini and vanilla and blend well.
Stir in nuts and raisins. Fold in sifted dry ingredients just until batter is evenly moistened.
Do not overmix.
Spoon batter into muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake until lightly browned, about 25 minutes. Let stand for 10 minutes, then turn muffins out on rack to cool.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Melt butter in soup kettle.

Add shallots and saute until lightly browned. Add gin and reduce by 3/4. Add rest of ingredients except cream and half and half. Simmer 30 minutes. Add cream and half and half and heat through. Do not boil.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine sweet potato with all ingredients and blend well. Pour into partially baked pie shell. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown and puffy.

title: vegetable dip
directions: In a
saucepan
heat
together
butter, oil and garlic. Let them steep
for
minutes without letting the fat boil. Add anchovy fillets.
Stir
and blend the anchovies until they are dissolved,
without
allowing
the
fat
to boil or brown. Prepare a dish
of fresh vegetable strips to dip in the sauce. When serving, keep the sauce hot over a spirit lamp.

title: lemon squares
directions: Sift flour and sugar into bowl.
Blend butter with clean fingertips until well mixed.
Pat evenly into the bottom of an 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: roast turkey
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove giblet and neck (may be inside or at the top above the breast).
Remove excess fat.
Put salt, pepper and Mrs. Dash all over the body of the turkey.
Loosen skin on the breast with fingers. With fingers, spread 7 tablespoons of butter under the skin on breast. Stuff cavity, if desired.
Tie legs together. Rub 1 tablespoon on breast. Sprinkle with seasonings.
Put in baking bag and add soup. Roast 3 1/2 hours. Check with meat thermometer to see if done.
Must register 170°. Push in thickest part of thigh, not touching the meat. Cool and serve.

title: pesto
directions: Place basil leaves (no stems; unwashed), garlic cloves and small amount of oil in food processor.
Continue to add oil until thick and pasty and leaves are all blended.
Add grated cheese. Blend slowly.
Remove from food processor and mix in pine nuts or walnuts.
Serve over hot linguine.
Makes 3 to 4 cups.
Pesto can be frozen or refrigerated.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Mix bread and milk.
Add 1/2 tsp of vanilla.
Fold stiff egg whites into bread mixture and bake at 325 degrees.
Bake slow.
Check after about 20 minutes, then check often until done.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix together and put in crust.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 375°.

title: caramel pears
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pears, in saucepan.
Simmer until smooth and blended.
Place pear halves in caramel syrup. Heat, basting with syrup.
Serve warm or chilled with sour cream or ice cream.
Yields 4 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Melt on heat slowly oil and chocolate; set aside.
Combine sugar, eggs, applesauce and vanilla.
In separate bowl, sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add sugar mixture to dry ingredients.
Add melted chocolate mixture.
Beat well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Mix powdered sugar, butter, cocoa and cream or milk.
Spread over cooled brownies.

title: banana shake
directions: Blend milk and ice milk in blender at high speed until smooth. Add banana and blend for 2 or 3 seconds.
Serve immediately.

title: easy potato soup
directions: Cook vegetables in 2 cups water until tender.
Add salt to taste.
Add milk.
Then to thicken, add potato flakes.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix eggs (boiled and raw), sugar, mustard, oil, salt, pepper and vinegar in blender until smooth.
Pour over potatoes and onion; mix.

title: cotton pickin good cake
directions: In mixer cream eggs, cake mix, oil and mandarin oranges with juice.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan at 350° until center pressed with finger is firm.
Do not overbake.

title: syrup for pancakes
directions: Pour ingredients into small saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Good on waffles, too.

title: pasta picnic salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Rinse with cold water. Drain well. Combine with remaining ingredients, mixing gently, but thoroughly.
Cover and chill 4 hours or overnight. Yields 6 servings.

title: creton for sandwiches
directions: Combine.
Cook slow over low heat.
Beat with a mixer when cooked.
Spread on bread.
Makes about 30 round open-face sandwiches.

title: hawaiian dip
directions: Serve with various crackers and raw vegetables.

title: creamy tuna broccoli and swiss sauce
directions: *May substitute 1 (10-ounce) package frozen broccoli cuts, cooked and drained.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into small balls.
Makes approximately 200.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Bring butter, cocoa, oil and water to rapid boil in saucepan.
Pour over flour and sugar and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix and serve with veggies.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and drain.
Stir in salsa, corn, mayo and chili powder.
Grease a 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Put 2 handfuls of chips from extra on bottom.
Put layer of meat, layer of chips and layer of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Top with shredded lettuce and tomatoes, if desired.

title: mary ann's chicken
directions: Make sauce with first 3 ingredients plus a little water.
Add chicken and marinate for 1 hour.
Bake 1 hour covered in 350° oven. Serve over rice if you like.

title: baked german pancakes(tastes almost like french toast)
directions: Melt 1/4 stick of margarine in each of 2 round cake pans (any size).
Beat eggs until frothy.
Add to beaten eggs the flour, milk, sugar, soft butter or margarine and cinnamon.
Divide batter equally between the two cake pans.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Turn down to 350°.
Bake for 10 more minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Place chili beans, tomato juice, chili lengths, onion and chili powder in a large pan. Add browned beef and cook until all is cooked well.

title: cherry cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Top with chopped nuts and brown sugar. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serve in squares topped with Reddi-Wip.
Makes 12 servings or divide for smaller pieces.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Have cheese at room temperature.
Mix both cheeses together. Add the nuts.
Add garlic to taste.
Roll in ball; sprinkle foil with chili powder and wrap ball in foil.
Put in refrigerator; keep cool.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve with Triscuits.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: cream puffs
directions: Put water and butter in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Add flour and salt at once.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture won't stick to pan.
While still hot, add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each.
Drop by tablespoon on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.
Reduce heat to 325°.
Bake 30 minutes longer.
Cut open. Fill with any filling.

title: hearty bran muffins
directions: *Adds nutty flavor; available at health food stores.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Beat at medium 4 minutes. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: cranberry relish mold
directions: Drain pineapple.
Reserve syrup and add water to make 1/2 cup. Dissolve jello and sugar in 1 cup hot water.
Add syrup and lemon juice.
Chill until partially set.
Add cranberries, fruits, celery and nuts.
Chill in a 5-cup ring overnight.

title: chocolate supreme
directions: Combine margarine, flour, nuts, salt and sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
