Mix the cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip until smooth.
Pour over crust while still warm.
Mix milk and pudding until creamy. Pour over the cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Cook in a double boiler until thick.
Fill crust with mixture.

title: jumbles
directions: Cream the butter; gradually add the sugar, beating until light and fluffy, then add flavoring and eggs, beating all together until light.
Stir in the flour and mix to a stiff dough.
The dough can be chilled at this point for easier handling.

title: spicy pecans
directions: Beat 1 egg until frothy and 1 tablespoon water.
Melt butter in pan; stir a lot.
Add sugar, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves. Put pecans in 1 egg white and coat well, then put them into sugar and spices; cover well.
Place in pan with butter and bake at 250° until done.

title: peanut butter and chocolate fudge bars
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix in peanut butter and vanilla.
Add sugar; mix well.
Pat mixture into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt Hershey bar. Pour over peanut butter mixture and chill.
Cut into bars and forget your diet!
Taste a lot like buckeyes only easier to make.

title: easy crab dip
directions: In a small bowl, combine ingredients.
Cover; refrigerate until serving time.
Serve as a dip with fresh vegetables.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: wild rice with mushrooms and almonds
directions: Cook and stir wild rice, almonds, chives and mushrooms in butter until almonds are golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 325°.
Pour wild rice mixture into ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole pan.
Heat broth to boil.
Stir into wild rice mixture. Cover and bake until all liquid is absorbed and wild rice is tender and fluffy, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: earthquake cake(9 x 13)
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Layer coconut then pecans. In bowl, mix cake as directed on box.
Pour over coconut and pecans.
In bowl, mix cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar (will be thin).
Pour over top of cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: three grain muffin mix
directions: Mix first eight ingredients well.
Store in an airtight container in a cool, dry place.

title: bread
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water; let set for 5 to 10 minutes. Add salt and sugar and stir together.
Mix first flour, egg and Crisco.
Add to yeast mixture and combine with whisk or mixer. Mix second flour in with a wooden spoon.
Flour the board and knead.
(Dough will be sticky.)
Continue to add flour (total amount of flour should be 3 to 3 1/2 cups) and knead until dough is no longer sticky.
Place dough in a bowl, cover with a cloth and set in a warm place until it doubles in size.
Punch down and knead for a few minutes longer.
Put dough into a greased bread pan and let it raise to just above pan.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 1 hour.
(When thumped, bread should sound hollow.)

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix thoroughly the shortening, margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour, soda and salt.
Add chocolate chips and nuts if you want and mix in slowly or stir in. Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes (depending on the size of cookie).
I like to make big cookies so it takes about 15 minutes or bake until light brown.
Cool slightly before removing from baking sheet.
Makes about 6 dozen "big size" cookies.
Happy Eating!

title: wilted spinach salad
directions: Dice bacon and cook crisp; drain and set aside.
Blend flour and bacon grease over low heat.
Add buttermilk and cook until thick.
Mix sugar, salt and vinegar; add.
Wash, dry and chill spinach in advance.
Just before serving, tear spinach into bite size pieces.
Pour hot dressing over spinach and toss.
Sprinkle with bacon and serve immediately.
(You may substitute sour cream or plain yogurt for buttermilk.)

title: pan coating
directions: Put in mixing bowl and beat on medium to high for 5 to 10 minutes.
Will look like whipped cream; will be thick and fluffy. Use to coat cake pans and any pan you are going to bake in.

title: green chili
directions: Cut up pork into cubes and coat with flour: brown.
Brown onions with pork.
Add flour to dripping like making gravy.
Add enough water to cover meat.
Simmer for 45 minutes.
Chop up chiles and tomatoes and add to meat mixture.
Simmer for 2 hours.

title: hamburger skillet stew
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, onion, salt, pepper, steak sauce and 1/2 of tomato soup.
Shape into 16 balls.
Brown in skillet in shortening; add vegetables, water and salt.
Pour rest of tomato soup; cover and simmer 1 hour.
Stir once in awhile. Remove 1/2 cup of the stew sauce and mix with flour; slowly pour into stew until gravy thickens.

title: "gooey" butter cake
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and 2 eggs, stirring until well blended.
Beat 1 minute.
Spread batter in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Beat cream cheese with an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Beat in remaining 2 eggs and then vanilla.
Set aside 1/2 cup or less confectioners sugar.
Beat in remaining confectioners sugar.
Pour evenly over cake batter in pan. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until cake pulls away from sides of pan.
Cool 20 minutes; sprinkle with some or all of the remaining sugar, as preferred.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Put Hershey bars, milk and marshmallows in double boiler (do not let water in bottom boil).
Heat mixture until it is mixed well.
Let cool, then fold in the whipping cream.
Put the mixture into the baked pie shell.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour or overnight.
Can sprinkle ground almonds on top of pie.

title: hot pineapple salad
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, layer the drained pineapple, cream cheese and marshmallows.
In a saucepan, mix sugar, flour, eggs and drained juice; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Mixture will be consistency of thin pudding.
Pour thickened sauce over pineapple mixture; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until cheese is slightly brown around edges.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In a large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water. Add pudding mix; beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Add the 2 cups of whipped cream.
Top with one-third each of the wafers, bananas and pudding.
Repeat layer twice, ending with pudding.
Chill thoroughly.

title: no crust egg custard
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a well-greased pan and bake for 25 minutes at temperature to suit your stove or until knife comes out clean.

title: shrimp appetizer platter
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Spread over 12-inch round platter or pizza pan.
Scatter shrimp on cheese layer; cover with seafood sauce.
Layer on Mozzarella, green pepper, onion and tomato.
Cover and chill until serving time. Serve with crackers.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Drain fruit.
Use juice from fruit and add enough water to make 1 cup.
Bring to a boil and pour over jello.
While hot, add cream cheese and whip it up for a minute.
Chill for about 1 hour, until soupy.
Add fruit to jello.
Prepare Dream Whip; fold into jello, then put entire mixture into a mold.
Chill until firm.

title: lime pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together; blend well.
Pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate until served.

title: wedding punch
directions: Combine all juices and sugar.
Chill.
Add remaining ingredients, just before serving.
Serves 65 to 70.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Pour boiling water over sugar and cornstarch; cook until thick.
Remove from heat; add strawberry Jell-O.
Let cool and pour over strawberries.
Refrigerate.

title: cabbage bundles
directions: Parboil cabbage leaves 5 minutes, drain and cool.
Set aside. Combine beef, bread crumbs, seasonings, eggs and onions; mix well. Form into 12 oblong patties.
Place meat patty on each cabbage leaf.
Roll up in cabbage leaf.
Place bundle open side down in baking dish.
Mix tomato soup with 1/2 can water.
Pour over bundles.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: grandma's sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
(Chopped onion may be added to the meat as it is browning.)
Set aside.
In a saucepan, bring to boil vinegar, brown sugar and water, then add ketchup, mustard and cornstarch or flour with enough water to make a paste.
Cook until mixture is thickened.
Combine hamburger with mixture.
Stir until well combined.
Serve on toasted hamburger buns.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except potato chips.
Blend well. Pour mixture into prepared casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until casserole is bubbly.
Sprinkle potato chips over top and heat again for a very few minutes until top is golden brown.
Serves 12.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Cream shortening, white sugar and brown sugar.
Mix with oats.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift together and add to mixture flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Bake in 9 x 14-inch pan for 25 minutes at 350°, then put on topping.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients well and cook in 350° oven for 45 minutes (approximately).

title: buttermilk cornbread
directions: Combine dry ingredient; add eggs and buttermilk, mixing well. Pour batter into 2 greased 8-inch square pans.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cut into squares.
Yield: 16 to 18 squares.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Beat margarine at medium speed with an electric mixer. Gradually add sugars, beating well.
Add egg substitute and vanilla; mix well.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients. Gradually add to margarine mixture, mixing well.
Stir in raisins. Drop dough by 2 teaspoons onto cookie sheets coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until
lightly browned.
Transfer to wire racks to cool.
Yields 3 dozen.
There are 65 calories (21% from fat) per cookie.

title: queso blanco
directions: Combine all ingredients and spoon into a 1-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: pepperoni puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In bowl, combine soup and shortening. Stir in biscuit mix.
Mix well.
Add pepperoni, onion and caraway. Drop by rounded tablespoonful on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes or until done. Makes 30.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt together.
In small saucepan, put butter, oil, water and cocoa.
Bring to boil and pour over flour mixture.
Add eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix well and put in greased cookie sheet with a rim.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: blackberry muffins
directions: Sprinkle berries with little of flour.
Add remaining flour with other dry ingredients; melt butter and combine with milk and beaten egg yolk.
Mix dry and liquid mixtures quickly and fold in stiffly beaten egg white.
Drop by spoonfuls into greased muffin tins.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields 12 to 15 muffins.

title: chunky macadamia nut white chocolate cookies
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with mixer until fluffy.
Gradually add sugars, beating well.
Add egg and vanilla, mixing well. Combine flour and next three ingredients.
Gradually add to butter mixture, mixing well.
Stir in morsels.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool.

title: big mac
directions: Cook 2 skinny hamburgers as desired.
Fry onions in oil until browned.
Arrange Big Mac as follows:

bottom bun, 1 tablespoon sauce, half the lettuce, cheese, 1 meat patty, half the onions, one-half bun, remaining sauce, remaining lettuce, 3 pickle slices, meat patty, remaining onions and top of sesame seed bun.
Place in 375° oven for 5 minutes.
Yields 1 serving.

title: ernest's shepherd's pie
directions: Line oil sprayed baking dish with 1/2 of the mashed potatoes. Mix meat, onion, milk and beaten egg together; spread on top of potatoes.
Cover with remaining mashed potatoes.
Bake in a 300° oven until light brown and the meat is done.

title: peanut butter cookie kisses
directions: Cream the sugars, shortening and peanut butter.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour and baking soda.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in sugar.
Bake for 8 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven.
Press Kisses in center of cookie. Return to oven; bake 3 more minutes.

title: no-knead refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix hot water, sugar, salt and shortening together in bowl. Dissolve yeast in warm water (5 minutes).
Add 2 cups flour to first mixture and beat until smooth.
Add egg and yeast.
Beat until well-blended.
Stir in remaining flour, one cup at a time. Place dough in greased bowl.
Brush top with soft shortening. Cover tightly with aluminum foil or bowl cover.
Store in refrigerator until double in bulk or until needed.
When ready to use, push down and cut off dough.
Shape in any desired fashion and put in pans.
Let rise until light and double in bulk (about 2 hours) at room temperature.
Bake in a preheated 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes (until golden brown).
Dough may be kept in refrigerator a week.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice to boiling.
Add gelatin mix; let cool.
Mix Cool Whip and buttermilk together and add to pineapple mixture.
Add nuts.
Chill before serving.

title: cherry pie royale
directions: Combine gelatin and sugar; add boiling water and stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Drain cherries and reserve 3/4 cup juice. Add juice to gelatin mixture; chill until slightly thickened. Stir in cherries and pour into cooled pie shell.
Refrigerate for 20 minutes.
Blend milk and sour cream in mixing bowl; add vanilla pudding.
Beat with rotary beater until well blended, about 1 minute.
Spread over cherries; chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: crawfish creole style
directions: Heat oil and margarine slightly in a saucepan.
Add onions, bell pepper, celery, garlic and green onions; saute until tender over medium to low heat.
Add parsley and cook another 5 minutes. Add crawfish tails, cover and cook for 10 minutes over medium heat.

Remove from heat and stir in shrimp, fish, red pepper, black pepper, salt, Accent, tomato paste and 1 1/2 cups water. Return to heat, cover and cook for 30 minutes over medium heat or until desired tenderness is reached.
Serve over rice.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: In a saucepan, combine the butter and brown sugar.
Cook over low heat until bubbly, stirring constantly.
Cool, add the eggs one at a time, to the cooled mixture.
Beat well after each, then add vanilla.
Sift the dry ingredients together.
Add the brown sugar mixture along with the nuts.

title: spaghetti with eggplant
directions: Wipe the eggplants, peel them and cut them into thin slices. Sprinkle with salt and leave in a colander or on a tilted plate for 1 hour to drain off their bitter juices.
Wipe the slices dry and fry in hot oil, a few at a time, until brown on both sides. Drain on paper towels.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown together in skillet hamburger, onion and celery.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Add all other ingredients and stir.
Top with chow mein noodles.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Melt margarine in large casserole pan.
Add rice and soup and 3 cups water.
Mix well.
Place fryer in and bake, covered, at 325° for 2 hours.

title: rice pilaf(microwave)
directions: Saute 2 tablespoons butter and onion on High for 6 minutes. Stir one time.
Add rice; cover with wax paper and cook on high 2 minutes.
Add stock, the bouquet garni, salt and pepper.
Cover with plastic wrap and cook on High 20 minutes.
Stir halfway through cooking time.
Let stand, covered 10 minutes.
Remove bouquet garni.
Dot top with a fork to fluff rice and taste for seasoning.
Makes 4 cups.

title: dirt pie
directions: Mix pudding mix with milk (directions on pudding box) then add Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Take Oreo cookies and break into small pieces.
Layer your pudding mixture with cookie crumbs.

title: 3 layer delight
directions: * Can use strawberry cake mix and strawberry pie filling. Lemon pudding is very good.
Change to cherry or blueberry pie filling.

title: date sticks
directions: Put dates and pecans into a bowl and take 2 tablespoons of flour and mix until all are coated.
Take 6 egg whites and beat until they peak.
Gradually add sugar, 2 spoons at a time, to the egg whites.
Add remaining flour the same way.
Gradually add dates and pecans and fold until all are coated.
Add vanilla extract.
Line pan with aluminum foil.
Spread mixture (be sure it is thin).
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut into sticks while warm and roll in confectioners sugar to coat.

title: lemon and pine nut rice
directions: Bring chicken stock to a boil in saucepan.
Stir in rice. Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes until all liquid is absorbed. Melt butter in another saucepan over low heat.
Cook and stir pine nuts or shell sunflower seeds in butter until golden brown.
Stir in parsley, lemon peel and lemon juice. Pour nut/butter/juice mixture over hot rice. Stir to coat.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain all beans well.
Combine first 6 ingredients; mix carefully.
Combine and mix remaining ingredients; pour over vegetables.
Cover; chill 2 to 4 hours or overnight.
Makes about 6 to 8 servings.

title: beet borscht(good to make in early a.m. to be served on a very hot day.)
directions: In blender or food processor, combine beets with stock.
Add lemon, dill, salt and scallions.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into a bowl; blend in the sour cream or sour cream and yogurt.
Chill in refrigerator until very cold.
Taste for seasonings.
It should be nice and lemony.
Top each bowl with another spoonful of sour cream and the chopped chives.

title: soupapias
directions: Knead together flour and shortening (I use a fork).
Add baking powder and salt.
Then knead water in 1/2 cup at a time until you have a smooth dough that is stretchy.
You may need a bit more water.
Let dough rest 1 hour for knead texture.
While that rises, brown ground beef.	Drain and set aside.
Chop tomato, lettuce, onion and put each in small bowls to use as garnish (like tacos) along with cheese.	Separate your dough in serving sizes needed (it makes about 5).
Roll out each small serving to about 1/4-inch thick and place a little hamburger on one half and layer of cheese. Fold other side over and pinch tightly closed.
Deep fry until golden brown.
Repeat for other "dough servings" making like a beef turn over.	Garnish and serve.

title: lemon delight
directions: Mix well and place in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken coating
directions: Put shortening and butter in pan; put in oven.
Mix Bisquick, salt and pepper.
Roll chicken in it.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour, 1/2 hour on each side.

title: pineapple bars
directions: Combine 1st four ingredients for crust (mixture will be crumbly).
Pat 2/3 of this mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook last four ingredients until thick, stirring constantly; spread evenly over crust.
Sprinkle remaining 1/3 of crust mixture over top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: rodes punch
directions: Combine Kool-Aid packages with sugar.
Add pineapple juice and water to fill up a 1-gallon container.
Place in freezer overnight.
Remove from freezer 1 hour before serving and let mixture become slushy.
Pour into punch bowl and add chilled ginger ale and 7-Up.

title: grandma thompson's old fashioned stickies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, shortening and milk as for biscuits.
Roll out thin; spread melted margarine over dough, then sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over margarine.
Next, roll up as jelly roll.
Cut in 1-inch slices; place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: christmas delight
directions: Melt butter in pan, size 8 x 11-inch.
When butter melts, add cracker crumbs and spread smoothly.
Add coconut, chips and nuts; spread in pan, then pour milk over all ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Cool; then cut in squares.

title: pretzel jello
directions: In 9 x 13-inch glass, melt margarine, covered, 1 1/2 to 2 minutes on 70% power in microwave.
Add crushed pretzels and sugar; mix and press to form bottom crust.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes on High, turning once.
Cool.

title: rainbow sherbet
directions: Mix together macaroon pieces with Cool Whip.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan, reserving 1/2 the mixture.
Spread the sherbet over the mix.
Top with the other half and freeze.
Nice to have on hand in freezer.

title: minute penuche frosting
directions: Stir over low heat until melted.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and beat until lukewarm.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Cook broccoli as directed on package.
Slowly mix milk and soup in large saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: jiffy cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together until light.
Add flour and baking powder.
Heat milk and margarine to boiling point.
Stir into egg-flour mixture.
Pour into greased pan and bake 40 minutes at 325°.
Make topping while cake is baking.

title: bakers icing
directions: Put flour and milk in jar and shake until lumps are gone. Pour into saucepan and heat over low heat, stirring constantly until it boils and thickens.
Set aside to cool.
Mix remaining ingredients in blender at high speed until light and fluffy.
Add flour mixture and blend at high speed until very smooth.
Spread over cake.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Chill juice and ginger ale before mixing together.
Put sherbet in punch bowl.
Pour juice and ginger ale over sherbet. Stir until mixed well.
Serve.

title: mini pizza
directions: Open biscuits and put them on the oven pan.
Then put spaghetti sauce on each biscuit.
Add the cheese and other toppings.
Set oven at 320° and let them cook for 28 to 43 minutes.

title: bouillabaisse
directions: Cut fish (using several varieties) into 2-inch pieces.
Add lobster.
In a large saucepan, place olive oil, parsley, bay leaves, saffron, fennel, tomato, orange rind and garlic.
Add fish.
Cover with 1 1/2-quarts water.
Add salt and pepper and bring to a boil.
Boil quickly 15 to 20 minutes and remove pan from fire.
Replace cooked parsley with a tablespoon of finely cut fresh parsley.
Pour Bouillabaisse into tureen over several thick slices of white bread.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: turnips
directions: Peel turnips and potato; slice thinly.
Combine all ingredients and cook until tender, about 45 minutes.
Mash with potato masher.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Grease or butter a 13 x 9-inch or larger pan.
Sprinkle rice in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle dried onion on top.
In mixing bowl, put mushroom soup, celery soup and water.
Pour over rice and place chicken on top.
Spoon onion soup over top of chicken. Sprinkle paprika and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.
Do not peek!

title: fast pound cake
directions: Fill powdered sugar box with flour.
Add alternately flour and eggs.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: caribbean fudge pie
directions: Cream the margarine with sugar. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Melt chocolate chips in top of double boiler or in microwave.
Add melted chocolate and instant coffee to egg mixture. Stir in flour and 1 cup broken walnuts.
Turn into pie shell. Top with remaining walnuts (halves), if desired.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool. Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip, if desired.
(The cream actually tones down the sweetness!)
Slice thin.
Very rich and yummy.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: In 10-inch skillet or baking pan, melt butter; add brown sugar.
Add well drained fruit and nuts; arrange to form top of the cake.
Set aside.

title: jill's jello
directions: Mix ingredients; pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate until set.
Cut into squares.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken; let cool and pull off bone.
Cut into small pieces.
Roll biscuits thin and cut in small strips.
Drop into chicken broth and cut up chicken.
Peel boiled eggs; cut into slices and put in with dumplings.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: black forest cake
directions: Beat
well
with mixer until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured
Bundt
pan.
Bake	45
minutes at 350°.
Cool 25 minutes. Invert
onto rack.
Slice into 3 layers.
Divide one can of cherry pie filling and Cool Whip between slices, ending with cherries on top.

title: sandra's pickles
directions: Wash cukes but do not cut off ends.
Pack tightly in glass gallon jar.
Add salt, pickling spice and alum.
Fill jar with vinegar.
Screw on lid and set aside for 6 weeks.

title: asparagus pepperidge
directions: Cook asparagus until just crisp-tender.
Add melted butter to the dressing mix.
Mix soup with milk.
You may use 1/2 to 1 whole package.
Alternate layers of asparagus, dressing and soup.
Top with buttered crumbs, if desired.
Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes or until bubbly and golden.

title: molded shrimp dip
directions: Heat soup.
Stir in gelatine.
Add softened cream cheese. Beat with beater until smooth.
Add other ingredients except shrimp.
Add shrimp last.
Pour into mold.

title: hershey bar cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour (or use cocoa instead of flour) a 12-cup Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan; set aside.
In top of double boiler over hot, not boiling, water, melt candy bars.
In large mixer bowl, cream butter or margarine, sugar and eggs until light and fluffy, about 5 minutes.
Combine flour and soda; add alternately with buttermilk.
Add chocolate syrup, melted chocolate bars and vanilla; beat just until combined.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from pan; cool completely on wire rack.
To serve, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes 16 servings.

title: beef kabobs
directions: Marinate steak in Italian dressing 2 to 3 hours.
Beginning with meat on skewers, add remaining ingredients with meat in between each vegetable and ending with meat.
Baste while on grill with the remaining Italian dressing.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add Karo syrup, sugar, butter, salt and vanilla.
Place nuts on bottom of crust.
Pour mixture over nuts. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake until knife inserted into the center of pie comes out clean, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake 25 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hawaiian nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; stir in nuts and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until batter is moistened.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 9x5x3 inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.	Serve cold with ice cream or toasted with butter.
Yield:
2 loaves.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix together powdered sugar and 1/2 c. peanut butter and reserve 1/3. Pour rest in bottom of a baked pie crust. In saucepan cook egg yolks, 1/2 c. sugar, 1/4 c. flour, milk and salt until thick. Add 1 Tbsp. peanut butter, 2 Tbsp. butter and 1 tsp. vanilla. Cool and our in crust. Make meringue: Beat egg whites, cold water, 1/2 c. sugar, 1 Tbsp. cornstarch and beat until stiff. Top pie with meringue
and top meringue with reserved peanut butter mixture. Bake in 350 degree oven until brown.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: In a small bowl, combine bread crumbs, cheese, parsley, garlic which has been finely chopped, salt and black pepper.
Place this mixture in a shallow bowl.
Place 1/2 cup of melted margarine in a shallow dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Have ready a shallow baking pan.
Dip chicken pieces first in the margarine, then into the bread crumb mixture.
Place in baking pan in a single layer. Drizzle rest of melted margarine evenly over chicken.
Bake for 45 minutes, turning once only.
Chicken will be crusty and golden brown.
Yield:
6 servings.
Carbohydrate 15 g, protein 8 g, fat 28 g, calories 339.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Cool.
Cut into small pieces.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch dish:

title: green beans bravo
directions: Several hours or the night before serving, pour liquid off beans.
Toss beans well with the next 4 ingredients.
Chill 1/2 hour before serving.
At serving time, add celery and radishes. Arrange salami, lettuce, egg and onion slices in center. Serves 6.

title: janet's sausage ball
directions: Drain browned sausage.
Mix in Bisquick.
Melt Cheddar cheese and add buttermilk.
Mix into one big ball.
Form into small balls.
Place on ungreased pan and bake at 350° for 12 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.

title: fruited bran muffins
directions: In large bowl, mix bran and milk.
Let stand.
In small bowl, mix flour, baking powder and brown sugar.
Add raisins and cut fruit to flour mixture.
Mix well to cover fruit.
Add egg and margarine to bran mixture; stir.
Add flour mixture gradually to bran mixture until all is moist.
Put in muffin pans and bake 20 minutes at 400° in preheated oven.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: italian-style rice
directions: In a saucepan, saute onion in butter until tender.
Add rice, cook over medium heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in turmeric; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Stir in cheese.

title: hershey brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Frost if desired.
These will stay moist for days.

title: homos
directions: Place all ingredients in blender or food processor.
Blend until smooth.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt.
Add boiling water and vanilla. Pour into unbaked crust and sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 420° for the first 10 minutes.
Then lower oven to 350° for 30 minutes or until set.

title: tex-mex bean soup
directions: Wash beans and soak over night.
Brown onion and garlic with sausage.
Add all ingredients.
Add water to cover.
Cook 3-4 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all ingredients together.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes, or until bubbles and cheese melts.

title: fried veggie-grits patties
directions: Add 1/2 teaspoon of salt to 2 to 3 cups of water and bring to a boil.
Add veggies to water, bring back to boil and cook for 3 minutes.
Drain veggies and rinse in cold water to halt cooking.

title: banana split cake
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix together flour, butter (margarine) and pecans (mixture will be very thick and lumpy).
Press mixture into bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Cool.

title: jello punch
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add other ingredients and stir.
Pour into a gallon container.
Finish filling with water (2 cups).
Freeze.
When ready to use, thaw until soft enough to chop with food chopper.
Add 1/2 gallon of vanilla ice cream and 1 quart of ginger ale (I use more).
Makes about 6 quarts of punch.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, ginger and allspice in a medium bowl.
Combine sweet potatoes and milk in medium bowl with wire whisk until smooth.
Make well in center of dry ingredients.
Add sweet potato mixture; stir until mixture forms soft dough that clings together and forms a ball.
Turn out dough onto well-floured surface. Knead dough gently 10 to 12 times.
Roll or pat dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut out dough with floured 2 1/2-inch biscuit cutter. Place biscuits 2-inches apart on ungreased large baking sheet. Bake 12 to 14 minutes or until tops and bottoms are golden brown. Serve warm.

title: eggplant parmesan casserole
directions: Peel and slice eggplant.
Dip slices in egg and milk; dredge with flour, salt and pepper.
In large skillet heat oil and brown eggplant on both sides.
Drain on paper.
Remove remaining oil in skillet.
Saute onion, bell pepper and Italian seasoning.
In a greased 8 X 11 inch casserole place alternating layers of eggplant, cheese, onion and bell pepper mixture.
Top with parmesan cheese and bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 45 minutes or until bubbly. Serves 4 to 6.

title: lettuce salad unusual
directions: Fry bacon crisp; drain well.
Cut up raw vegetables and layer in large container.
Mix the sugar, cheese, salad dressing, salt and pepper; dot over vegetables.
Crumble bacon and sprinkle over top.
Cover and store overnight.
Toss when ready to serve.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Melt butter, add sugar and peanut butter.
Press in long dish (11 x 6).
Melt Hershey bars in microwave for 1 minute, stir and then put in for 1 more minute.
Stir and spread over top of peanut butter mixture.
Chill and cut into squares.

title: iron skillet chocolate pie
directions: Melt margarine in skillet and stir in flour, sugar and cocoa mixture.
Add beaten egg yolks and milk.
Stir until thick and add vanilla and almond flavoring.
Continue stirring until smooth and shiny (about 1 minute).

title: dump cake
directions: Grease cake pan heavily, then dump the ingredients in the order listed and spread evenly in the pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
May serve with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: praline crunch cranberry-apple pie
directions: Combine 2 cups flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Cut in 8 tablespoons butter and shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in water, 1 tablespoon at a time, until dough just comes together.
Form dough into 2 disks, one slightly larger than the other.
Wrap and chill 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Roll out larger disk on lightly floured surface to 12 inch circle.
Fit into 9-inch pie dish.
Combine pecans, brown sugar, 1/2 cup heavy cream, cinnamon and remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Stir in apples and cranberries until well coated.
Spoon fruit filling into pie crust.
Dot with remaining 2 tablespoons butter.
Roll out remaining dough to 10-inch circle.
Cover filling with dough. Vent top.
Brush with remaining 1 tablespoon heavy cream and sprinkle with sugar.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake 15 minutes. Reduce to 350°; bake 50 to 55 minutes, until filling is bubbly and crust is golden.
Cool on wire rack.

title: mississippi cabbage salad
directions: Combine cabbage and onions in large bowl.
Brown almonds and sesame seed in butter.
Put sesame seed, Top Ramen noodles and almonds in salad just before serving.
Add dressing (follows) just before serving.

title: shrimp dip spread
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.

title: steak and ale marinade
directions: Marinate chicken or steak in this mixture for at least 24 hours.

title: quick snack
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Bake at 350° until done, approximately 30 minutes.

title: chicken fried steak
directions: Mix flour, pepper and salt.
Pound it into the steak.
Cut steak into serving pieces.
Beat eggs and cream together.
Dredge meat in flour; dip in egg mix and then in cracker crumbs.
Brown in a large frying pan in hot oil.
Turn with tongs.
Cover and cook over low heat until tender.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Fry sausage or bacon until crisp; drain.
Save drippings. Sift next 4 ingredients.
Stir in cornmeal.
Combine egg, butter and buttermilk; combine with dry ingredients, corn, chilies and sausage or bacon.
Mix until just blended; do not overbeat. Batter will be stiff.
In a 10-inch cast iron skillet, heat drippings approximately 1/8-inch deep, over medium heat until sizzling.
Spoon batter into skillet.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lazy lasagna
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain well and leave in pan.
Add cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese and sauce. Mix all together and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until nice and bubbly around pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Let stand a few minutes before cutting.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with tostada chips.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Drain and mix with other ingredients, leaving some cheese for top.
Cover with tinfoil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scrumptious slaw
directions: Toss together; let stand about 2 hours.
Before serving, toss in 1/2 cup toasted almonds and 1 tablespoon sesame seed.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in large skillet.
Simmer for about 4 minutes.
Remove whole vegetables before serving.

title: cheerios treats
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to boil; stir in peanut butter and vanilla, then add Cheerios.
Press into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cut into bars.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into individual serving dishes or large serving bowl.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown beef and onion. Drain. Mix hamburger, beans, ketchup, mustard, brown sugar and chili powder together. Bake 20 minutes at 300°.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Stir sausage, cheese, eggs and milk.
Put into pie crust. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until golden brown on top.

title: fruit and sherbet
directions: Put bread on a pan.
Then put chees.
Flip it to see if it's dun.
When it's dun let it cool.
Then eat.

title: salad dressing
directions: Put in container and shake well.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together the cooked, cut up chicken, cream of mushroom soup, mayonnaise, milk and water chestnuts.
Spread half of dressing in bottom of greased 9 x 11-inch pan.
Pour on the chicken mixture.
Spread remainder of dressing on top.
Bake uncovered at 275° for 45 minutes.

title: fiesta hot chocolate
directions: Mix cocoa and flour in 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar, milk, cloves and 1 stick cinnamon.
Heat just to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly; reduce heat.
Simmer uncovered for 5 minutes (do not boil).
Remove from heat; remove cloves and cinnamon.
Stir in powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat with molinillo, wire whisk or hand beater until foamy.
Pour into 4 cups or mugs.
Serve with whipped cream and cinnamon sticks.

title: date-nut bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with flour.
Add shortening and water. Let stand for 20 minutes.
Beat eggs with fork.
Add vanilla, then sugar and flour, beating with fork.
Add date mixture; mix to first blend.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan, bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Heat soup, broth, chicken and vegetables until boiling.
Stir and boil one minute.
Spread into an ungreased pan.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over soup mixture.
Crust will rise during baking.
Bake at 375° until lightly brown, about 30 minutes.

title: baked chicken
directions: Put chicken in stove and cook about 10 minutes, then take chicken out and put ingredients on it.
Bake at 350° until tender.

title: homemade banana ice cream
directions: Mix and heat on medium-low until thoroughly hot the eggs, sugar and milk.
Mix in separate bowl the Eagle Brand milk, half and half, vanilla and bananas. Add heated mixture and pour into canister.
Fill to line with milk.

title: slush punch
directions: Combine.
Add
water to make a gallon.	Freeze.
Remove from freezer 6 hours before serving.
Serves 15 to 20.

title: ro-tel potato casserole
directions: Boil and cool potatoes.
Slice potatoes with skin on and put in 2 quart casserole dish.
Melt and mix remaining ingredients. Pour all this mixture over potatoes.
Bake uncovered until bubbly.

title: nut puffs
directions: Cream
together the first 4 ingredients.
Add flour and nuts; mix
well.	Chill
hours
and make into small balls. Bake 10 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar when cool.

title: granny's hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and chili peppers.
Stir in garlic salt, tomato sauce and chili powder.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add grated cheese, sour cream and egg.
Mix well.
Roll biscuits thin or separate into thin pieces to cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish. Use 1/2 can of biscuits for bottom and 1/2 for top.
Pour mixture over biscuits on bottom and top with remaining biscuits.
Cook for 30 minutes at 375° or until brown.

title: tommy biscuits
directions: Mix and knead. Cut or drop. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: homemade waffles
directions: Combine eggs, Wesson oil and milk in electric mixer bowl; mix well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture, beating at medium speed.
Beat for about 2 minutes.
Pour batter into hot waffle iron.
Bake until done.

title: beef roast
directions: Brown roast on top of stove.
Use approximately 4 tablespoons of oil to brown roast.
Add onions and flour and just as onions begin to turn lighter, add mushroom soup.
As the liquids thicken, add 1 soup can of water or more to thin the gravy.
Cover and cook in 375° oven for about 2 hours or until done.

title: copper pennies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Blend all other ingredients into a sauce.
Pour sauce over vegetables.
Place in covered dish. Refrigerate overnight.
Will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks.

title: mom's banana bread
directions: Using electric mixer, cream sugar and margarine together on medium speed. Add eggs and beat. Stir in flour, alternating with sour milk. Stir in mashed bananas. Bake at 350° in 9 1/2
x 5 1/4-inch greased loaf pan for one hour, or until done.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add all ingredients except flour; mix well.
Gradually blend in flour and add walnuts if desired.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
